Played for a while, but lately I play game and make progress, make sure the game has saved my progress to the cloud, and when I come back to play again, it's as if I had not logged into game collected prizes for my progression or that I spent both money and gold in game for an upgrade. Game is decent to play but if it can not save my progress why on earth would anyone want to play it. Am very happy I did not spend real money in game. It's very frustrating to get on game and earn both gold and money, go to settings upload my progress, look at date and time and is current on supposed on the save to cloud, save even a second time, log out and come back on and it never happened. Game comes back as if I had not logged in all week and still giving me prizes I have collected at least seven times from last weekend's event.

They try so hard to hide the fact that this is NOT a first-person shooter, it's an ON-RAILS, ARCADE LIGHT-GUN-STYLE SHOOTER. If you don't know, that means you don't actually move your character, the game places you in one position from which you shoot a few enemies before being moved forward (like you're on tracks). It's a very competent example of an on-rails shooter, but since they tried to pretend it's a FPS to get my download, I'll rate it as a FPS.

I'm going to give it 3 for now. I've ran into an issue of the game staying stuck on the loading page while the the game goes on. I can hear the sound effects and can shoot by touching the screen but can't see anything. I just did the update hoping that would fix it, but it didn't. It does it on all game modes and I'm going to uninstall it and re install it to see if that works. otherwise it's a pretty awesome FPS for mobile games. Winning while using the DRONE in SNIPER OPS is IMPOSSIBLE. How do you expect us to hit our targets when the drones point of view the crosshairs are white and the background is bright white, and super light green. The drones point of view needs to be changed so it looks just like the rest of the game. The sniper zoom button on the left side of the screen needs to be moved to the right side of the screen near the trigger. It screws things up when moving the crosshairs onto a target.

Really enjoyed the time I spent with the game. It reminded me a lot of Time Crisis with the popping in and out of cover. However, I have given it a one star review because, upon logging on past the first day, I was greeted with MANY popups for different special deal packs all ranging in price from $15-40. I'm talking like five, in a row, that appear individually, with no 'don't show again' options. It was intrusive and exhausting, and ultimately slaughtered my love of the gameplay.

The game overall is fun. However, the timers on their free crates are broken. They start at 4 hours and you can watch a video to reduce this by 50%. The problem is that sometimes when you logout and come back the timer has gone back up to full amount as if you didn't watch a video to reduce it. Game breaking? No. Annoying? Definitely. EDIT: changing to 1 star until the developers fix the free crate issue.

It was cool at first, good, ok, and now just boring. Even when clicking and watching tons of ads the outcome is low towards progression. Not worth my money to consider investing in either. All I'm really doing is replaying alot of the older levels to even have a chance at later levels. Even so there is a 2 or 3 try limit with who knows how long before you can try the level again which instantly becomes a game limitation which ideally I dislike being limited in games.

Fun game that I really liked. I liked playing it occasionally when I was at the doctor's office or otherwise having to wait. But all day every day it constantly sends notification trying to get you back to open the game to get this reward or that. I already get enough notification throughout the day, with text and emails I don't need some stupid game constantly setting my phone off and annoying me. I'll uninstall.

This game was fun, but for whatever reason, I dont know if its just me or what but, when im aiming at the bad guys, my cross hairs seem to go all over the place and my shots and bloom are all over the place like theres a glitch or something. No similar issues with any other games or apps.

content: The levels are repetitive sequences and get to a point where it's completely pointless to play. The levels get harder and harder and difficult to pass. And the "hacker" missions are way too difficult and conteols suck. No dotted aim means you're just firing and then adjusting

Why you keep deleting my comments (I bought a new phone and opened the game on it everything from the beginning Where is the progress you made in the game Where is the time you spent in this game and where is the money you spent I advise everyone not to pay or buy anything inside this game because you will not get anything just for a simple change)

Its very booring when played so many times . It becomes hard level later since we dont have cards for upgradation . It is just shooting . Nothing interesting. We cannot change our position unless our cover becomes damaged . Needs more improvement. The game size does not suit for the gameplay. Thank you. Waiting for the company's reply.

You hit the P2W paywall within 5 minutes. Probably the fastest I've ever hit a paywall in any mobile game ever, and that's saying something. Shooting is wonky, your accuracy is perfect the first couple levels and then MAGICALLY it's trash once you get past the hand holding first levels. Then of course everything is Ads or $$ to open boxes to upgrade everything extremely slowly with terrible gains. Beware, it's a cash grab. A waste too it's not bad.

Control, graphics, are good, shooting seems realistic but let's be frank not all can use money to play the game.... I am left with lots of skills to upgrade, but lack of game currency makes the upgrade difficult,...it will be nice if the developers, can allow players play the zombie mode, or previous complete 3 stars level without the use of ‚ö° energy to generate game currency!!!!.... I have like 3 skills to upgrade, I can't play the next level because my combat level is not up to what is needed,

Only the good thing is the graphics.very expensive upgrading . Time taking menu. At first it seems that it is very good but later on it keeps becoming more and more bad.it is a total disaster. I think next time when you must improve on your game.
Game play is okay. Not much to it, point and shoot. Don't expect to play any longer than 5 minutes per session, that is unless you want to pay money, lots of it.

content: Will revise to 5 stars if you fix the buttons that are supposed to mute SFX and music. Not being able to listen to podcasts/music while playing this game (which i play to kill time) is absolutely infuriating. It really can't be that hard to address this issue, you certainly have extensive ways to make money from in app purchases so why not address something so basic as mute function. The buttons exist, they simply don't do anything.

Graphics are great. One star because the aiming is horrible! Game requires headshot missions but you gotta shoot the guy in the damn head like 20 times! I really enjoy difficult games but this is just annoying!!! Ok some missions want like five headshots, with 70% heath, and can't use more than 50 rounds. So you shoot one guy in the head 20 freaken times with another guy shooting you, when u shoot the other guy you've used more than 50 rounds and you have no health cause the aiming is so lousy!

Good game, last few levels near impossible without "perks". According to app, loot rate for perks in small crates is 58%. I've used 100s of gold coins won through events etc to get crates with virtually no perks such as health, slow motion. Definitely not near 58%. I can't help but suspect this is closely link to my progress in the game which is complete for almost all but last 3 levels, just a few objectives not achieved. In other words pay to win as you approach final objectives

Its a great game, but i think the drone missions need better performances with the drone control. Also the trigger happy mission is really terrible(the truck movement, the target and all that).I feel the missions are too little in number and the energy capacity for special missions should be looked into.... You guys should just fix the drone missions already, they're freaking annoying, like the drone basically controls itself for 75%of the mission, its 1star till its done

Great GamePlay, Characters, and weapons. Attention to detail was put in considering its a mobile game. However, after completing Episode_12 missions, it does not want to move on to new Episodes for more than five months+.... It's locked, and written Coming Soon. After spending money and purchasing perks, I'm now left with nothing to play. Just replaying old missions, upgrading weapons and armour that one will never use.

This game is not moving ahead of 75%. After killing a final boss of level 9.9, it gets hang and not moving further. Guys don't waste your time if you are very eager to complete the game 100%.. because it is not going to happen... Another very irritating this is to open the cards, while opening cards you need to click on each and every cards all the time, which is very frustating, irritating, time consuming and senseless, rather it should be opened automatically.. I wasted my time to reach at 75%

Ridiculous and robbery. Have playes off and on for over a year and now when i log into the game with Google it no longer gives me the option to continue with my saved progress. it shows brand new games in local and cloud. i just purchases a subscription and 3 packs same day for nothing. have emailed 2 times and gotten no response

Before you install please note you only have a max of 10 energy. You also need energy to do any of the broken buggy missions. Like when you have to use a rocket propeled grenade launcher to take down 2 suvs and to get perfect you can only use 3 rockets. 3 rockets to take down 2 suvs doesnt sound too hard but when you have to lead the target before you fire and get a direct hit to even have a chance to destory them its really horrible.

wepons you can pick are useless. Famas is the best assault. u can find others w/ better attributes, but dont make real difference.here is the thing:lower cadency is better. Bc the game is badly done so it cannot register so many sots in a second, so u waste ammo and sometimes 3 clips to kill when u would kill w/ a couple bullets using the basic arms. The loot crates give u useless cards when all u need is MONEY. the free money from watching ads is always the same, even if u are in a high level.

Doesnt open on my samsung note 10 plus. It stuck at google play login, it keeps loading nothing happens. And I searched in internet found some solutions to clean cache but didnt work and tried to clear data but after that the game shows "expansion file not found. Connect a wifi and download again" seriously? I'm on my high speed wifi but this cant even identify that! And I'm wondering if it doesnt work on world's best device on market which can take it!

Yes at first game nice, But at few chapters it is very not reasonable to that task they ask you to do, Some of that captures you can see they require you to buy for healing and etc, Even your lvl already full upgrade, But when you shot it is still the same, And few area are totally open space with no cover and you need to fight with so many enemies! Even if at real situation also you died. You need to search and try to shot one by one that clones then you can know which one. NO SUGGEST PLAY!!!

Was 5 star...and could be again if the bug preventing headshots in 13-7 Flammable gets fixed. The only thing preventing mastery of the game. Edit... now 1 star. Several dozen comments from players and I've sent 2 messages directly to them. 2 bug fixes/updates have been released and this one isn't fixed so no way to actually win.

Way, way, way to expensive to play!! I've been playing for over a year and due to the ludicrously low earnings for running missions and daily tasks, I can't even get to level 7 on upgrades. Fun game but expect to pay a ton of real money to get anywhere in this game! #notworthit

I think there is a glitch in chapter 13-7 flammable. One of the objective is to get 6 headshots to achieve a star, even though using perks and trying to clear the stage several times, it seems impossible to get 6 headshots. Even though you fire on the enemy's head, it doesn‚Äôt count the kill as a head shot. If the developers are reading this, please get it fixed. Other than that i give it a 5 stars rating for sure

Level 13-7 is impossible to beat with 6 headshots. There videos all over YouTube with people saying they cant beat it. Literally not 1 video of someone beating it. Yet the maker of the game has done nothing to fix the issue even though it's been going on for almost a year. Don't waste your time with this game

This game is awesome. Graphics is awesome. Game play os awesome. The only reason i am giving 1 star is because in missions with air strike where you take control of drone it does not work. First I loved this game but now it's boring

content: Not really what I was expecting based on the screenshots. Its advertised as something that resembles a third person action shooter. Its more of a on the rails shooter where you don't actually control your character's movement, your character moves for you when you've cleared the current section. The game is essentially a modern version of an old school arcade game from the 90s where you shoot enemies on the screen and then move when they're dead.

Not that great, game has a limit to how long you play by using up an "energy" every mission. Sure you can switch to a different game once you run out, but it's not good when a game forces you to do so rather than choosing to do so when you want. Plus it's pretty much an on rails shooter which is a turn off(atleast the first 3 missions were.)

Meh, started off by trying to force me to buy 'special' offer before even starting, no option to wait and play first. went pretty smooth up until the point where it damn near impossible to play, on third level. Then you have to upgrade to where it can cost major bucks to go further. instead of a few kills at a time, now there are 20 plus grenades. the quests to get 3 stars is stupid and irrelevant. got to only use half of ammo to get a star?!?! then the 10 ways (@$5 each) to make yourself better.

Honestly just extremely repetitive, and the progression is so freaking slow. You virtually do the same mission over and over with no real feel of accomplishment. The only good thing about this game is the graphics, the even then the animation is extremely stiff and stale. Just don't waste your time on this until they actually care about the people playing the game.

Fun at first. But they have these "missions" that require an "energy" to use. The maximum energy you can have is 10, and once you use those, you have to wait like 10 min to get another energy. And you can only do each mission 3 times. To do it again, you have to pay like 30 gold to get another 3 tries. And to get gold, you can get a little bit in chests after completing missions, but the main way to get gold is to PAY. I uninstalled, because there are better uses of your time.

fun first person shooter. too much time (1hr) to wait for a skill to become available. we already wait a while to get the cash to upgrade a skill. and they get more expensive. either lower the cash required or the time. Uninstalled the app after I got stuck on a level because I didn't have enough money to upgrade the player and couldn't make it any other way. Waste of time.

Full design is pay to win. Completely annoying. You get a few upgrades at first, which YOU NEED. Then you're never strong enough for the next level, which is very short. I can't stand this set up. Good graphics. Horribly greedy setup. 1 star for set another one for graphics. Uninstall.

its alright. the missions are fun and all but controls are quite bad. i don't see the point to the scope button. If no-scope, it gets pulled up anyway before u can shoot. how to zoom in/out via scope is never taught. -1 for that. ideally it should be pretty intuitive. Also, placement of scope button in the same half as aim zone? -2 for this UI decision. Lastly, it's really hard to shoot a single bullet as assault coz u have to keep holding even after peeking to shoot. toxic for accuracy missions.

Nah, I don't like it. Not enough freedom of movement, the area to control the aim is too tight, impossible to 100% due to ridiculous mission requirements combined with loaded set up and disqualifying previous accomplishments on following attempts [level 10: get 10 headshots without being detected; only 3 enemies, one moves, and the angle doesn't allow for accomplishing both]. It was fun for the first 9 levels, then it quickly lost its appeal. Not for me. Deleted.

Game graphics are really nice. Gameplay, not so much. Slow to develop and repetitive. Controls are odd. Assault rifle you literally hold and not tap to shoot. Sniper is tap. Sniper you can zoom and scoping in only happens if you either tap or hold the icon, which one I couldn't figure out. Then it zoomed in and I didn't know that could happen nor how I did it and I couldn't zoom out. Also clear that you'll have to pay sooner or later. Uninstalled

Good Game, Terrible Customer Support. Taking into consideration that this is a mobile game, this was a huge waste of money. I always try supporting a product when I like it so I made a couple purchases. But due to a technical glitch I lost everything. I'm waiting here 1 week later and no response or acknowledgement. Not just a waste of money but also time.

OK game, good play. BUT can't play after so far unless you pay. They stop doing the bonus extras, and the game does get too hard to play with out buying stuff. Uninstalled, now it won't reinstall. Customer service won't answer so it stays off. Too bad, adds were not intrusive, and you could watch them for actual items.

its an ok game, very challenging! BUT theres a HUGE problem with the timer for crates & rewards! I'll collect a free crate, then use a video to half the time to 2 hrs,,, and when I come back later,, it still says I have 3 1/2 hrs left! Thats killing my collections, and waisting my speed ups!! This needs to be fixed, then good game!

Game is overall fine. It's obvious they want you to spend money. Drop rates for upgrade cards and money is very lopsided, I have hundreds of upgrade cards, but no cash to complete upgrades. Wait times for energy to refill is too long. Rewards for completing a level/boss should be higher. Controls in moving vehicles (drone, trucks, mech) are too sensitive for small screen on a phone.

If I can hit someone with a headshot using janky phone controls it should kill, kinda like the real world. Uninstalled, clearly designed to get people to make microtransactions to keep up with the difficulty curve.

Graphics & gameplay are really good, for the style it is. However, no instructions/info avail to really learn all of the gameplay components, so disappointing & a bit frustrating. However the serious drawback is the near constant bombardment by demands for IN-GAME PURCHASES. Very definitely a PAY-TO-PLAY game. And, for style of gameplay it provides, which is only basically pulling a trigger, it most definitely IS NOT WORTH the time/effort. I support Developers, but not this one ‚òπÔ∏è Uninstalled

Starts well, but makes virtually no use of characters other than the Assault and Sniper characters. Some early game episodes require a little skill to master. Late game episodes are made difficult by adding ridiculous obstacles (hundreds of explosive canisters everywhere for no reason) and one is bugged where it is impossible to complete the achievements. Additional bugs include aim spot being way off target (tunnel chase) and character models not holding weapons correctly.

I accidentally deleted the app and it disappointed me because it didn't save my progress even though it is connected to my Google account. I was chapter 11 and 990 combat level with 17 exp level. So annoyed with this kind of game where it didn't save progress.

At first, this game was fun and I was able to complete the levels without buying more $ or gold. Then I got to the Psycho soldier and wasn't able to beat him. I even bought more gold for health packs and still can't beat him. Also, you shouldn't have to empty your entire magazine to kill someone. You draw cards for other characters and guns, but you can't actually use these until you draw 15 cards for them. Also, the best part of the game was the 1 mech level. Why not more?? A total waste of $$!

IMPOSSIBLE TO COMPLETE As many people have already stated in their reviews; there is a widely known bug in stage 13-7 that has been around for a long time that prevents anyone from completing that stage with the full 3 star score. In that stage you are required to get 6 headshots; however, the only enemy entities with working headshot detection are the huminoid robots (of which there are only 2).

The actual time time fighting is way too short and the time in between campaigns is littered with confusing options to upgrade everything by, of course, making in app purchases. It's as if gameplay wasn't only a second thought, but 3rd thought.

content: The stages are short that suits playing whenever you have a little break time. Not a true fps feeling. Gamers are standing behind the shooter. In true fps games, we see only the weapon (imagining that we are holding it). The other negative point is that the game moves the player for you after a kill. It's really quite dull. I gave it two stars for the gunfire sound, but I quickly uninstalled it after playing it but once.

Decent gameplay quickly gives way to needing expensive "crates" to get "cash" to pay for the upgraded abilities that are required in order to have any hope of progressing. The crates are EXPENSIVE compared to other games. Instead of $1-5 micro transactions they want more like $15. You will unlock and need the upgrades way faster than you can ever hope to earn "cash" to pay for them. Video ads can supposedly be played to earn cash but are regularly "not available" with no explanation.

Great game to play. Just bad that upgrades take so long. And in campaign mode there is a glitch or something in level 13-7 flammable. Its impossible to get 3 stars. And in campaign mode it does say how long you have to wait for episode 14.

Greedy. Greedy. Greedy. All they want is your $$ and they do everything possible to get u to do so. Takes 2 energy a play, takes forever to level up, the crates %90 of the time never have anything useful like health and slow motion. They keep giving u 3 and four skill crates that are already astronomically overloaded and if u had all the $ and gold in the world it still would be impossible to catch up. The crosshairs are clear and they have u sniping in snow, all part of the money grab. Fun but$

Sniper mode the targets are way too small. The cross hairs sometimes become dam near invisible. You can only use the health recovery once per mission. Crates give you the same cards even though they're fully upgraded and never the cards you actually need (makes you spend more). Started off fun but became increasingly frustrating. Waste of money. Uninstalled

content: Its nice to find a game that is offline playable. That said it is still a pay to win game. Progress is agonizingly slow unless you are willing to spend real a lot of real money. I think that there would be a great number of people that would pay 20 to 30 dollars to unlock the whole game with an accelerated loot drop system, as opposed to the current way of play. I like the graphics the controls are good, a duck option would be helpful.

Updated 01/15/21: Pretty good for an offline mobile shooter game. The game doesn't get stuck waiting for a network connection in between missions and the controls are easy to use. Other shooters I have tried have clunky controls, made it difficult to move and shoot at the same time. The graphics are decent enough and the game play is quite engaging. However, at late game boss fights becomes impossible to beat without using perks, which can be difficult to obtain from free loot crates.

Well the game plays alot like games from around 1999. Game play is extremely linear with no controller support. In fact the settings menu is almost non existent with very little or no control. So for me this game is not fun at all. With all the advancements in technology we shouldn't be playing in the past with gameplay and controls. To only offer primitive touch is very noob.

My first shooter. It starts out really fun, but then heads off into space and zero g and that felt like a different game. I enjoyed the combat in the jungle, city, etc but it felt like the game lost confidence in itself and just started throwing all these high concept ideas at you. If it had just stuck to more complex and challenging levels like the beginning of the game it would have been a lot better.

It's fun, but for about 2 minutes at a time -- like so many games these days. It's a quick level, and then clicking on upgrades and loot boxes for the next 5 minutes. The home screen has 21 different things to click on! It's UI insanity and clickbait. Here's my unsolicited advice: simplify everything, and make the levels longer than 2 minutes.

Awesome game with great graphics. As always the upgrades are endless and of course you have to pay A LOT of real money for them. You can earn coins in the game to buy upgrades at outrageous prices. And the equipment you can earn by completing level's, never seem to be the the ones that you need. It takes away from the fun of the game because it's so obvious that you will never get the items you need without paying ridiculous prices for them. For that reason 3 stars.

The game is really fun, the controls and graphics are Amazing especially for mobile. I just have one problem, I've been playing for a few weeks now and its just then that I've noticed it hasn't saved any of my achievment progress. Which is a bummer! since I am trying to build my gamerscore. Its a fun app but Im thinking of deleting it if my achievements aren't even being saved. I would like to have my achievements restored if possible. I rank 8! In this game I would like my achievments to show.

Solid game, some parts do require internet! Graphics are good, stamina to keep going gains rather slowly (without wasting 'gold' or spending real $). Over all 3 stars, definitely room to make improvements. controls could be better & options to switch cover & move around would be great. being stuck in one spot only to run to the next gets rather old.

A pretty decent cover shooter. I would rate it higher, but some of the timed missions are a bit ridiculous. The Sniper Special Ops Night Missions in particular have extremely short and frustrating timers. It's difficult to get your bearings, locate all your targets, and shoot all the targets in the allotted time. The Zombie special event had its own issues, like the character standing in needlessly vulnerable spots when she could've taken a few steps and gained a tactical advantage. Okay game.

Don't try too hard. You can clean all stages and get all stars. Once you hit the final level, that is over. The final sniper level requires 6 headshots, but doesn't register any headshots on any of the enemies. The final level requires 40% health, but is a gauntlet of 3 - 12 enemy holograms firing on you in the open with no cover while you find the real one, until they shuffle and you have to start again. (Takes about 4 shuffles to kill one enemy) Online is ok, but last levels slap in the face..

Very Expensive to play...It started out good, but quickly escalated to having to use real money buying cash, gold, equipment cards and upgrades to your abilities. In the 8th level, final mission, you have to shoot various targets while riding in the bed of a truck down a long tunnel...the game started glitching, and was jumping from frame to several frames ahead, making aiming and shooting very frustrating.

Good game. Have been playing for a couple months. Some levels are very difficult and I'm only on level 11. My biggest complaint is the layout, using Samsung Galaxy Tab A, of the aimong/movement/fire controls for the sniper in the Battle side mission. Between the secondary zoom and settings tab, invisible until, SURPRISE, you open it, there is practically no room for even one finge (Precious secs fly by as you discover controls don't function properly because settings was opened and altered.)

I love the graphics in this game. That's my favorite part besides the very low amount of forced ads. My three star rating is because of the gameplay mainly. You can't move at all except for popping up and shooting. I downloaded this thinking it was like Bullet Force or something where you could play against bots hence the offline feature, but it turned out to be an rpg which really got old after the first chapter. Make more features and I will redownload

Good aimtrainer for mobile, and is is completely usable offline, one thing that bothers me is the fact that you have to wait for a certain time to get more coins/tokens to play and they're hella expensive too, what like $4.99 for 10 of them which takes 8 hours to reload??!! Anyway i also think that free moving would be nice and not just a designated area to stand and shoot. But if your looking for an aimtrainer for mobile that doesnt lag, then this is a good choice fpr you.

Originally got this as an offline option for a plane ride, it served its purpose. Much like the majority of the reviews here the game is fun and addicting and then hits a combat level ceiling and thats where the game loses motivation to continue. I wouldnt have put a cap on levels as upgrading is the fun part of dominating through past levels.

Seems like a good game, just not for me I guess. The aiming is a little weird and causes me to lose a lot challenges in the levels. Instead of having a finite area to move your aim, why not just have a simple joystick? I only got to stage 4 in the first chapter and we decided to quit.

Ill admit im conflicted because the game itself is AWESOME everything about it is excellent. My ONLY problem with it is it takes SO much to achieve so little unless your willing to buy gold. other than that the grind to get enough cash in order to level up your skills...takes forever. the drop rate for characters and weapons is low and takes ...forever. other than that a good game but the grind has made it boring and repetitive.

The game is an interesting game... But, the problem I have is that, the civilian you are saving in zombie mode most times blocks your line of firing, sometimes you end up shooting them and then game over. Also there is no scope for assault rifles, but only for sniper why? The scope is very important, especially when shooting enemies at a distance. Scope increases the accuracy of the shots.

This is a polished app. Game mechanics work very well and controls are good. It has the potential to be a good game. The menus and different game screens are well designed. What I did not like about this game is that you spend more time getting cards and navigating the menu system an all the in between actual game play screens than actually playing. I would suggest focusing more on actual game play and less on the upgrades, crates, characters etc.. Make levels and missions longer and larger.

Great gameplay and graphics, but doesn't take too long before you have to buy in-app purchases to make any progress. After a couple days of playing you will find yourself repeatedly playing the same skirmish levels over and over just to make enough cash to progress and that gets boring fast. The only other option is to shell out tens or hundreds of dollars per week... Too bad as it could be a truly great game. I'd happily do a one-time payment for the game, but not $50+/week for ongoing purchases just to be allowed to play...

content: Excellent game in every aspect. Truly love how you're not forced to see ads, but instead they reward you with game $$$ if you choose to do so and that for me is amazing, quite intelligent actually. Review edit: Even though I love this game, there comes a point where you already have every gun, every character and can't get more upgrades for your characters. You keep on getting unusable money, because there's nothing to do with it. You guys have an awesome concept, it just needs minimal tweaking.

Pretty good and challenging 3rd person rail shooter. Played for a couple weeks and have seemigly maxxed my card levels and am at combat level 1250. Yet I am constantly being challenged by levels 1300 and higher, but I do not see how that it is possible to go above 1250?? Small screens and dark levels can be challenging. The boat levels are almost impossible as the aim is too wobbly, popping in/out cover too slow,and the crosshairs are impossible to see.The boss level with swarms is impossible 11

I like the game so far...has nice graphics...I do like that if u don't have enough cash to pay for your skill upgrades, u can use the gold bars to pay the rest of it...but I don't like the mission rewards from campaign...should give more cash amounts to be able to pay for the skills with...the skills get more expensive as u upgrade n I understand that to keep the game exciting...but u end up using all your energy before u can make enough to pay for them

The game is very short... However, kudos on the ads. Other games should take example. There are ads of course, but you don't have to watch any of them. Ads are ONLY for bonuses, no ads for just playing. Most games try to squeeze ads in between levels and whatnot. Not this one. You can play 2 hours straight without watching a single ad and that is extremely refreshing. The problem is, if you play 2h straight, you might just finish the whole game. It is quite short..

As someone else commented, once youve maxed out all skill cards and have all characters and weapons, there's not much to strive for. Once you DO have max skills, stages becomes much easier. The stages are mixed, with assault, sniper, and demolition levels. One gripe that I have is that you can't change the color of the targeting reticle. It's permanently set to white, and is almost impossible to see during sunlit stages. Big plus: game is totally F2P, but you can spend money if you choose.

Good game initially but short lived. The game play and campaigns are fun. Timed battles are a nice option. The events were fun but I think someone has forgotten to turn them on periodically. I played a couple phases but now it has been "coming soon". There is value in changing characters and weapons to complete campaigns. It isn't always about using the same set up every time. I just wish the events would come back and there wasn't such a quick ceiling on skills. Also...no ads...no p2p.

First of all, this is a great game in everyway, graphics are good and the experience is smooth and most importantly the game doesn't show adss unless you requested them. But I encountered two problems: one, I can't access events any more, all I see is coming soon, second, although I've finished all the levels in Episode 12 it still shows 91% missions complete. Please fix the two problems and we'd all be great full.

Not many games can deliver a free offline game experience. And this one delivers. You can upload your progress to the cloud too.  Only downside is the way you collect characters and upgrade your skills. Also  things like heath rations are hard to get. Most of the items you get are buy opening up crates.  I still like this game though. And I play it from time to time on my subway rides.

Absolutely beautiful game with amazing design and plenty of choice. But it pushes microtransactions way too much. I cant open the game without getting at least one "special deal". I just opened the game and had to wait on four or five game ads to even see the menu. This app deserves five stars, and I would give it that if it weren't for this.

The game is fun! Good graphics, many levels and interesting story line. It has a vast selection of firearms and characters. However, the game makes progression time consuming and slow. You have to pay if you want to progress in a timely fashion and the prices are not cheap. Its a great game but the developer should make it a little more accommodating for those without the capability of paying.

Great FREE game. Levels are challenging until you build up weapons and stats. 13 levels of missions in the game so far. 13-7 needs to be fixed. It appears you cannot complete this mission. Support does not seem to be very responsive to questions or bug reports. This could very easily be a 5 star game if the developers were more responsive.

The game is a lot of fun, the graphics are solid, and the controls are pretty good. It scales up the difficulty at a reasonable rate. Energy depletes super quickly, though, so it's not a bingeable game. Plus, the money required to upgrade skills takes forever to acquire.

This is the most sterling game I've come across so far, a rock solid 5* straight across the board BUT it is also the most slanted game also, too slanted. You pay a premium for premium games, I get it, I even support it, I've made 3 purchases so far but this game goes beyond that!!! I'm sticking with it, it's fun & challenging, but I don't agree with its cost from a certain point on(-1*). As far as playing it, I'm not sure you can beat it, smooth, creative, tight, responsive, but sadly, slanted.

I play this Game everyday almost it's a very fun game probably the best game on the app store and it's free and offline so you can play anywhere. I'd love to give it 5 stars but it does has 1 issue that really bugs me and that's the reticle it is very hard to see at times as the current color of it blends into the environment. It would be a really nice addition to be able to customize the size and color of the reticle. Also a way to use In game money to buy perks would be nice. Download asap

Videos for boxes/perks/upgrades or faster upgrades does NOT work. üòíüòû It makes the game go blank, then restarts slowly fron the opening loading page. _PLEASE FIX for my device: Android, LG Stylo 4 (w/ Boost Mobile service). Even so, it's a VERY FUN GAME! Challenging enough to keep you on your toes! (Some boss levels have almost made me give up on the game; the 1st 1 with an enormous drone to take down: seems impossible w/out perks & can't get any perks while not passing levels.)

I love this game! The gameplay is really fun and easy to learn! The grafics are about as good as they could be too -- for a game designed for phones. However, the plot is undeveloped, scatterbrained, illogical, and hard to follow. If this game had a more understandable, exciting, developed storyline, this game would be an EASY 5 stars.

So far love the app just one thing..... With the sniper, and im not sure if its my device or not but after I aim and shoot, let's say i miss, then I try to move while aiming, as i did before i shoot, it resets. Then i gotta get it perfect, without EVER moving my finger off the screen, just to get a shot off. I have learned myself to work around it but its still annoying lol! Other than that, Great Game, Very worth downloading :) !!!

Awesome shooter game. Easy controls, great graphics, lots of characters and weapons. been hooked since i downloaded it. I have a few issues though...upgrades for cards are really expensive and take forever to complete, not enough demolition or hacker levels, and i keep getting the same cards to unlock characters and weapons all the time even after they are already unlocked. All in all it's a great game.

Controls are decently responsive (would be better if I used a keyboard and mouse I'm sure). Its been a fun game so far with different challenges. I'm limiting my review to 4 stars because assault missions in campaign mode are by far my least favorite type (of three available), and represent 80% of the missions.

It's a great game and I really enjoyed it. The reasons why I'm rating this 4 stars instead of 5 is because 1. Ads are a bit annoying and 2. When I play a hard level and can't beat it, I usually have to wait a couple of days to upgrade making it so I end up not playing as much and then deleting it. Great game though, nice graphics, characters etc.

Just what you would expect. cover, shoot and only get so far unless you pay. Your survival chances depend on your cover but unlike all other cover games, you can't change cover unless the game allows you to. Which is never unless your up against a big boss. Then still they control when you can cover. I gave it a 4 for graphics but it's not hard to find a better shooter.

Game is good. Each mission is short, takes less then a minute on most of them to complete. Like others said, 13-7 has a flaw where you can't get the headshots needed for a perfect score. There has been no updated missions except for skirmishes. I'm maxed out at 1250 and have everything unlocked so just doing skirmishes is getting a little boring. How is anyone over 1250? I'll keep the game and hope for more chapters and challenges.

Fun, addicting game. Plenty of options so far (~75% in) of playing with a few optional ads and no payments for upgrades. It's a offline game, but really have to have some internet at times. I can't see beating the game without any internet connection. It is possible, but someone's lucky, or skilled, or has ALOT of time on their hands. If I find out this is a CCP game, take this as one star.

A good on-the-rails shooter with easy to use controls and pretty satisfying combat. For a Free-2-Play game, it is quite generous with consumables and upgrades. I've made it quite far without spending a penny. Though you will find yourself grinding early missions often, it is nowhere near as bad as other freemium games.

ALMOST a 5 star game! No real money needed. I was able to make it to the end with gold star on every level except the glitched one of course. I kept replaying the missions in level 6,7,8,9 that give you grenades and medicine. I stock piled them! That monkey boss level was tough without being able to slow down time for me. I hope the DEV sees our comments and fixes the glitched level. The zombies and battle missions are really fun although I feel the opponents are just bots and not real players.

Best cover based shooter I've played on Android. Wish the game had a way to grind for gold, as I've already finished this game. Powers are all upgraded. Only thing left to do is unlock characters... things is, I'm not into completionism. While the game had something to do, I was very fun. Hope they'll be more to come in the future. üòÅüëç *Would give this game 5 stars if it had some sort of PvE wave mode for assault replayability.

I have collected all the weapons, characters, and have all skills to max. Overall, I had fun with this game. Sometimes it can be a little grindy waiting for chests and upgrading skills. Mutilplayer is simply shoot more people than your opponent. Level 6 just uses Black Ops' Nuketown map(?), and I'm still working on 100% the game (level 13-7 is giving me trouble, and some boat levels). Sometimes you have to be a little patient with chests and skills, but it's overall a fun game that I enjoyed.

Here's the problem in sniper ops the area is too big, and the enemy too far apart to kill them all in such a short amount of time. I have not completed not 1 of the sniper ops missions. Either give more time I'm thinking 1:30 for easy 1:00 for normal, and :30 for hard, and or make the area smaller and the enemy closer together. Also there's no cover so when you're not running out of time you're being killed so please provide some coverage. Please fix all of this in the next update thank you.

An overall good game you just peek and hide while shooting enemy's. There are boss fights and a full story as well as other game modes. You can upgrade your ability and even unlock other character's throughout the campaign. The only thing I think would make the game better is interchangeable weapons and maybe more freedom with your traversal.

Cool game. Great graphics. Very tough. I wish you could get the health packs, grenades, and time slow things by using your earned gold coins or dollars. You really do need them to assist you, but you don't earn enough of them through normal play. I will not buy them with real money. You earn gold coins and dollars in the game and need to use them to get more perks.

This is the best game on the market, HANDS DOWN! Challenge, achievable, takes talent. Not just how much you can buy. And they have plenty to sell. But I get it. And they do too. Make the ads pay for it. But not mandatory, game play is challenging if you want a boost ok...after these messages. Genius. The reason there is a 4 instead if a 5. Sometime the toggle control sticks (only moves when you are not aiming. But the MAIN reason is the only black character had the ONLY NEGATIVE skill*.(5+T.Rex)

Very nice and interesting game but very hard to control most especially in the hackers level you'll find it very difficult to aim your target the machine will be just roaming about not the way you want it, and also when you're in the ship levels. We'll be great full if you upgrade this problem for us.

I'm gonna give this 4.5 stars. Brilliant game. Pity its spoiled by old fashioned "Energy" recharges to play missions. Which means you can only play for so long. Limited Ad options are handy to gain more but they stop pretty quickly. Unlimited Ad options would pay for the game in itself. Cupl of bugs too. For some reason bad guys can detect you through brick walls and buildings even though you cant see them directly to take down. Perks another money issue but still worth spending a few bucks on.

Have been looking for a new game and this appears to be an interesting one. Through no fault of yours the controls are difficult for me due to neuropathy in my hands. I would like settings that allows me the option to eliminate background music etc.

The gun sight is hard to see in a lot of the areas due to the background. Of course the weapons are very expensive like most of the games and the weapons are slow to reload. You can get to a certain point and either spend real money to upgrade or delete the game because you won't go any further.

It's a fun game controls are not bad but seems like u can't hold the directional control feels like u have to slide it which requires me to reposition my thumb again. I wish the receptacle or the sight can be better to see it. But over all it is a good game with good graphics

Nice game, good graphics, cool storyline. Being able to play both off & online is a true gem, honestly. A bit more improvement with the controls though, seems a bit shaky, especially in sniper mode, other than that, great all rounder.

The only thing that make it 4 Star rating is that I can't get special pecks which makes it difficult to finish some messions (e.g kill enemy with grenade) , so it will be easier if I could buy pecks I want. Please fix connection error in special pecks

Addictive! Right up to the point where the game just runs out, and no further levels are available, just reads 'coming soon' for further missions. Awesome game, disappointed it's just stopped and hasn't been further developed.

Surprisingly, a very nice game indeed. I really didn't think a free shooting game on mobile could be very nice, yet this game is really amazing! It is fun to play, very well set up and genuinely fantastic game! No ads, no forcing you to buy anything, no waiting a day to play again (like for "lives" to recharge). Thank you truly, for a great game, it is always appreciated.

So far I think it's a great game that has potential for improvement. I think you should add a win streak bonus in skirmish battle that awards more plates. Also, similar to how you award gold when a player has already unlocked a character or weapon, you should award cash when a player has maxed out a skill and gets that card from a mission or chest.

Good game but some improvements needed. When the game was still from Genera, the skill and reward system was different. Starting characters like Liu Wong and Vladimir plus Dubstep Rifle use to be nice to use, under the old skill system. Now they have no advantages. Also how to get cutscenes? I finished the first 2 chapters with all stars and nothing, then later i play again and they're there. Other chapters no cutscenes, what's the criteria?

One of the best offline shooting I've played yet. Only down fall I found is it's really hard to get perks ( grenades, health and slow time) w/o really buying chests. I think should be in some of the cards after beating a lvl. But that's just my opinion. Other then that not one complaint.

I like the game, the graphics are nice, I love that animation when I shoot the last enemy in sniper missions....but I don't know why more episodes don't come in....I have completed episode 13 and am waiting for 14 and more episodes but they have failed to arrive....please of u can make some more....I will be grateful

Decent offline game, but grindy and some of the challenges require either psychic powers or repeat plays which would be fine if it didn't have extra rewards for getting the challenge done right the very first playthrough of a level. The energy system and tickets for the events seems off like you can't really clear out your energy so you can't just clear it and log out but you have just enough tickets to maybe do the event and get the rewards but you might need to spend gold to get the reward

It's actually a 5 star game but I said 4 cause I ain't been playing that long. If it stays the way it is I'll upgrade to 5. Action is very segmented so its convenient.

It can be a bit challenging if you're not familiar with 1st person shooter games, but overall it is definitely a fun game. So, maybe that was my earlier issue back then.

This is the best game i've played so far. Love the graphics especially, really great, but the stats damage of some of the weapons are'nt too pleasing, the sometimes make me angry, especially during assault missions. Also the perks, i really thought that i had to buy them separately, and not waiting for a crate to deliver them. However, the game is really great, ive completed most of the missions, and is only waiting for the new episodes to be unlocked.

This is a really fun game, but upgrades cost a lot and income per level is low, so it takes too long to gain enough cash to buy the next upgrade. You must upgrade to proceed, so there is a deliberate throttling of game progression to entice you spend real money. Limited energy also comes into play, so you can't continue to replay levels forever to gain cash. On a positive note, ads are far and few between, the graphics are great, and the levels are challenging but not impossible. Nice balance.

Really fun, and purchases are optional. Its not perfect in every aspect, but it is outstanding in the important areas. I am able to progress easily, provided I am willing to grind a bit, but not a lot. I take myself out of scope mode when trying to move the reticule around, sometimes. The game has events all the time. It takes awhile to run out of credits, but they regen in a hour. Its the best 'sniper' type i've played. It has a decent story. All characters and weapons can be grinded.

There is no such thing as a Perfect" game so I won't dock them for the relatively 2 'flaws' I will mention: 1) level 13-7 is impossible to clear with 3 stars and 2) still waiting for more levels. The game is fun, challenging, yet easy to learn. The gameplay is smooth, does not crash. Best part is the game DOES NOT RUN ADS and doesn't require you to spend money to win.

This game is a joy. Am not really a gamer, stuck at home like a lot of people. Figured I needed something to pass a little time here and there. It was very intuitive after just a short time of playing, the controls and gameplay. Not sure about spending money to make it easier by purchasing the goodies, maybe depends on how long I'm considered non essential. Haha. Stay safe and take those headshots..

Addicting game. The quests are really challenging and makes you want to constantly replay them for the 3 stars. Most of the time you can get 3 stars, if it's an easy level. Shots are very accurate, no hard controls. Headshots are very easy, but the one shot one kill is a bit tricker. There's an online sniper part for tickets. Overall, pretty awesome game. Reminds me of Sniper from Xbox 360. I love that game and I love this one.

Been playing this game off and on for about a month. When I do manage to play, it's hours at a time. There is plenty to do, from special missions, to sniper ops, to regular campaign, and beyond. Even though I gave five stars, I would like to point out that occasionally during elite sniper ops missions, enemies don't spawn often enough and you end up failing, even if you get headshots for time boosts. For me, this might happen one out of every 4 or 5 sniper ops missions. But still upsetting.

Really fun and unique game. Unlike a lot of other games in this genre, Cover Fire really mixes it up in terms of how the game is played. Some stages might involve shooting from a moving truck, others shooting from behind cover, and for sniper missions, the view switches from third person to first. The only thing I don't like about Cover Fire is that gameplay is limited by a credit system set up to encourage players to pay in order to play for more than about 10 to 20 minutes every few hours.

This is the best first person shooter game I've come across! Good graphics, good character and wepon options (Though adding a few more characters would be cool.) LOTS of content, very fun. My only complaint is I have no idea how to switch cover, maybe add a cover button in the coroner of the screen that allows you to select cover? All in all I've enjoyed my experience with this game so far great work guys!

I love this game. I'm not really into PVP or teaming up with others online, so this offline shooter is perfect for me. There is a skirmish mode but it's not two players trying to kill each other. You're just trying to beat another player's score. The weapons and character upgrade system isn't overly complicated. You're not forced to buy anything, everything is unlockable through gameplay. All the ads are voluntary, i.e. you can watch an ad to get a reward. Hope they add more levels soon!

This is one of the best shooter games I've played lately, hands down. Leveling up and grinding for that next upgrade gives a sense of accomplishment. The entire performance of this game was very well articulated. Its wonderful with the mechanics, graphics, and the whole aspect of it. Pissed I just stumbled upon it. although i wouldn't say no to a way to upgrade your energy capacity without the need for VIP. Roll tide and roll up

This is hands-down my favorite mobile game EVER. Definitely the best sniper experience, and I've tried them all. I refuse to pay cash for perks, which usually leads to feeling hopelessly inadequate within a few levels. With Coverfire, I get excellent graphics, a terrific variety of challenges, and am generously rewarded with bonuses and upgrades that keep me looking forward to each task toward completing the game. I feel my skills improve while staying excited and having fun for hours.

This game is awesome. Graphics and sound especially are excellent. Playing on an S9+ and everything works perfectly. Very fun and addicting. Highly recommend. Nice game, passes the time. Some missions harder then others, on any level. Strategy and accuracy is the key. Head shots, but usually takes a couple in the brain to take down. Sniper shot is one shot one kill. Boss fights are challenging, especially starting out and your gear is low. I used money 1 time, and it really didn't help to much. Could have grinded my way up. Other that I see nothing wrong.

This game is great! It keeps you engaged from the beginning with a skipable intro then your thrown right into the first campaign no wait time! It has several different playable characters that are chosen automatically for each mission which is good cause who wants to keep the same player? I usually don't play games as much anymore but this one is fast to get into for a few quick minutes then get back to work. Just try it cause it's action packed!

Fun game with secondary missions available to earn more rewards. It's highly frustrating! I do wish some of these frustrating factors will get fixed/edited by the developers.

One of the best. Would be good to have a mission where that shines.) The IAP model ruins most games, but didn't ruin this one.

A beautiful single player game. The controls are intuitive and will eventually feel like a natural extension of your hand. Must give a shout out to whoever drew the pictures! Cut and loading scenes are comic book style pieces of art. Plenty of daily bonuses to keep you checking in and playing. Upgrades, freedom to select new characters and weapons with diverse abilities...all add up to a highly addictive game to play

Best shooting game, by far!!!!! Period!!!! Awesome graphics!! Like how you can go back to previous missions and play again. Helps with gaining money to upgrade skills. Love the side missions also. Extremely impressed with this game. Graphics are above average for an offline shooter. Easy controls. Levels are fast-paced and addictive, but also short. (Makes it easier to step away for a sec and come back for more.) Only bummer about the game is the lackluster campaign story: starts off so strong then just tapers off into confusion.

Very fun ‚Äî playable and replayable for hours. Smooth gameplay, intuitive controls, and scalable graphics that are easy on the eye. Purchasable upgrades however "BUY IT NOW" screens aren't forced down your throat every other minute. I've been playing for a while now and every upgrade you can buy with currency you can also earn through objective completion. Upgrading your player and abilities isn't overly complicated and actually impacts your performance greatly in-game. Highly recommend.

Great game. I like it. Simple and easy to play but fun and addicting also. Lots of unlockables and upgrades. I'm broke and really don't have money for in-game purchases and I haven't had a problem yet or felt like the only way to play is to pay. Overall one of the best experiences I've had in gaming period console or otherwise.

Excellent App! I have truly enjoyed playing this game for the past month. I have progressed pretty far without having to pay for upgrades. You can unlock guns and characters by playing the player vs player game...you have to win about 25 times in a 3-4 day stretch. There is also a fun zombie game. I have found it fun to do the daily tasks for extra rewards. The tasks are the same every day, but they keep me checking in. I haven't even mentioned how cool the story mode is yet-get the game!

Fun shooter game. The game takes care of your character's movement, so you can focus on aiming and shooting. The missions have 3 mini objectives, which are fun to complete and really add to the enjoyment factor of the game. The event missions/contests are enjoyable, really adding to the enjoyment and replayability. I play 10-15 minute intervales through out the day (~3x per day) and then every so often a ~2 hr session to use up all the extra energy. This game makes my day brighter :)

Love It. Absolutely stunning graphics and easy controls. I think that they should probably have a setting that allows you to move the joysticks the other way around for leftys. My favorite mobile game so far. I think that this game is so good that it should be a priced game. I it were I wouldn't be able to play though. =(

Best shooter game out there. Fast loading time. lots of characters and weapons. only thing i would change is the videos that hell speed up the process of upgrades and chests were explained more. sometimes you get more than other times. Theres plenty of them, but i never know how much are available, so i dont know what to use them on. Definitely download this game.

My first day playing. Its pretty good thus far. I've blown 20 bucks on upgrades but its got me farther along . Update. 30 some odd days later. Its addictive as hell, you CAN get upgrades without making in app purchases, if you are patient.and there is a myriad of ways to get bonuses. I also like that you can complete missions in a offline single player mode, you test you shooting skills in skirmishes head to head with other random players and they have challenges pretty regularly.

I am super surprised at the quality if this game! the controls are amazing, even on a cheapo phone, and I haven't even checked if it's android controller compatible. The cover system is reminiscent of Army of Two, the grenade mechanics are alot like Crisis, I'm not sure why people complain, Iv been getting all the items you can pay for through missions and daily tasks, and there have always been videos available to get as much free stuff as possible, the pay to win is not aggressive!

I don't like writing reviews. pretty good game. 3rd person rail shooter. good controls. good casual feel. really simple once you figure out the menu options. good for killing time. has a fatigue system like most android games. has in app purchases, but aren't required.

I was totally drawn in to 'Cover Fire'. The action of the battles and skirmishes were realistic enough to make me duck bullets in my living room. The mini missions (Sniper Ops and the others) were just as good as the main feature. The characters were just as enjoyable. I only wish it didn't take so long to earn the money that was needed to upgrade my character, his weapons, his abilities, his health, and everything else. Still.... with all that being said... Its a 'kick ass' game. TRUST!!! A.K

This game is very entertaining and useful in the killing of time but i must say that it can be difficult later in the game to level up your attributes. Could you as the developer's please give us more chances to earn by watching videos and ads or maybe give us chances to win things by playing mini games that are challenging in various ways. Like for example to win 5 gold once every 5 rounds you have to play a side game and the goal is to shoot as many people or zombies as possible with set award

Great game! Excellent graphics and easy controls. Moves at a nice pace. Just like playing a game on a console and flat screen. Simple enough to play and follow that it's never frustrating or annoying, yet difficult enough that it is challenging and really keeps interest.

Really good game play, its nice to not have ads constantly! recommendation would be to have the reload faster from beginning along with the reload upgrades. its a little slow sometimes. also rework the headshot in sniper mode, when the enemy is wearing a helmet. several times I have fired a headshot. but it didnt register as a head shot with the enemy wearing a helmet

Excellent game. Very addictive and very warlike. This war simulator is top of the line and one of my favorite games. It is even good for offline play. The graphics are fine and the way the game teaches you to be accurate and calculated for better rewards is effective in the delivery. Thanks to the developers on this one.

This game rocks! The graphics are amazing especially the slow mo kills showing bullet trajectory entry exit with the ememy flying backwards on impact. SICK but Awesome! The game is broken up into levels with mini segments so you don't have to focus so intensely for too long at a time. It allows you to easily upgrade with your earnings so you don't need to spend real$ & THE CHICK WITH THE SHAVED HAIR ON THE SIDES IS A BADASS HOTTIE. OH YEAH! Hats off to the Developers! This game is sweet!

Great game. Graphics look sharp, clean and detailed on my tablet. Game play is challenging and lots of opportunities to upgrade your weapons and shooter skills without being forced to pay money. Developers did a great job. Even the ad bar is out of the way so you can enjoy the game. Great job devs. I definitely recommend this game.

Excellent game üëçüëç but they could have added dodging into the game and more gun action control the aiming is okay but needs work!! They need to keep in mind that all smart phones are not design the same as a joystick controller.!! Other than that I'm very sure that you will get great enjoyment from this game as I have and do!!!üòÅ

Definitely a great offline game. The ability to upload to the cloud storage is awesome. It has never crashed on me (big plus). I like the sniper ops missions, zombie modes and the campaign is quite satisfying as well. Graphics are good, fluidity of the game play and perks is done well.

To be honest I don't comment on games. I always believed it was a waste of my time. But this game right here...this is another story. I love it. It has endless fun. I love how you can improve your character's stats and earn weapons. I also like how they put you right in the action. Most shooter you just have to waste time by looking around for your enemy which get exhausting after a few game plays. But this game doesn't make you exhausted it makes you want to play more.Thank you guys for a gg ü§£

This little cover shooter that could deserves 5 stars. Ads do not ruin gameplay or time spent using the app, they are not intrusive or invasive. Cool little events that change every week, neat Metal Gear-esque storyline, cover mechanics are smooth and dine right with cover that has a health bar and deteriorates over time, varied gameplay between sniping, cover shooting, and blasting things with an RPG from a helicopter, tons of freebies constantly thrown at you, this game is practically perfect

I love this game so much that I loaded it on to a new phone which I have never done before and started it from scratch!!! The only thing that I would change is being able to move the aim and fire buttons, both to one side or the other. I only have one arm so moving my finger all the way across the screen while holding the phone in place gets difficult. I don't know if you guys even read these, but if you do and I would greatly appreciate it because then I could play on the harder levels.

Cover Fire is extremely enjoyable if your craving a shooter. According to some reviews it is similar to other shooter games but this is my first one and I like it. I dont have VR but I feel this would be killer to play VR style. One thing to note, the story line scenes are a little brief. Adding in some voice acting to the scenes may improve immersion into the game. It's all good though in my opinion.

this game is fun without having to buy anything. as a shooter you are able to play in three different modes assault, sniper and flying a drone as you advance through the missions of the game. The missions are short with most only lasting about 1 minute. if you like shooting games this is the one for you.

The game is very good. It has unique playstyle and the variety of weapons and characters.But you need to upgrade your card wisely if u want to play higher levels cause some levels require very hard objective to get full 3 stars and perfect too. The events is fun and very competitive but it will be more fun if it isn't disturbed by hackers so pls fix it.

Easy to pickup and has some solid challenges in trying to achieve 3 stars for each mission. Can easily be played and beaten without spending any money. Pvp is satisfying but becomes boring after a while. Suggestions would be more missions, whether continuing the current campaign story or a completely new campaign, also the option to modify the characters and guns. Only downside is once the campaign has been beaten, it will be just waiting for online tickets to regen or special events to open up

First let me say this is a well thought out game scheme. Like the current shooting games out there that utilize a clever "auto-firing-you-just-do-the-aiming" system, this game has an "auto-cover-taking-you-gotta-aim-and shoot" system. The game takes you thru several tense, over the top sequences. All while using 2 to 1 finger presses. Well made gents and lass', well made indeed...

Cover fire isn't another in-play purchase first shooter that dogs you to buy gold. It is exciting enough to where you can slowly use game points to get what you need. It's fast action play makes the time fly and that means lots of fun. No complicated maps and there is a lot to unlock. As you increase the power of your skills it knows exactly what and when you should be rewarded so it keeps you riveted to your phone like nothing else matters. It's a mobile gamer's keepsake.

A great, light shooting game for a hobbyist looking for one. This helps pass time even when offline while you wait somewhere and get back connection. Only two concerns arw when on a vehicle and you fail to hit the targets on the train you automatically get moved on but the scope gets difficult to turn back to finish the job and well it feels the same when a grenade is coming at you. But, overall for not a serious gamer, I love to play it from time to time when I get the chance outside.

It's a very interesting game,the graphics are at a good standard and everything is clear...but the is only one problem the civilian that you saving in zombie mode are not active and the zombie are too fast when they are attacking. So I'm recommending for me as a player to move while defending the civilian or my self instead of being just in one place.

This is the best gun shooting game I've ever played... The graphics, weapons, subjects, and the environments...are so fantastical.... Most of all i like the idea of how this game gives out it's rewards, it's so Cool..... Frankly speaking...dis game deserve more than five stars. I think the missions could be made more complex by letting a player control movements of it's subject.also if it could b possible....the subject has to be able to drive a car too....stab an enemy with a knife.

One of the best shooting games ive played on my phone, great graphics and i like the controls and gameplay, i was hoping there was an option to change the crosshair to another colour as the white one can be a bit hard to see at times but thats just a minor thing, also adds dont keep popping up but you can watch them to earn and double rewards, overall a great job by the developers i thought.

This game is super dope! The gameplay is neat and the graphics, art style and story is also great. One thing that I notice tho is the lack of character variety on the other class (demolitions, etc.). Other than that it is great. Definitely deserves 5 stars.

Very good game. No pushing ad's. A glitch here and there but I think it's just my screen protector. Skill is on the players. No need for internet or wifi. Overall great game worth the download and the try. So true it out if you like a challenge and shooting. Starts off easy gets progressively harder.

Very cool. Even better when I lightly tap the scope to line up my Headshots b4 I actually pull the trigger so 2 speak. Awesome grafix as well, i just need to keep upgrading to move forward. Ads are not to intrusive. Can't really complain when I need upgrades huh lol other than that, when I can afford to purchase, I'll be grinding hard. Enjoy team. Depending on ya.

This is a very good ofline game and after some this will become so hard to get 3 star but I like difficult games. Some of the level are so hard that it took 10 -20 tries to get 3 star. Graphics are so good. There is some problem with controls sestivity. Please increase sensitivity.

Excellent game all round. The UI looks good & is easy to navigate. The well-paced gameplay is action packed & challenging enough with a good soundtrack to round it off. There are no intrusive ads(a special Thank You devs) but optional ads are offered for extra loot. Well done dev team, Cheers!

Amazing concept and the cutscene art is amazing. It's a good game if I'm honest but I wish that it did have controller support so some people that don't feel comfortable with the controls can Bluetooth a controller to their device and play like that I do understand that it isn't a first person shooter but I think it would be pretty cool the be able to play with a controller

The gameplay is good. Almost like 1st person shooter in PC games. I have played all of the missions. I hope the developers can update more campaign missions soon. Can't wait for it. And also please update new events, it has been a while since there is an event.

Excellent shooter all around and I've been a console guy for 50+ years. Great graphics and control. Bit heavy-handed on the monetization side but so far I haven't paid a dime, and I know you've got to pay for such high production values, but thankfully I'm a very patient man... kudos to your team!

Best game of played so far but i have some problems. Firstly the civilians you are saving in zombie mode sometimes block your line of shooting and you end up shooting them. Excellent game lots of options modes of play. Doesn't need money to advance but it will take time. One you can play without time penalties meaning you are not forced to come back to keep your place/ rank. Well worth a try
For an offline game, it's excellent. The graphics are out of this world. The concept outstanding. The experience exceptional. The campaigns are nice and long to keep one busy for years.

This is my 2nd time I play, previously in iOS. Probably best shooting/action games on mobile. It is not plagued with forced ads like any other games, only rewarded ads. Thank you for making good game, hopefully you can add more contents in the future.

Only started playing a short while now but loving it so far. Different characters and scenarios, main game with other events available. Not forced to spend money and ads are optional. Graphics are control responses are great. Nice game to play when you have a few spare minutes.

One of the best games I've played,not asking for any $$$ unless you a willing to upgrade faster and get bigger items, I make do with what I've got and still earn while completing or just passing each level,I still get rewards.really injoyable game.thumbs up to the creators of this great game worth more than 5 stars.

Just downloaded it today and enjoying every bit. March 1, been playing game almost everyday. Still enjoy it mostly. Tough areas to get through. Only negative thing is after you max out all your skill cards, there's nothing left to use the in-game money you earn. The only way to get more health, stop-watch, or grenades is to spend real money. I've been racking up a ton of in-game money and nothing to spend it on. Hopefully the developers can do something about using that money to buy anything

What can I say, besides if it is a Call of Duty type game that you are looking for, then you have found it to the degree. Only in this one you are subject to be one of 3 Players. 1, A sniper rifle expert Giving cover fire to your main player. The main player armed with a scar rifle And a few tricks in his bag.. And lastly a helicopter machine gun/rocket launcher backup. All in all pretty fun game, the only damn part is you have to spend money if you want to keep playing after a while.

Good fun and decent graphics. This game is my favorite past time would suggest it for anyone. I just wish the damage was more realistic and there was more weapons choice

Cover Fire is a great mix of Battlefield and Gears Of War. It feels like a premium experience and a good one at that. That game has an option to go 120 FPS and High Graphics which make the game feel like a console game. I highly recommend at least giving the game a chance.
