Was going to give this app 5 stars. In the second city, I bought the sniper rifle it told me to buy TWICE, which was a decent amount of in-game coins. The first time I just earned the money again by doing side missions and bought it, but a second time with less money than I had before, I would have to do alot more side missions than before, which is annoying. I recomend this game for the first city, but after that, this game is a total bust.

It is a nice game. Ads (that also force you to head to the play store) after each mission gets really tiring and annoying. The money earned is really insufficient to buy new weapons and upgrade. Looks like you really have to use real money for this game, and I won't do that. However, the user interface is great. Still a good game. Also, I've been buying weapons with the in-game currency, but the money gets taken away but the weapon isn't added to my purchased weapons list.

The game for some reason will not turn on now. I try to get into the game and it will kick me out of the app after 5 seconds. Missing out on the Zombie Nightmare campaign and the rewards that come with it. Great game just absolutely hate the crashes. 3 days later and the game is still kicking me out of the app when I try to get in it to play. Great game but now I think it's time to uninstall.

It's amazing how the enemy can shoot thru solid buildings and kill you, but you can't see them and when you fire at the building where the bullets are coming from, the bullets bounce off. Customer support is a joke, so I don't even bother. You never get an actual response, only automated standard response. Very frustrating.

It's got really good graphics, and the gameplay is entertaining, but once you finish the 21st city , all you're left with is repetitive tasks to get game tokens. PVP mode requires heavy weaponry, and unless you've bought it earlier in the game, it's unattainable. The developers need to add more cities. Update: nearly two years later, STILL NO NEW CITIES. Doing my review from 3 stars to 1.

Just spent a ton of (in game money) on the current highest tier (unlocked) assault rifle, upgraded it to the point where you're waiting an hour for parts you arrive, only to go back to missions and find out that it doesn't have enough damage to ever be able to use it. Should be able to undo something like that. but I can't, so I'm just demotivated enough to just say screw it and uninstall it entirely. All that work to get all that money, just to waste it.

cool game, pretty realistic for a while. Then you reach a point that you cant get out of. Upgraded weapons are expensive but you can't get enough points to buy one. I got to a point that it takes 2 shots per man and there's 5 men and I only have 5 rounds. Reloading takes about 5 seconds. Cant even get a bigger magazine cause you have to have kills. Been on the same mission for 4 days. It sucks.

Contains ads is more than a bit misleading, it is mostly ads; and that is just the start. Some of the ads are on the edge of malware behavior, opening other apps and links without permission, or interaction. I get that ads drives the revenue for development nowadays, but the frequency, behavior, and duration of these ads encourage me to turn off the game, and go do something else; removing my eyeballs from the equation.

There are way too many ads especially right after missions. The reward shooting range is such an inconvenience. There is no possible way to get to the 100th round without wasting diamonds. The only good graphics is the opening screen. Other than that it's trash. It would be so much better if there were less ads and it was controller compatible. The premium price is way out there. It would be different if it was like COD mobile with great graphics and stuff like that but it's a low grade game.BAD

That's it. I'm done. App deleted. The statical odds of getting the red skull in the daily challenge (the only way to get battle coins for free) is 1 in 4. Nine days in a row I got the skull on the second shot. Not the first - every day it was the second shot. That's not bad luck; that's programming to ensure I lose. The only way to progress in the game is to pay $$$ to buy what is required. The scenarios have begun to repeat with higher spec requirements. I have better things to do.

This game was fun for a few hours, but quickly becomes obvious that you must lay out a whole lot of real money in order to advance very far. Lots of annoying watching the same ads for games over and over, and then makes you wait to regain "energy" in between missions - sometimes for literally 15 minutes - unless you subscribe or upgrade by buying something. Spent an evening playing it, had my free entertainment, and now I'm deleting it and finding something else. That's about what it's worth.

Was great after I first installed it, then as I progressed, it stopped working. It keeps telling me that it can't connect, and that's hard to believe especially when both my wifi and phone signal are strong. So after multiple times trying to connect, I just uninstalled the game altogether. So, please don't waste your time on this game, unless they come up with an update to fix the connection problem.

Game is fun, but takes too long having to do the same exact boring mission over and over again to save enough coins for upgrades. Also gets really frustrating in the PvP arena when you get killed every 2 seconds and never even have the opportunity to even get anyone else in your sights. This game could be a lot of fun, but these 2 things have ruined it for me. UNINSTALLING!

Not a fan...good for people that just want to snipe without real skill, but not someone that is use to timing there bullet travel time. I'm not a fan of the dramatic pause.There should be able to have some type of competition for other players. It's a good basic game, but it's something that you easily get bored of and will delete later on. I wasn't a fan of the gameplay at all its boring to me and dosent catch my attention, but there isnt anything wrong with the game.

For the 1st few levels it's like shooting fish in a barrel. Then get rid of the game. The rifles become inconsistent from 1 shot to the next. Drop is okay, sometimes. For me, the trigger in the bottom corner of the screen was easy to miss. The target may be running thru a field but you can't turn your weapon. You just have to zoom out and watch helplessly as the target run for a 100 yrds until out of sight.

So many bugs. It looks like every item is in the shape of square. Responds very slowly when adding scores or diamonds. When you are disconnected due to the poor connection, you just loose the points. Double score/reward button freezes/unresponsive all the time. Items are ridiculously expensive. Each item cost easy $30 but with plenty of bugs unfixed. Poor graphics. They tried to make money with little effort. Everything's just repeating same things with higher scores. I would not spend a penny!

It was fun for a little while then the adds and the repetition made this game unplayable. You may play a 30 second round followed by a 30 second add. It takes way too much time (and adds) to build up your weapons, and some of the missions are basically designed only for guns purchased in the game...or for tons of patience.

This game is kinda fun at first, but as you've probably seen from other reviews it tries to force you to spend money after almost every mission you do, and if you decline it asks you, "are you sure?" like YES I'M SURE! Not to mention it's FULL of ads, sometimes 3 in a row if it gets the chance. Lastly, multiplayer has never worked for me, I'm not sure if it's a network thing or a money thing, and you don't even really get to choose the guns you use on missions, and the gun physics make no sense.

Everything about this game is geared towards making it unpleasant to play unless you spend money. Ad based play time is about 4 minutes of ad time to 1 minute of game play and everything is dragged out with the option to "upgrade" instead of waiting. There's certain aspects of the game that you just can't do without these upgrades. Ultimately, it has possibility, but the greed factor of the developers makes it just suck.

Total garbage! The more you progress the more ads you comeacrossed at first you can skip through them but then there are the 30 second ads you can't skip through! Also the game spams you all the time constantly to buy thingsin game that you don't need and makes it difficult to decline. At the end of every single mission you get hit with ads and in-game spam. The makers of this need to become real life sniper targets. And to them: do not respond to this review unless you actually fix the issue!!!

Too many ads. And not enough play time. Only get 10 energy once that's out you have to wait forever. The game is fun. Just should get more game time and less ads. Level New Madison A ticket to ride there is a glitch when you get on the other train you spin in circles and the other snipers shoot you there is no way to win. I've used all my lives trying to beat it impossible. I'm uninstalling this game and will not redownload!

I thought it was good but it's a trash game! Once you get so far in the guns don't hit their targets on the main quest line even if you set it with perfect accuracy!!! I line it up and watch as the enemy keeps running to reveal a bullet hole in the ground behind him after I watch it go through his chest!!! As in normally would be dead but it's like he goes ghost mode and no bullets actually hit him just pass through! I'm severely pissed because i was really starting to get into it too!!

Do yourself a favor. Pass on this one. Yes, the game can be fun for a bit...unless a level bugs out on you and you have to grind side missions to progress. When I tried reporting that city 7 mission 3 was broken and I couldn't progress, I got a standard reply for issues with connecting to PVP or World Ops. They didn't even care enough to read my help ticket. Now it's happening again in city 11 mission 4. Games have problems, that's a given...but these guys don't care, and that sucks.

You spend more time watching ads than playing. Levels are repetitive with same storyline, and often are only one target. Takes less than five seconds to beat some levels, but ads are around thirty seconds. Diamonds are difficult to earn and are basically useless. You get one diamond for watching a long ad, but upgrades are in the thousands. Way too unrealistic.

can't compete with the big spenders. "discounted" items are always too expensive or are unavailable to purchase with money saved and requires real money. levels are redundant and not challenging. pvp servers are always offline and the game is super glitchy. I paid for a month of premium, only to be charged more to get any real benefit from the subscription. total ripoff of a game. I'd give it zero stars if I could.

Game is being monopolized by cheaters and the fun is gone. I've been a Premium Plus player for about a year and I'm about done. It was fun until hackers took over. It's unfortunate the developers don't seem to be dealing with the situation because I may have to say goodbye. Addicting. Great graphics and challenges. PVP is my favorite to play, but in order to advance through levels in different games, one needs diamonds which aren't always easy to come by.

Playing in PVP mode is horrible. There are people that have hacked the system to get powerful weapons and so much protection that they cannot be killed, but constantly knocked you out as soon as you come back to life. Either fix the game to separate by level so all players play at an even level or you will lose players. On the boards people are getting pretty fed up.

Fun at first but A MILLION ads. Plus the "money" part of the game gets in the way of enjoying it. Some missions aren't clear they are costing you and every "deal" is a way to get you to spend money. If you're a gamer you might enjoy. If you just looking to kill a little time this will get old quick. Sometimes the buttons dont let you shoot. And SOOOOOO many ads. I've deleted the app now.

So the missions are fun but a bit repetitive. The PvP arena is a great concept but hardly works. Connection issues up the wazoo. Mid game you have someone lined up, you shoot and the bullet goes thru them no hit. Second shot, clear headshot, nothing. Seconds later same person hits and kills you. Or you get a loss of signal error mid session. But miraculously the signal is fine for the Ads after the round.

Total money grab! The way the game moves you can not save up any cash to buy anything except what you absolutely need for that stage. Discounts for weapons stages ahead, then offers a discount on the gun you'll need next when you have nothing saved and only gives you seconds to buy. I don't mind spending money but this game feels like it's reaching into your pockets!

I have another account that I have made it up to a silver skull level but I have had so many problems like so many others. Some of the issues are constant connection issues, freezing up, lose of points and rewards. Game changes, a lot of money if you want to compete. I lost several accounts and apps customer service never recovered them, it took me months to build accounts and imagine the frustration when they disappeared it happened a second time I promised to never spend or build another one!

In the mission for the plane, others have reported the same. They aim in the box and it does nothing. I've tried over 20 times and no matter how many times I shoot in the box, it doesn't take down the plane. I've watched videos and they hit in the box and it hits, but mine doesnt. I've uninstalled and reinstall and same issue. Would like to continue through missions, but it won't advance... And stuck now. Sad times. Like the game though.

More bad than good. Bad: 1) Waaaaay too many ads. Much more time lost watching forced ads than time spent playing the game. 2) Graphics quality is juvenile at best. 3) Frequent "special offers", always at a higher cost than your current coins/diamonds levels. An obvious, and annoying, effort to get into your wallet. Good: It's free to find out how bad it is. It's kind of fun for the 1st 3 or 4 levels, until the frequency of ads ticks you off.

The story mode is repetitive. The multiplayer mode is horribly bad with mismatched opponents. Giving an edge totally to the players that pay to play. No way within the game to make suggestions or contact the developers. A great time waster, but nothing more. And just for fun they throw in "seasonal" items that are completely useless if you've played the game for more than a week. The upgrades for multiplayer are entirely useless unless you've played the game for years or pony up the cash.

Fun game but it is another need to pay game. Options to buy items with credits received in game consistently (and conveniently for them) give you a connection error. I doubt that would happen if I'm paying money for something. Update: even after paying for items, I was still having server connection issues, tired to uninstall and reinstall, same issues plus it didn't renew my purchases then. Oh well, I'm done with it. Was a waste of money but I should have known better. It is a sucker game!

It's fun, but designed to force you to spend money to progress. There is an advertisement every other mission. When I had the chance for a free 1 week subscription, I took the offer. Then I found out the game is $5 A WEEK after that! Who spends $5/week on a phone game?! Maybe if they didn't make it impossible to progress in the game unless you spend even more money. But no, they still make it so you have to spend more money. Potentially fun game. I'd be happy to pay for it ONCE.

Cool game but becomes unplayable if you don't want to pay. You need to upgrade your equipment in order to continue playing the game. Upgrades can be done via coins earned through gameplay - however, sometimes you'll have to wait 10 minutes to equip your gun with upgrades purchased, even if you haven't opened the game in 2 days. Also, for example, you may watch an ad to earn coins, then immediately after the ad, you have to watch another ad and even then your equipment may not be equipped

After playing a while I have to lower my rating of this game. It gets boring fast. The ads get more frequent and the missions stay brief until 3/4 of your time is spent watching ads or waiting for the now glitchy game to load. It's also straight pay to win. I have literally emptied magazine after magazine into the head of an opponent on my same level in player vs player mode only to have them finally notice me and finish me off in one shot.

New players NOT welcome. This game could be a lot of fun, but it is very unfairly tilted toward experienced players. Experienced players are able to lose intentionally in order to get matched up against easier opponents. Newer players who do this are penalized. However the most experienced players can do it with no penalty. This puts newer players at such a disadvantage that it ruins the game.

This isn't even pay-to-win, it's pay-to-play. The rifle you start with is only good enough for the first couple of levels, then you have to upgrade. The problem? YOU CAN'T!! The game has coins and diamonds and you need diamonds to buy a new gun. The game gives you gold for completing missions. You have to but the diamonds to keep playing. No F-ing way! The game is not free and REQUIRES purchases to play.

You want your rating? You got it. You have to buy practically everything to continue missions, you offer a challenge level that let's you attain a certain amount of goods and then when you lose it, you lose all the goods unless you want to BUY your way out of that, the game play is still the same ol same ol from sniper 3d of years past and the graphics/game play are definitely not the quality the ads portray. Junk ad filled app not worth downloading. You've been deleted!

Ridicules cost on everything!!! Why would anyone play a game that pops up ads every few minutes and then there own ads with 100$ purchases. I am fine with supporting games that I like by purchasing items but it's as much as a gaming system. I actually liked the game for a few times but every item is so much money that it makes everyone quit. 20 dollars to upgrade the muzzle or stock exc. that barely upgrades the weapons because there are 50 upgrades on just one part. LAME STUPID AND GREEDY!!!!!!

The game itself isn't bad, however in order to win you HAVE to buy power ups, and there are items that you can purchase only if you have a premium subscription (these are the best items). The absolute worst part of this game is that it "rewards" you with a chance to purchase "diamonds" for a special price. Lowest price is $2.99 for 30 gems which doesn't get you anything. So the game itself is good but all the offers to buy a win completely ruin the game.

The number of ads are ridiculous! They try to force you into upgrading to Premium by wearing you down with the ads. Not going to happen! But, I can tell you what is going to happen right after I submit this review is the big delete this app! A true waste of time even writing this review. Hopefully, I've saved one second of someones time and they in turned used that second to save the world :)

Energy limit is dumb takes too long to get things accomplished. There is constant ads after every mission. A mission may last 20 seconds the ad is 30 seconds so you spend more time on ads then playing. Would be great if they could fix those up. They try to make you pay for stuff but you dont have to. It would be easier if you do but I wont. Especially with all the ads they make plenty off of me

Wish I hadn't downloaded it. As others have said it is extremely taxing to play/complete w/out spending money. I personally have not, however this means I have spent hours completing "side missions"/levels to scrape together enough "coins" to continue. The most frustrating part of playing for "free" is the game limits how many missions you can finish at a time by requiring "energy". To get energy for free you wait, but you MUST have WIFI. And the Ads constantly Interrupt the game.

Had some problems initially, but finally solved them. I thought the issues I was having was due to not being able to see clearly on the small screen. I installed on a new 10 inch tab and I'm still not getting five seconds before I'm dead 17 times in two minutes! I thought the cheaters were under control but apparently not. Wish I'd have saved my money - it was an expensive lesson!

The game has a huge bug that isnt being addressed. My energy fails to regenerate and all of my weapon upgrades have stopped upgrading. The timer is stuck. The PvP area is also inaccessible, it says 0. I've sent numerous emails to tech support with no reply. This game has a good amount of ads that pop up after each mission most of the time. The concept is great but this bug deters me from playing it. As of March 22, 2019 the game is happily now uninstalled. Still no reply from developers.

This game starts out great, but no matter how many chips you collect, coins, etc., you can never get ahead. The weapons always fluctuate in price. Also the scenes never change. It's the same city in the PvP, and mostly the same in the other challenges. Also, in PvP, certain players will spend hundreds of dollars, have impenetrable armor, one shot kill weapons and bullets, and you get killed within a second of arriving on the screen. If you don't have hundreds of dollars to spend, this game sucks

If i could give zero stars I would, this game is horrible. It might seem fun at first but some of the Levels, for instance the one where you shoot out of a helicopter, is literally impossible. You are noticed and killed if you even miss one shot or if you waste 10 seconds. To add on you cannot shoot anypart below the waist if you shoot the legs or waist it goes THROUGH them and they run away. I unistalled after a few hours because it was so ridiculously hard and tedious to play.

Nice concept, poor execution. Frequently spawned in a vulnerable stance so other shooters can get free shots at you before you can even turn around. Getting tokens and diamonds of a useful quantity requires purchases. Ads are pushed in your face at each break in game play. I keep forgetting that it's one big ad cluster with a game in it. My bad.

Don't bother. Third Head Hunter event in a row that once you are in reach of the top prizes, the game randomly freezes a second or two, and you stand there and die. Or you get on target and freeze with the trigger doing nothing. And by the time it unfreezes, they have shot you. An exercise in frustration. If you play it, don't blame me when you throw your phone at the wall. I warned you.

Even if you made all the in-app purchases and got the best gear, I don't think this game would be very fun. My complaint is with the controls. The zoom control is on the left of the screen, as is the fire button, which for some reason is small enough that I often tap to shoot and miss. Since a lot of the game is based on timing, a failure in basic UX with the controls makes the game a frustrating experience at best. Why not move the fire button to the other side of the screen and make it bigger?

BEWARE UNWANTED PURCHASES. So many intrusive ads to make purchases you can accidentally make one easily. I ended up with a WEEKLY $5 subscription to this awful game. Not only did I get bombarded with prompts to make purchases, they also made it a subscription you would never expect to be charged weekly. I lost $55 on this stupid game before I noticed the charges on my credit card. Now I can't get it back.

What a shame. This game is really addictive and quite awesome. Hear comes the bad...I played, got right up there, and had to start all over again. I consider myself a hardened player...level 60 first time, level 72 now. There's no way you can kill more than 10 people at a time, I'll even say 11,maybe 12 if you're lucky enough!! I've been shot through walls, deducted energy because server issues, matched up against fighters completely out of my league consecutively, and not been able to recharge

It really is a fun game, typical pay to advance, but fun. The problem is that two times, in two days, that I used diamonds to make a purchase, the synchronization "failed". The diamonds were deducted, but I didn't receive the upgrade. Once is a glitch, twice looks more like a feature.

Game would be great except for all the ads and some missions no matter how upgraded your weapons are they won't hit where they should ie the zipline mission it sends your bullets in a different direction every shot. And don't allow you to use a gun with more then 4 or 5 shots and less then 3 seconds per target. I am not spending cash on this game because it would be a waste. Deleting this pos game.

Loved the game but now it's been down for a while. It's full of glitches but I was willing to look past it. But when you haven't been able to play it for almost 2wks I uninstalled it. Just a waist of space at this point. I don't recommend downloading it until someone gets these problems fixed. I would have given it a 5 star until all of the problems starting happening. Now I will give it a 1 star.

Update: ads were bad before, but you could close them. Now the ads aren't skipable. I would suggest avoiding this until they're removed. The rest of the review is still accurate. There are 2 ads after each mission. Sometimes you can hit the mission button before the first one loads and avoid it, but most times not. Energy system is dumb too like I wrote in my original review, but the game waits for you to get invested before the ridiculous amount of ads starts appearing.

I can't get past the opening tutorial without the game crashing. I've completely closed out of the game, relaunched, and played the tutorial a dozen times and I STILL cannot progress father than the tutorial. I keep seeing this game in my recommend and you'd thing with 100+ million downloads and a high rating, the game wouldn't be crashing so much. If something gets fixed, maybe I'll play again and change the rating. Very disappointing.

I've never played the game. But the ads for this game are extremely obnoxious. They're the playable ads, which is whatever. But there is no way to exit them. At all. No exit button and hitting my back button does nothing. I've left it open for several minutes and it just remained on the ad. Clicking the ad just brings up the mini game but afterwards you can't leave that either. Please fix your advertisements! I'll return and change my rating if and when you do.

Game is cool to which I give 4 stars for that. Lately the AD's do not include the 'X' at the end of playing. This leaves 2 options both of which annoying. 1 - made to go to play store which you have to close, then its just a repeating cycle. 2 - close out the game completely then restart which is annoying to have to do every 2-3 missions. Please fix or this game is getting uninstalled.

The game holds your hand through the entire beginning, constantly making offers only available if you pay. The game caps hard if you are just wanting to "play for free" like it claims. The only way to get the most from this game is to shell out a lot of microtransactions. Would be a great game if it weren't always forcing microtransactions. I would be willing to buy a full game of this for $2 in the play store, but that wouldnt go far with microtransactions.

I am one of the people that fought all the way from the bottom to get right around the top grandmaster level golden lion What you are doing with the trophies now and resetting everybody 4 times a year. Count me out! I don't care what you do! I will not fire one more bullet! I will not play one more round! But most importantly I will not spend one penny until the trophy situation and the structure of the game goes to back the way it was ! I already saved one months subscription!

Game was glitching so I uninstalled and reinstalled. Before doing so I took a screenshot of my progression. I reloaded the game and reloaded my account. It did recognize, but lots of progression and gold coins are missing. I have spent real US dollars upgrading my status and position in the game. Also having troubles upgrading to Premium Plus. I can't be spending money and time into a game that isn't stable/reliable. Will wait a day or two to see if it self corrects, if not, then I am done.

Lots of in game purchases right off the back. After every mission you lose energy, surprise... Low on energy buy some more. Game would be better if they let you okay a decent while before trying to fleece you with paid upgrades and unlocks Update: you can only get so far (about 9 levels) before the try to force you into a purchase. Unless you like to spend money on games, avoid at all cost.

Dont bother downloading. It's been 2 years since they upgraded missions.. Once you complete all levels, that's it. It's done. Dont waste your money on this game at all as it will eventually come to an end. It's filled with guys who spent money to upgrade so you're killed instantly in 1 on 1 play. It's a waste of time

I literally just downloaded this game. Made it through the first 3 levels. Bought my gun and started missions. Upgraded the and that worked perfectly. Completed the first mission on thr city map. That also worked fine. Then i was hunting down the most wanted criminals. Completed the first mission fine. Then i completed the second mission and the phone crashes. Waited for my phone to restart, opened the game and expected to see crimial #3 but no i had do #2 again. Same thing happened phone crash.

Cool graphics, great weapons and upgrade options. Unfortunately, like EVERY OTHER GAME, a point is quickly reached where a lot of real money is needed to continue. PvP is impossible unless you spend a ton of money. Missions become repetitive and monotonous.

Crashes all the time! I've had to Uninstall and reinstall numerous times. After reinstall, it's works for a day or so, then starts randomly crashing again... Rinse and repeat. This has happened 8 or 9 times now... I love the game, but how can I give it more than 1 star if it doesn't actually work???

I'm very unsure of the legality of this game. If the game shows a red marker indicating you need to upgrade your rifle, or face an extremely difficult mission; what they really mean, is that the game is literally impossible to move past. If you try to shoot a targets head with an underpowered rifle the character will move as if they have sixth sense. If you try to adjust for this, they will not move at all. Also, if you miss their his by a pixel they will not movie either. Impossible. Cash grab.

It's a fun game but it's far too costly to be productive and too many glitches to quantify their value. It only takes a couple weeks to progress as far as you can playing solo. There is no way to stay competitive with p2p play without spending a couple hundred dollars. They also have 2 levels of premium. The first merely removes the ads. No other perks

Decent game to pass the time. Way too many ads!!! Rewards earned are not given, unless you pay real $ for them. Weapons cost too much money,and by the time you get one upgraded to the max,its already obsolete for the next city,then you'll have to start the whole process over again. This game needs totally redeveloped!!

Could have been an awesome game, too bad they're shady and lame about gun buys and upgrades. I get the whole idea of upgrading and needing to spend real money to a due certain things, ultimately it is a business. But the thing that bothered me, was that they give you these so-called "one time deals" And they are always, 100% of the time just above the amount of diamonds that you have. I've tested it. The second part that sucks majorly! Is buying new guns is always, just above your money.

DO NOT SPEND ANY MONEY WITH THESE DEVELOPERS. It is a fun, great game. But do not purchase anything in-game. I have had purchases disappear, and have read many other reviews with the same experiences. It is also impossible to talk to anyone about it. Emails get returned as undelivered. In game chats go unanswered for weeks, then they disappear also.. Very frustrating, borderline fraudulent.

It's fun when the connection doesn't all of a sudden drop. seems to happen a lot when ur doing well. at times it feels like the game is rigged. u get more stars when there's better connection. update... down to one star. PvP is unplayable anymore. lose connection every time. I do not recommend this game until their servers are fixed

In game purchases/ads to this game are extremely excessive. Needed to delete it because it got to a point where the game held hostage quite literally in form of a piggy bank for necessary diamonds to proceed in the game. In order to get them, even though you've won them, you have to pay a ransom each time. Increasing in cost each time. $30 for something you need to continue to upgrade the game? Waste of money and time. It's the most ludicrously expensive game I've ever played. A total scam.

Pure manipulation. The game is designed for one thing: to manipulate you into spending money. You try to get a free gun and it says that there is no internet connection. But when you press the purchase button (as a test to later cancel) it goes through just fine... Piggy bank fills up but you have to buy it to get the bank. Lots of examples. The game would be pretty fun if it just let you freaking play.

More adds than game play. The first few levels are pretty cool, but in order to advance you must either grind or spend literally hundreds of dollars. After every mission an add plays. The game then offers a "gift" to rewatch the same add. A higher tier rifle costs almost 20 dollars of real money and most are only unlockable if you pay for a "premium" subscription. Constantly try iij ng to sell "limited time" or "one time only" offers. Kills battery and eats data.

I've had enough, the game sucks. Too many ads, too much error, too much cheating in pvp and too many times you never get rewards you earn for various things such as headshots , daily login etc. The list goes on. And I have never been contacted by support, though I have asked for help many times. Save time and money and don't waste either on this game.

Decent game play, however, the "watch videos for diamonds" feature only shows videos 1/4 of the time and you don't get diamonds if it doesn't. So most of the time your watching the ads for no return. This is in addition to the ads they show after every mission (these almost always include a video and static ad). Regardless, the gun "sales" always cost more diamonds than what you have to force a purchase of diamonds. At first and second level this is tiresome at best. The long run, not worth it.

Game hasn't been working right for going on 3 weeks. I've tried contacting "support" and can't get any help with the issues even after trying all troubleshooting steps/suggestions. Worthless tech support, just robots that get you absolutely nowhere. Never been so frustrated with a gaming app, which initially I was really enjoying. Tried again 9 months later, with a brand new phone same issues as before PVP still won't work and I'm sure their "support" is still non-existent. Done trying! üñï

Loved it until the last update. My energy doesn't refill, watching a video for energy isn't an option anymore, any attempt to update a weapon is at a standstill. I even deleted it and redownloaded the entire app and was faced with the same issues. I'm deleting with hopes I can try again in a few months.

Previews looked alright it just a money grab. Literally every 10 minutes there's something to buy. Deceiving part of this one that makes it bad and definitely turned me off from even playing for free is they don't even mention some of the offers cost anything. You just get payment screen. It may be $1 or $50. Game is rip off.

Been trying my best to like the game. The first 3 cities was great. Easy to play. The free premium made it a bit easier to even enjoy the 4th some of the 5th city. However thats still having dropped some change on this game. You make this game too pay to play. Not even pay to win. Just pay to play. That is horrible. Even yalls free challenge target shooting. Getting a skull on the first shot is infuriating. Especially for a player patiently waiting a day just to be allowed to play it. Deleting

At the best of times this game was greedy. Now, it is over-the-top greedy. Upgrades are impossible without spending money after the first couple of rounds. The preponderance of ads every other game is ridiculous over kill. The fact of the matter is this game is not worth either money nor time investment as it is simply frustrating to get to a certain point and know that you can go no further without money. That's not the way this game used to be and I ascended many many levels before quitting.

Initially I was going to give this game five stars. However once I got far enough into the game to get an option for double coins for watching a video or diamonds for watching a video, that would have solidified my rating. But there is a problem. The videos don't work. I can't play any of them. I have lost out on plenty of coin options and at least a thousand total diamonds which I could have use to upgrade my weapons. I was going to keep the subscription to the game but what's the point.

This game has nice mechanics and graphics, but if you don't spend money, you can't play. I've been playing for a few weeks now, and the missions simply do not give you enough money to keep up with the upgrades needed constantly. You spend 78k gold on a new sniper rifle and it requires upgrades immediately. It tries to force you into buying gold.

GREAT GAME! I love this game and I think its a ton of fun to play! I would rate it 6 stars If I could! IF it wasn't for the game being full of ads. Good graphics and game play. But man, this whole using up Energy thing, is some major BS. if you play a few missions you run out of energy and cant play for 10 min. Then, when it refilled, I played one mission and it drained completely again and I had to wait forever to be able to play again. Honestly it's just a stupid idea only made with the idea of forcing people to pay if they want to even keep playing. Not just paying for upgrades, but paying to have to play. Pretty crummy.

Stay away from investing time/money into this rip off game.  The toughness of the enemies ramp up so fast that you are forced to put money into the game to get a better weapon because headshots with your standard sniper rifle just won't cut it.  There are plenty of scams in this game.   One, they look at how many diamonds (very hard to get without $$$) you have and spam you with one time offers.  The catch is that the offers will always be 30-40 more diamonds than what you've accumulated.  The more you accumulate, the higher the offer.  Just so you spend $4.99 to get the extra 30 diamonds.  You'll never get a one-time offer for anything you can afford. There are tons of ads.  Everything displays an ad.  Some ads don't even show up and you're left with a black screen.  Sometimes the ads won't even close and you have to kill the game. The aiming is a joke.  Bullets travel right through enemies even when you make allowance for wind and distance.  Zoom all the way in and you can see the bullet go right through the enemy's shirt without taking damage.  I had one guy who would duck as soon as I hit the fire button.  Then would stand up in place and only duck when I hit the fire button.

I don't do the pay to play thing. I'll purchase a game but won't pay indefinitely for one. This is a fun enough game but you can't realistically get past level one without spending cash on an upgrade. Followed by more cash for more upgrades for more levels. You can watch videos to get more diamonds but you will need to make a career of it. Honestly, I would throw $5 at this... once. It isn't worth more than that.

Has energy where after every 5 minutes you'll run out, and the only way you can get energy is to buy premium. Premium costs REAL MONEY. The ads are insane too. Every time an ad plays, (which is about every minute.) It completely breaks the game. It freezes it, and 1% of the time, you have the game go completely black, and sometimes white. Okay design, but these problems make me give a 2 star review.

This could be a really fun game, but I would never recommend anyone commit too much time, effort, or real money of any kind to it unless some changes were made. The matching in arena mode is ridiculous. You can put hours and hours into the game and still often get matched with other players who can shoot you one time and kill you but you have to shoot them 48 times in the head to get a kill. I'm not sure if this is on purpose or not but out 50 arena matches it was only times that I was 1 game away from a reward that I just happened to get put in the worst location against players who somehow would kill me within 3 to 4 seconds respawning every single time... the cost to continue with the next game and not lose 4 hours of progress is buying stuff. On match 19 out of 20 I was in 3rd place out of 8 with 3 seconds to go, and then the match ended and I was somehow 7th, and would have had to pay $10 to continue. If it was like 2 or 3 dollars then ok, that's fair, but $10 for a game that seems very much rigged seems a little greedy to me. Most of the game is pretty good. I like the different challenges and game modes. The controls are kind of backwards though. Most people use their right hand to fire bullets out of guns, not their left hand.

Bad design and Only for grinders or payors - the game play is annoying as you have to play the same kind of stages again and again. The most annoying part is their greedy algorithm where they expect you to pay as their offers are always little higher than what resource you have. And you can't use single gun, no matter how much you upgrade it and you can use it only for that stage. For the next stage, you have to buy new one and upgrade it all the way, just to throw it away for the next stage.

It seems like the longer that you play, the more frequently you start to see ads. Also you can't just click the x on the ad, you have to touch it very precisely in the middle of the X or it takes you to the play store to install whatever it was just advertising. And sometimes this happens more than once on a single ad. Essentially you end up spending more time clicking back out of the play store than you do actually playing the game. The game play itself is fun. Like others commented, you aren't going to get very far without paying real money, despite the number of ads it shoves down your throat.

Just when you get to where you do one scenario, you have to upgrade it again to do that scenario! Then in the player vs. Player arena, you need massive body heat to compete. The PVP section is perpetually down, and even when you can get in, it's not much fun unless you either buy the right upgrades, or grind your way through the entire single player campaign to earn the upgrades. It was a good game, but...  the last update is terrible... 0) About $10 / month to have premium status? (This problem was always there) That is simply insane. Just make it a 1-time purchase as many other games do and I would pay $10 for it, but $10 / month???? Simply insane. 1) No way to get progress without paying anymore, they just increased (a lot) how much diamonds each objects costs, maintaining the number of diamonds that we can get for free (this is the coin that can be mostly get through real money purchase). So now there is no way to get objects with diamonds unless you actually pay for them, before you could watch a lots of videos and at least get some of the low/medium class objects, but now no way...  2) Multiple bugs that were not there before (e.g., sometimes, when a bad guy is killed, he is still looking as if it is alive, which is super confusing. In addition, the energy bar also looks completely full sometimes when it should be completely empty... )

Game is ok. PvP is very glitchy and frequently umfair. When you get an enemy down to it's last bit of health, 7 out of 10 times computer characters will finish him and steal your points. I've been killed numerous times immediately after spawning before I could even ready my weapon. I'd give more stars if those issues were addressed. But I'm not holding my breath for it.

I'm still on my first level if that tells you anything. They should refund my money!

A decent gun in the game is a $60 purchase, but there is no point. No matter what gun you use, results and graphics are the same. Definitely not worth spending a cent on.

really easy sniper mechanics, nothing like the other games I've played with very accurate controls. also, the game system is very unrewarding unless u get premium, which would make sense if it were a one time investment but no, it's monthly and $4.99/month for very boring graphics and sniper mechanics. also, the discount packs u get are always priced higher than what you have.

That's fine, I got tired of being told I shot the wrong guy. It was the one with the yellow hat,or it was the one running, when nobody's wearing a yellow hat and no one's running until I shoot. I don't need to be shooting anyone anyway.

Very well made and extremely addictive. BUT it's one of those games u can't just keep playing cuz there's energy that runs out so you r tempted to spend money on the game. It was cool for like 10 minutes but then they you r flooded with ads and eventually it gets to a point where u can't play until u get more energy. It's a super basic free bit not really free game. It come off super annoying and takes away from it actually being fun cuz u can't keep playing. Dropping a star. Pvp drops too much.

you get coins by completing missions. you basically have to upgrade the rifle after every mission in order to start the next mission, using coins to buy parts. i probably had to buy 5 different "grips" for a mauser with a wooden stock. because you spend all your coins on upgrades, you can't ever save coins to buy an upgrade rifle. the only way to get a new rifle is to spend real money on diamonds. game play is too short and easy, then you run out of "energy" and can't play for a while

I'm a 1st time player & didn't expect to have to buy upgrades, especially early on. I'll keep playing in hopes of finding a way to keep from having to buy anything. As far as the graphics & controls go I have no complaints, they did a pretty good job. Where even a greenhorn like me can easily navigate through everything.

The prices for in game purchases are the worst I've ever seen. The whole game is basically one long grind for people that don't want to spend $50+ at a time for diamonds. Not to mention the ridiculous real time waiting periods to buy upgrades to your weapons (unless you buy diamonds of course). If you want a mediocre sniper game with overinflated prices and repetitive gameplay, then this is the game for you.

The game itself is pretty fun, not challenging but not easy either. Ads are not actually that bad. The reason I am giving the game two stars is because at least half the game is locked behind a MONTHLY SUBSCRIPTION. Not a cheap one at that, $12 a month for a mobile game? That's excessive. The gameplay is the only salvageable part of this game. I saw that could never buy all the weapons and immediately got turned off to the game, maybe if the monthly cost was cheaper/more affordable.

It could be better. Ads pop up right before it asks "Would you like to watch an ad for 20 of diamonds or coins." But it expects you to watch another after that as if that wasn't annoying. Also, as soon as you get money it wants you to buy something to upgrade because your weapon isn't good enough. Its annoying and the ad that showed this game was lying by a long shot.

Fun game, scummy developers. The game is fun and simple. However, they will do everything they can to get your wallet. Every *special deal* I've gotten so far (from competing missions) is just a tiny bit more currency then I currently have. Every time. They program it so that your so close, and will give you an option to spend money to get the currency for it. Also, the ads are horrendous. A single mission takes about 10 seconds. Then after a mission or two you get a 30 second ad.

a good time killing game. you can upgrade weapons without using real money if you are patient. my only complaint is the energy bar does not always fill back over time as it is supposed to. most of the time it will remain empty for 24 hours. it should refill a bar every 7 minutes or something like that. currently mine has been empty for 17 hours. this obviously limits the amount of time you can play. EDIT: you do reach a point where you can not upgrade weapons without buying tokens. I'm uninstall

Good game but a lot of advertisement. I played this game a few years back and dont recall there being as many advertisements. I practically immediately uninstalled this game because of how many advertisements there were. The advertisements should be used for upgrades or something rather. Also there was a sketchy in app purchase that didnt say a price or anything but simply just asked "Do you want to upgrade this" and then it said "purchase failed" after I clicked to upgrade.

Lots of fun, but it definitely has bugs. Right now I am stuck in Schalltein due to one of the bugs. When I kill the assassin in "Lady Kill" she falls to the ground and the laser from her gun continues to search around. Out in the street several blocks away there is another image of the assassin. Only half of her body is visible. She appears to be trying to walk down the street but her legs are not visible. The game never advances beyond this point.

The game is good( graphics and storyline etc). My issue is after the 3rd "misson"they keep trying to sell you premium membership. Which in itself is not wrong. I kept denying and used the hunting rifle. Come to find out premium costs $4.99 per WEEK. I never opted in and uninstalled app. I fear young kids and teens will fall for this and their parents will have to pay (also the option is in the same place "start misson" was last level. Sleazy is probably the best way to put it. Hope this helps.

This game was really fun about 5 years ago. Now with the new trophy system changes, they cater to the newer players and promote cheating and hacking with the new unfair trophy changes. Long standing clean players are being forced out of top leagues unless they spend a lot of money to stay there. It's not real fun and it certainly isn't fun after finishing the cities if you are a free player, let alone a paid player.

Two stars because it is fun at times. every "offer" you receive is always out of your reach to get you to pay money. And the daily login rewards is completely screwed up. Been playing for a week and I still have two days before it resets (it adds on time every time you close the game). The developers are aware but won't fix it. They recommended un installing and re installing the game to fix it but that doesn't work either.

The game started out fun and addicting, but quickly got pretty boring because it became too much of a grind. Upgrades and weapons are too expensive to the point where you need to play these stupid repetitive meaningless "challenges" to make more money. These "challenges" generally take about 5 seconds and are not very rewarding. This game would have been way more fun if it were less if a grind. Or alternatively, if the grinding felt more rewarding.

Was a great game until the upgrade. It takes 50 hits to kill another assassin except for those who purchase the products. Then after a kill you're transported to another part of the arena where you or another opponent can be put right on top of you and you don't know trying to taking out an opponent and then you're shoot at close range and killed. Was a great game but sucks now with this new version.

I USED to enjoy this game immensely.....until I got to the last mission in Schalltein, "A whole gang at once".....the motion of the copter and the limited time you have to take out all the enemies makes this level IMPOSSIBLE to pass! Others have had the same issues. Consequently, it has ruined the game experience for me and I will now delete it from my phone!! Don't make a game where you make it so far only to reach an impossible-to-beat level!!!!

Update, after second install to start over. Uprades have NO effect. Uninstalling and re rating down - others are correct, developer bugs are many. Too bad. Started out fun. Fun so far, but if you upgrade poorly by "Wrong Address" you wont have the tools to advance. Only option is to uninstall and start over. Impossible to advance without sufficient 'Damage' and magazine size. Frustrating. Also, almost too easy at times....

Have bought the first "pack" for $2.99 and was able to take advantage of enjoyable play. Level 10 (for me) requires upgrades and stops gameplay. Free no more ... Required PAID to progress. Considering I have used in-game currency to acquire other, currently unusable weapons at a deep discount, the game is rigged to MAX me out. Progressing to higher levels is 'rare' per their info. Fire button and Zoom on left side are poor placement. Accidental discharge when zoom/unzoom or no fire.

This game was fun for the first 2 days, but if you don't pay real money to buy coins and diamonds you won't get very far and the enjoyment runs out. The missions barely give you enough to cover one upgrade which is fine in the beginning, but as you go on you need multiple upgrades to complete missions. So if you're looking for a game to pass the time that you don't want to pay money for downlode something else.

it was fun for a little bit. the graphics are 15 years old. There are way too many ads that randomly pop up in between screens. So its not just after you finish a level. The game very quickly became unplayable due to lack of in game funds to upgrade/buy weapons. This is a "pay to win/play game".

Only 21 levels. Spending money in this game is a waste because everything is exponentially expensive as you level up. Weapons are almost worthless in the next level. Game would be so much faster if you could opt out of the slow motion final kill shot for EVERY mission. It was cool the first 500 times.

I do like the game but lately it's been coming up with no connection to server since the last update which has been happening during the pvp. After I shoot 1 it won't let me shoot anyone else but they can get me just fine. It doesn't happen all the time but it is getting more frequent and yes I do have a good signal. I loved the game before but now it's getting glitchy.

It's a fun game for what it is, but the videos that you opt to play to get coins or diamonds don't even play half the time. And like eveyone else has stated, those "special offers" for weapons or upgrades or whatever are always just above your current balance, obviously to entice you to spend real cash. And if you happen to have enough, there's always a "connection problem" that prevents you from completing the purchase.

The GAME itself is great. HOWEVER, the ads they spam you with every minute or two is awful and makes me want to uninstall the game. If you want 5 stars, cut back on the ads. Not only does it take away from the game play experience but to be spammed to death by ads if annoying AF and it eats up data like crazy!

I like this game, but am uninstalling and almost gave it a one star. There are way too many pop up ads!!!!! I understand the need for ads, but when you ask me to watch a video for more diamonds or coins and when I'm about to click that another video pops up....that is bull. I bet it's against Google's terms as well. And when I earn coins and diamonds I have to wait for 20 minutes to equip my upgrade....nope. too much of a hassle. Too many annoyances to keep installed.

If you like ads, limited opportunity for success without paying or watching multiple advertisements, you'll love the experience. Seemed like it was going to be good until after being asked to rate the game. I played for a week to give it a chance. I found the game play was good, but not good enough to pay and certainly not willing to spend more time watching ads than game play. Uninstalled and deleted!

Really liked the game to start with, but quickly found out it's all about making in-game purchases (which I dont do). Only the bare minimum is offered to those who dont pay and there is constant 'buy this and that' in the game. Could deal with the ads cause that's part of free games BUT when the 'Golden weekly deal' comes up after every single thing you do....to much, to aggravating, to many other free games

Too many bugs. Often in the PVP game, the bullets have no affect on an opponent but you can still be killed. Also, numerous times, I have had my "points" reduce without playing a PVP game or winning points in a game only to have the overall total reduced. Headshots are supposed to add 40 points in other games but they never accumulate.

Can't connect to PvP server 1/2 the time so it's hard to make progress. "Free" but missions are only like 2 minutes long and each one is prefaced by 30 seconds of ads. Premium is an option but it's an expensive option. Fun game but all in all not really worth all the hassle or the premium price. Uninstalled after a week.

Its fun but the updates always take away any means of progressing without paying like watching ads to get free diamonds or whatever. Now I have to sit through an ad after every round and get nothing for it. It would be nice if you could sell weapons from lower levels to be able to progress in the game without playing the same shooting range level for a month trying to buy the weapon you need to move forward. You're never gonna use the level 1 rifle again.

I've just lowered my previous review. This game is a great bit of fun, but after spending $24.99 for Premium Plus, I have been unable to play PVP. This change wasn't immediate but after a couple of days of gleaning the benefits of the subscription, no server connection has been available. I hope this is resolved soon as I do enjoy playing it but the issues related to the subscription are leaving me very disappointed.

So far it has been a great game. Amendment: after advancing to lvl7 you will be bombarded by ads. So many you'll have frequent crashes & quite a bit of lag from ad play. You can earn loads of diamonds which are needed BUT you have to pay to collect the diamonds you earn. If you keep this app you'll have to play exclusively offline to keep crashes from happening.

Pretty fun. I get using ads in a few game but this one forces you to watch an ad between every single game. And some ads have no way to close even after they complete, sending you to play store to download. If you go back it presents the same window with no way to close the ad. Have to exit the whole game. I'm sick of it.

Its an alright game. If you have patience then you can adjust to the mechanics of it. The negative of it, is that you have to aim and then try to hurry and tap the button to shoot your target. The crosshair moves on its own after a 5 second stall. I guess we can blame it on the imaginary wind resistance. üòÑ

Fun game. But it moves rather slowly. Too many ad breaks & I feel as though in order to progress through the game any faster would cost real money. The idea of running out of energy to complete tasks and having to wait until energy returns is odd. You basically have to not play the game for a while to play it again. So, cool game, but I would have paid for an ad free version. But even in a paid, ad free version, I'm sure there would still be forced, in-app purchases.

It's a fun enough game, but maybe it's time for another update for bugs and glitches. I have entered the daily shooting range and won weapons only to have them not added to my inventory. Reward videos randomly load and you may get your rewards. There should be a link in the game app to contact someone to let them know issues

I played thru all 21 levels without spending any money. Problem is I don't care to play the PvP or the world ops. Now it just boring, it looks like no more levels are going to added. Fun, but extremely violent game. If you are looking for free play THIS IS NOT the game for you! Every mission you get asked to make a purchase, and if not that, there's an ad. I would like to keep playing, but these issues make the game not worth the trouble. Pretty cool graphics, and developers are clearly talented, but the greed will drive you away

Fun but extremely overpriced. It plays good but the game has a membership for $120 a year when it's barely worth a permanent purchase of $10. (Which there is no permanent full game purchase) Linear equipment upgrades due to lack of money or energy to achieve money. And other weapons of the same tier require diamonds that you will never have enough of. And the sales are always above your money so you're forced to leave it or buy their currency.

To be honest its really a rip off. Not only do they bombard you with Ads trying to sell something everytime a mission is completed. Also when they offer you a gun even if you have the money you can't purchase it with out having a premium membership which is up too 70$ I believe it was so frustrating I uninstalled the game. It's just not worth the hassle when there so many other better games that doesn't require you too buy a membership.

Pretty cool game. Good graphics, plot, missions, etc. But unless you pay, real money, for upgrades, the game becomes impossible to progress to the next levels. I dont mind working for some of my upgrades. And I understand the creator of this game is trying to make money for his/her hard work creating this game. But making it impossible to progress in the game and forcing the player to purchase upgrades just sucks!!! Sorry - Uninstalled :-(

Just wasn't for me...way way to many commercials and that is when it wasn't crashing or loading up...tried several times to uninstall and reinstall it in hopes to get it to work with no luck...great idea and I hope they fix it and I also hope it works better for others...I don't like giving low stars on apps..I know someone took a lot of time into making this...I hope you get this working better and becomes a number 1 game... üíØ%

Fun game, and minimal ads at the early levels, but once you keep dismissing the offers to go premium, they start pummeling you with ads. I kid you not. If I'm having to watch 2 twelve second ads after every mission, I'm done. It literally takes almost as long as the mission itself. Plus, the upgrades feel rigged. You cna spend all your "winnings" on upgrades, and then like 2 missions later your gun isn't powerful enough. Too much of a pay to play sales funnel.

This game use to be awesome. I have spent a lot of money. I dont now. When the new trophy fix and patches came about everything went awry. Instability, miscounting of points one should receive or no points. Can barely get connected to participate. Gone through the wildlife procedure...no problems on my end. Always server problems. What is going on? Are there specific patches for different parts of the world? Contacted the developers on too many occasions..same answer no problems on their end. Very frustrating.

Fun, but quite easy for a long time. Must keep upgrading weapons to even attempt missions. I don't mind ads and working to earn items, but not both of those plus pay to play. The three different currencies are another way to get it real money.

Just like everyone else's reviews, the game just had too many ads. While in PvP you constantly lose connection, points and playability if you can connect to the server at all. Special offer guns can rarely ever be bought because they are a higher level than you are able to purchase. Don't offer if it's impossible to purchase. The game could be fun if it was playable but as is it's just annoying, frustrating, and feels like a cash grab.

Love the game , but you have to buy your moneys for upgrades. You win diamonds to get upgrades, but they put them in a bank and you have to pay for them. The higher levels cost more money. Level 3 you have to pay $10 for diamonds. If you don't you progress slowly. You can gain 10 diamonds for watching a 20 second video. But you needs thousands for upgrades. Kinda ridiculous.

Game is okay but there are always problems getting the awards for watching adds and the supposedly "free" daily bonuses. Even worse was when I attempted to contact support in the game, I only get a bot who is repetitious and doesn't help. When I reached out via email, Google Mail couldn't deliver the mail to the address listed in the Play Store. These problems happened often enough that I ended up uninstalling the game as it was wasted space on my device.

I've been playing this game for years and my opinion has changed several times. At firat, I dismissed it as a greedy money-hog but after passing a certain tall slump, it becomes playable without having to put money into it. Affter a year-long hiatus from it though, I have to bring it down to 2 stars for 2 reasons: (1) too many ads and (2) it teases you with guns that are inaccessible without diamonds (while locking you out of buying it with coins). Dirty tricks! Still fun when they're not trying to scam ya...

Game is fun. you can play for free for a while, but at some point you will need to put some money in it in order to advance. 3 major issues that the game has : 1 - you do NOT get all the rewards when you win in PVP battles, 2 - support does NOT get back to you when you submit a ticket (besides the process is very difficult, since you have to go thru a Bot that asks really stupid questions and never answers!!); 3 - constant server issues that create lags and issues in PVP battles or other contests. I guess these issues are ok as long as you play the game for free. But I would not pay for it, knowing that these issues are rampant. Many reviews mention same similar issues.

It's fun until it's not. Then it's frustrating. Then you feel like you're being ripped off. After a month or so of play I've learned some of the game's quirks. Some are annoying; others are unfair. 1. Coins earned are not awarded. The math doesn't add up. Example from a recent game: Mission reward: 2,852K Headshots: 160 With Premium: 2,852K TOTAL: 5,704K 2. Opportunities to watch videos to earn diamonds or double awards don't always work. You tap the screen and nothing happens. 3. Routinely have trouble connecting to server in both PVP and general play. 4. Battle tokens disappear. On two recent occasions I tapped the "upgrade" button and, before I could select an option, 180 battle tokens drained from my total without explanation. 5. Many times, after the game fails to connect to server, the required number of Experience Points are not replenished or refunded after they are deducted. 6. there are no rules of play. It's easy to figure out the basic rules (IE: "I shoot you, I get points. You shoot me, you get points") but beyond that is unclear.

Continuously begs for money. Every "special deal" requires more coin/gems than you have, so then you can buy them with real money. Premium is 4.99/week for a mobile game with 30 second missions, thats 260 dollars a year and even then you would have to pay more money to progress. Uninstalled less than 24 hours after downloading it Not just P2w, its stupidly expensive on top of that.

I had high hopes for this game but it is complete garbage. It is very fun but once you reach a certain point then the game becomes driven by in app purchases. my biggest issue is with the piggy bank. It could be a great way of rewarding players who can't purchase the packs all the time, but instead it's just another way to bleed us. If it wasn't for the near impossible way of getting better weapons, and the terrible money system, this game would 5 stars. Needs more opportunities to unlock items.

The targets health scales per level, and headshots on enemies (with zero helmets) past level 6 or 7 require ammo and muzzle device upgrades, but they arent really upgrades, they are just options that increase the guns performance without actually adding a logic change to the gun itself (like upgraded bullets don't become fragmented hollownpoints. They just magically do more damage. So, You must upgrade rifle with redundant upgrades like ammo, muzzle, etc to keep up with level increases.

Standard game play is fine; actually somewhat relaxing sometimes to just shoot for target practice during campaigns and such. However, PVP is an awful experience. It seems nearly impossible to spot anybody unless you're just lucky enough to be looking in the right direction, yet somehow others find ways to locate you quickly (almost as of they have a radar cheat or something like that). Also, the matchmaking process doesn't seem to match you with similarly leveled players, which is not fun...

pretty decent game until it starts glitching and you can't get past the level because you either kill the wrong person when it's really the right person or doesn't recognize that you're shooting the person that you're supposed to be shooting. It's an ok game. Decent time waster with no real story or super difficult tasks. Nothing like that. Good for the bathroom break, bus ride or waiting room. My only problem with it, and why I uninstalled the game, was the amount of unskippable ads which just seem to randomly pop up on you. It's annoying. And I'm sorry, the game isn't that good for me to soldier through. 2/22 update: redownload, looks like they now delay the ads until you've played a while. Still not worth it.

The game is fun, but it's starting to have too many bugs and server disconnecting to keep it from running smoothly. It's ok for free players, but it's truly made for people to pay in order to get the real experience of the game. The parts of it meant to help free players always break down which push people into paying to play if you want to advance in the game.

Good game if you want to waste time not super difficult or intricate also an offline game so thats cool. My problem with it is its pay to win. You're required so spend a bunch of coins to upgrade the only affordable gun, then can no longer use it once you complete all primary tasks and have to buy another one with coins you don't have in order to advance to the next level.

Cool game. The ads are very short and most of the time you can "X" out of them before they even finish. Game play is smooth. Graphics are decent. The game engine can be sketchy at times but not so much it becomes annoying or frustrating. My biggest hang up so far is the name edit function. It keeps reverting back to my REAL NAME. No matter how many times I change it, it wont stick. And screw asking for support with the email listed, they dont read it or answer it.

Edit: End edit. Addictive, but fun! Can't play too long without paying and especially long when you factor in the expensive guns and upgrades you need. Sure, you can play free but it's rather boring that way....sigh. Now, when actually playing, it is pretty cool. It's fun and the controls are actually intuitive and responsive. Overall, the game is setup rather well.

I have very mixed opinions on this game, there are hundreds of guns to choose from, it's not just sniper rifles, you can get pistols and shotguns and assault rifles and even special weapons, which is good, but this game feels overall cheaply made and programmed, it needs a sensitivity selection because it is way too high, the graphics are 15 years behind, and it's overall pretty cheap. also the game is mind-numbingly easy, and the missions are the most repetitive thing since I whip my hair.

great fun excellent graphics but one major issue, if you don't spend money you do not play or advance, they have it rigged so you can't aim and shoot in the last set of required kills. you try aiming to the left and it will only go right or you try shooting and all the sudden your gun won't fire, it's not fair to have spent the amount of time and skill it takes to get that far only to be screwed around by not being able to shoot or aim like all the other targets. it is a fact pay or loose. l

Game is pretty fun and gives a lot of different playing modes. The one thing that ruins the game for me is the placement of the zoom and fire buttons. I have bigger fingers so a lot of times when I try to zoom in it fires the gun too. It would be really nice if the buttons were spaced fatter apart. Or if we could just have a button to push for zooming in, like every other shooting game I've ever played. Have the scopes be variable zoom, one press is 4x, two presses is 8x, etc

It's a fun game that after the first level gets fairly difficult. Unfortunately, the weaponry you need to proceed with any success is virtually impossible to get without spending actual money. There's no possible way to "earn" them. When I reached the level of defending against teams of shooters with a 2 shot hunting rifle, it lost it's luster.

The developer is greedy as hell! Constantly requires you to spend more money every day just to play or continue. After you are several hundred $$$ deep into it, they put you in a position where you cannot continue after level 17 unless you spend even more money! I'm uninstalling this frustrated because I otherwise loved the game. It was addicting. But when it costs 2-3 times what an X-Box game costs and they still keep requiring more and more $$$, then I have to draw the line somewhere. I am drawing that line today. They have more than enough of my money...

I am having fun with this. Just wish there was an option to turn off the camera that follows the bullet. Its more fun watching people fall from a distance. Also the missions end too quickly when you shoot random people. Needs a mode where you can shoot whoever maybe timed and untimed. Also a sandbox mode to make your own missions or whatever would be amazing. Also I would rather buy the game and not deal with in app purchases. Flesh it out a little more and charge for the game instead.

The controls are more towards 3 star because it gets crowded. Finding your target is more difficult than necessary. A lot of features are bent towards purchasing. The reminders that you can get better mats by purchasing are annoying. Even the items that become available with in-game currency at "discount" are not obtainable without serious grind. Could have been better. Uninstalled.

the gameplay is good, but why oh why is there an ad that pops up every single time i complete some type of mission?! it lags and drags and takes long to get back into the game. i love this game, great shooter. but if it weren't for these ads i would've given it more stars. it's too the point i have to sometimes restart my phone bc it freezes due to this issue. and yes, it takes way to Long to respawn in pvp mode. PLEASE FIX SOON

This game needs more updates. The frame rate needs to be fixed. The ads are frequently interrupting me. The game crashes constantly. I always miss shots because of the frame rate. Whenever I do the Christmas events, it always crashes and I waste energy. The game needs offline playing like when you are on vacation without internet, you can't play without any internet, or when you have an internet/electrical outage and you are bored, you can't do anything. Would've gotten 4-5 stars if you updated.

Very good time killer, fun and stuff, but 1st, Energy gain time for 10 minutes is a bit much, and according to Logic, this game doesnt have any. on a mission in the second city, I shoot the guy wearing blue headphones IN THE HEAD, and he gets to run away because "I didn't have enough damage from my gun". He, at least, should have walked or fallen dead, since he wore nothing on his head except those blue headphones. That, is the only complaint I have with this game so far.

3 stars because: 1. The game crashes often 2: there tends to be too many adds. You get one after nearly every mission. 3. There is some bug or glitch where the game spases out. You cant stop it, you cant pause, you can only close the game and reopen it. This happened to me a few times. It also happens on the main menu. Also, when i try to but any sniper with diamonds it just says saomething about server sync. I dont know how to fix it. Otherwise, it's a good game.

It is a fun game, without a doubt, and very straightforward. Shoot the badies and clear the stage, not much to it, but satisfying. I don't happen to enjoy the amount of ads to spend "IRL money", and at such a high price. Every other round at least plus another here and there is a bit overkill. I feel like I'm being "nickel and dime'd", but if you can get over that, pretty good game.

Simple and fun, not a ground breaking game, but it's nice to casually play and kill time. I haven't had any issues playing yet without feeling I need to spend money. The only thing I see, is that there is a circle with bars (energy), every mission or task takes one off, but when you level up it replenishes. I'm assuming at higher levels, this may be an issue, but I haven't ran into that yet. 3 stars only because I haven't played hours on this yet to properly give it a proper review.

Great graphics, plots, mission, weapons, etc. Glitches: I have seen the common complaint about the energy bar not refilling. Mine will fill but empty after just one play. Sometimes when I am in the sniper arena, my shots don't register for the entire time until I die and regenerate. My biggest complaint is you can't progress without spending real money. I spend money to upgrade only to find 5 minutes later they want more money to upgrade again or you cant progress.

Overall the game is fun. My only complaint is: when I have no energy and agree to play two rounds of another game, to receive energy, but after playing those two rounds, i still have zero energy. I've stopped playing the game, until the problem is fixed. Otherwise, i would rate it at least four stars.

very fun game. i played through and beat every level. says coming soon.. will there be more cities added? only downfall is that i got addicted to it and ended up spending way to much money on it.(like new xbox and many games type of cost) then figured out how to win and save up and go through all of the levels without buying tokens or gems. still needed to purchase a little to finish the levels but beat the game. would give it 5 stars but it costs way to much. i dont know what i was thinking!!

Pretty fun although the controls are a little wonky. It's easy to accidentally shoot, which can scare away the target. Restarting requires using energy, which takes a while to replenish. It seems very hard (maybe impossible) to get any gun other than the default one without paying due to the sheer price of them.

i fell in love with this game almost instantly and then I got to level 5and have been unable to complete the level because I feel that there is a flaw in the development of the game, when you start level 5 the touchscreen simply put goes haywire and makes it impossible to beat the level.
