Fun..but chill with the ads. Also the premium is way overpriced $12 a month is absurd for such a simple game. Lower the premium price to 2 or $3 a month you might change my review. Also you don't need to have an ad to see if someone wants to buy new weapons in between every mission. That's on top of the third party ad. I also get this off playpass which there wasn't supposed to be any ads which was disappointing.

I'd like to give it 5 stars, but I can't. The game is fun and challenging at times. There have been issues with it saying that I have no internet connection when trying to make purchases and receive bonus rewards. I've deleted the game and reloaded it with no changes. I've had issues with targets that were shot with headshots not counting as headshots, targets not falling after being eliminated, and targets shooting me from places it will not let me aim at. Wish the troubles would get fixed.

Pretty cool game but not cool enough unless your willing to spend a bunch of cash in order to get the guns and upgrades you really need. Another complaint... I like how they have an option to watch ads in exchange for diamonds so you can actually accumulate enough for the neccessary upgrades and weapons. Except it only works half the time. I missed out on soo many bonuses because the videos wouldnt work. Pretty frustrating..

Basically a trial. The game itself isn't bad. Graphics are OK. Gameplay is solid. Max Payne style bullet headshots. Feels very satisfying. But after playing for about 15-20 minutes, I didn't have enough money to upgrade my gun enough to play the next mission. Also, I ran out of energy and have to buy more energy credits to play missions or if you fail. I am about done with all free android games. It's become a cesspool of how much money can we suck out of people for a mediocre game.

This is kind of catchy at first. It does some things right. The gameplay gets repetitive quickly. Especially the 'warehouse' and 'prison break' missions. They mainly want your $$$$!! The ads get very old quickly!! You reach level 8 or so and it gets really buggy. The multiplayer really brought this up to par though. It just isn't given enough development to be great.

Fun game, but there are so many ads it's ridiculous. The game just wants you to spend money to get upgrades that are required for difft levels. I really liked playing it, but between the relentless ads, and lack of 'coins' for upgrades to continue, and requests for money, it's just too much. All of this made it not fun to play anymore.

So...I like this game. But as with most "free" games, there are LOTS of ads. Seems I might be able to get around that by subscribing for $60 a year (or $12 a month or $5 a week) but that hardly seems worth it. Would consider buying one of the smaller packages of they removed ads. Update...Uninstalled. I would keep if there was a more reasonable way to get rid of ads. $60+ for a mobile game is not worth it for me.

Fun game that gets to a slow crawl quickly without spending real money. You have to upgrade your weapon to be able to successfully do missions but there comes a point where you aren't making enough coins anymore to be able to upgrade and you have to use energy points to grind the same low paying missions to save up. It's a good tease to reel you in to spend real money. The ads weren't too bad, also.

I enjoy playing the game. Easy to understand and get into, but the ability to get weapons without paying is ridiculous! You are constantly being reminded to upgrade...which of of course you cannot due without paying. I really think this would be a fun experience if it wasn't constatly asking for money.

Overall the game has been lots of fun. But recently there's been a problem with upgrades. When I try to upgrade a gun to level 7 it says ' server sync failed.' and then it doesn't upgrade. But it never happens for levels 1 to 6. So that seems weird and its kind of annoying.

I really enjoy playing a lot, but there are several major problems w/ aspects of the game, example: 1- it's almost impossible to aim from moving platforms, 2- you can only look through your scope to fire or lower your weapon to look around, but in wide view you can't shoot at all. Only allowing me to shoot when using the scope is a huge fail. Another major bug is 3- the "lost internet" messages which are always incorrect but continue to occur regardless. Still I do like playing.

it's fun and addictive but it's basically pay to win, can still win without paying but unlocking new weapons takes forever...you'll never have enough for any of their special offers...the multiplayer is fun but opponents always have better gear and you'll just end up spending whatever you have on upgrades for one weapon. Overall it's fun, good graphics, just sucks that they try to suck money out of you.

So far I love it. It's crazy I'm getting a kick out of shooting characters, but I am lol. Update 12/27/20. I still enjoy this game. However. I am being cheated out of diamonds, coins and Free Premium trial. When I click to watch videos, nothing plays, so I never get the reward for that. I've leveled up for a free premium trial due to head shots, and everytime I click it, It says mission failed. And I've been offered double rewards to watch videos, but the videos do not play. Please fix!

The only way to win online is to not upgrade your gear so you play scrubs and get the most powerful rifle in the game to one-shot everyone. I spend most of my time just being dead waiting to respawn. If you dont have a great rifle, you can win by simply spawning at the right spot in the beginning of the game. Needs major reworking to be less frustrating to play against others so that players can't just win by not putting on expensive gear. My suggestion would be to simply add the damage output of the rifle to the gear rating so that players can't cheat the system so easily.

I mean, its a great, fun game where you can buy your own weapons, customize them and all this other stuff, but it seems so.... flat? Also, EXPENSIVE!! Okay, so what I mean is for each mission you are suggested to level up. Even if you level up 2-3 x to get ahead you still need to level up for the next mission. ALSO, they are very good at making you spend money IRL. For instance, they give you a piggyback and when it fills up with dimonds you can open it and take the dimonds IF you pay for it.

This is a pretty nice shooter game. Though aiming the sniper is king of hard, the controls are easy and simple. Average graphics, like the ones in GTA San Andreas. The people you shoot don't seem to express their emotions on their faces. Overall, it's a pretty good game. But it's also filled with pop up adds and is also very greedy, persuading players to make in-game purchases.

It was a decent game to start out with, but unless you want to spend a lot of money, interest is lost. Eventually, you can no longer advance because the weapons you have are not powerful enough to even start a mission. The only way to get the weapon needed or to upgrade it, is to buy tokens to buy the weapons. Earlier in the game, you could watch ads to obtain limited bonus tokens, but eventually that stops, so then it is nearly impossible to get the tokens needed (unless you buy them). NO.

The game is great, but in this recent war, our enemy team has changed about 7 times to different teams, with higher ranks. we were winning, then it keeps changing, and we are losing now. something has happened, and this app has been hacked or something. cant win if they keep changing out the team you're going against.

I like the game as it's good for when you have a little time to kill and it seems everything is obtainable without using in game purchases. My issues are that I tried the free premium trial to see if it was worth paying for as I really like the game, but received none of the premium benefits, and my email to them went unanswered. And with the radar in pvp not being very accurate (like saying im being shot from the left, and showing them on the right after I die) it's difficult to stay interested

It's a great game! ...low-key it kind of gives you an idea of a snipers frame of mind satisfied, in a way if one isn't too careful it can be very influential... all in all I give you three stars because there's still a few bugs, a few Kinks to work out before it could be what very well should be!! In conclusion is very well worth a try! I even find myself wanting to make a few buys!

Ok, going down another star. Game is still really good, but as you level up you have to adjust for wind and distance but there are no markers as to know where this two factors sit, that way you can adjust. Being prior military this is a huge issue. Am I supposed to guess what the parameters are? After the money I've spent you should be better able to adjust to the situation.

Good game. My only issue is that in the middle of the PVP matches, shots sometimes stop registering. I can sit there and shoot an opponent and nothing happens. It's very frustrating. Especially when you are winning and get screwed by this glitch. Please fix this and I will upgrade my rating to 5 stars. Until then, only 3 stars.

Save your money!!! Can't believe the amount of money I've spent on this to move up in the ranks and now everything works until I start a mission. Then it freeze up and I can't aim or zoom in to shot targets!! They have fixed alot of the issues I talked about but I wish there was a way to resell weapons that are useless as you move up in ranks.

The first 3 seasons are fun. Great actually! Really fun. Then guns/upgrades start costing a lot so you play another 3 because you figure you've already invested some time. But then the guns/upgrades start costing 23, 25, 29 mil and you gotta update each item 5 or 6x and you're only getting 6 mil or 2.2 mil for the smaller games... It's not real fun anymore. And the time you invested... ya chalk it up to a waste. It's kinda crappy cause this is a really fun game. This is the 3rd time I've downloaded it. It is extremely fun. One of the most enjoyable games I've downloaded in the last 6+ yrs.

It's ok the graphics could be better and it's just like every other game out there where u have to bust your but getting points to upgrade your rifle and when it's finally optimized and you've spent every credit on it. All of a sudden it's no good on the next level and a new one costs way to much so your stuck playing the lower level for a month to earn enough for the new gun and then that's not even enough u have to upgrade it b4 u can use it. Just make a game that costs 5 and give everything 0

Overall, a decent game. The graphics are somewhat glitchy, but decent. The designers of the game REALLY need to work on the language translation, as it gets worse and worse as the game goes on. I'd happily volunteer to be a grammar nazi if it meant fixing the errors.

The game is fun and challenging, the only thing so far that I don't care for is all of the advertisements after every mission. Maybe you could put them in every so often instead of after each mission. I like to play this game but it gets old fast waiting to dismiss each of the ads all the time, otherwise I would have given it a 5 star üåü . Most upgrades you have to buy otherwise it does take forever to get enough money or diamonds with missions for upgrades without having to use a credit card.

Decent enough game. You can progress pretty far if you have the time and patience. Or money of course. The regular missions are pretty straight forward. Mostly easy. Every now & then the parachute ones can be a little annoying. PvP is fun once you get the hang of it, plus they'll respawn characters (literally) right next to each other way too often. And speaking of respawning, it seems like it takes an eternity to respawn once you get murked. Plus the hacking & disproportionate matching sucks.

I like the game but there are so many ads and videos to watch. I would have actually paid for the game to stop all the nonsense, but it costs 60.00 a year. Yes, per year. And to top it all off, you can only play for like 15 minutes at a time and it makes you either pay to keep playing or watch a video or make you wait a half hour to play again. 3 stars at best because it's a great time killer. Worth maybe 10 - 15 bucks to purchase. Not 60.

At first the game was a great past time, and it still is but i switched to a new phone and started fresh and its terrible. Ads every time you finish a task Bam an ad. When i upgrade a gun and back out bam another ad every time i move inside of the app its annoying. I watch more ads than i get to play the game. Literally minute to two minutes im having to watch an ad. So out of an hour of game play i actually get 20 minutes of play. Im at the point of deleting the game for good its that bad....

The game overall is decent, and I think its the best sniper game thats available on android. The issue i have with it though is that when you play PVP, you are battling against a lot of people who are a way higher ranking than you a lot of the time, so its extremely easy to die. I think this is super unfair to those of us who are just starting out and i wish they would figure out a way to divide people into certain levels of difficulty when doing PVP.

Love the game. But constant upgrading of equipment gets old quick. And if you're willing to watch the CONSTANT ads for generally a little reward then it should at least work and not act like you either never touched it or that you already watched the video, without watching it or the double reward bonus.

I would personaly like my zoom and fire option on the right. The game also doesnt realisticly react to wind or bullet drop. Most shots are easy shots. I would also like to have more options for shooting platforms and not be locked into a predesignated firing point. You begin to hate the piggy bank. It makes getting upgrades harder if you only free play

A little hard to remember what I'm supposed to do with the control situations after taking a week away not playing it..so I gave up on even trying after 30 frustrating minutes trying to figure it out . Nice graphics and colour . If I was 23 years younger I would of figured the hand controls out way faster.

Ostensibly it is a free app. It's ok for what it is. Too much push for spending real money. Pick bank - just a trick for that as well. The "free diamonds", "double your coins" buttons hardly ever work. I still don't know how I going to gain "battle coins", yet I have to use them for upgrades that are necessary in moving forward.

This sniper game has a few 'defects', flaws that the player should not have to experience when preparing to find the criminal to shoot and simultaneously do to setup the shot. No sniper will use a bolt action, when the semi-automatic in case of a miss. And, at all times the zoom must be automatically engaged. And, a great sniper rifle does not have movements as the shot is locked on the target.

The game is fun, but it's annoying. The only perks I see from the membership are unlocking weapons that you can spend money on to use, or grind enough on "most wanted" levels to earn coin. Or you'll get a little more con after each mission. But the problem with that is it is constantly making you upgrade your weapons to move on. It's simply a money grab despite if they say otherwise. The bullet time is fun, up until you need to upgrade constantly, and then simply isn't worth it beyond that.

Knocking off a star. Now forced to sit thru 30 second ads constantly and diamonds are worthless because you are ALWAYS offered things that cost more than you have to try to get you to spend actual $$ Fun game, and actually playable without paying. It does constantly try to entice you to buy upgrades and it would go faster if so. But I have had hours of enjoyment without giving in

Gameplay is cool, easy to use and not necessary to pay to play for awhile. Developer was unresponsive to lost credits however (even in their preferred contact method) and failed to replace "diamonds" or replace purchased item. Wasnt much money so can write off the game, but sucks that it didnt mean much to them.

I love playing this game for the past few months, but the game upgrades just keep freezing on me, so I have to keep uninstalling and reinstall the game but doesn't fix. sadly theres no customer service option in game to ask for help. I'd rank this higher but if this is how the game is gonna be theres no point. It's a fantastic game no the less.

This is a fun game. The only issues are the feature that allows you to watch a video for more energy or to double the reward doesn't always work and the upgrades are too expensive. Also there is no save feature. I swapped phones and all my progress and precious purchases were lost. Extreemly frustrating!!

Brand new, 3 missions, but so far its good ~ It pushes hard for you to buy upgrades w rl money (never), and has a hated "energy meter", so how long it lets me play before that runs out, and how hard it is to balance a small phone in your hands while juggling a wavering scope and trying to tap a "fire" button, all without fumbling and dropping a pricey phone as suspects try to run away, THAT determines how fun this game is in the long run. It has the *potential* to be a simple, satisfying game.

My main problem with this game is that it has a energy meter. There is absolutely no reason you would need a energy meter in a game like this, and if your playing offline the meter doesn't refill whatsoever. It also is quite p2w when it comes to PvP, and new players can't even participate because there is no selective matchmaking and 10 bullets to the head won't leave a scratch on better geared players. The main gameplay is alright, but it gets repetitive.

Game is great minus the obvious cash grabs. "Special deals" off of guns, but the guns that always come up are always more than you can afford even with sale price or arent buyable due to weapon tier level. When you have a decent amount of cash (30k or so) the discount prices NEVER show up. Only option would be to buy with real money (gems). More than half of the guns are gems only. If you want to play for more than 10 minutes, be prepared to spend a boatload on gems. On top of all the forced purchases due to the rapidly increasing difficulty vs the money earned, you get spammed with an ad at the end of each mission

Good game, a little difficult when they want you to shoot a moving target without giving you any lead. Also apparently the bad guys can see and shoot through buildings but you can't. Have been shot by hidden bad guys several times because they can see me and shoot through the building they're hiding behind because I can't see them.

Fun game at the start. Once you get further in the game it's. Almost impossible to progress without spending your own money. The ads seem to get worse further into the game. Play a level then an ad. Then another ad giving you a gift. Piggy bank is a joke, once filled up then they want you to buy the diamonds. Understandable, free games really are not free. Other than the constant ads, and the app always wanting you to buy something. Not a bad game

Exellent game. The only two things that I would highly recommend, is to make a way to earn currency and energy by watching ads, and to make way more missions with harder difficulty settings. Other than that, I think the game is excellent. Three stars until fixed though

Mixed... The challenges are certainly fun... but when you run out of energy (goes quickly) you kinda sit around for a while! This game is heavy on ads (you get free currency this way), but sometimes the option to play the ad for the reward just doesn't work. Until you make a purchase (I used the last of a Google play card) you get interrupted after every mission you do with an ad. The game has a biiiig grind, and it tries it's hardest to get you to pay to play. And things just stop working...

Very fun start, and pretty entertaining for the first couple days. But the required weapons needed for mission then become so expensive that one would pretty much have to start spending real world money to keep playing. The amount of diamonds needed would literally take a week or more of grinding to have enough for even the cheapest tier 2 wepon. But worth installing and playing for a couple days. Just don't get attached to game unless you are ready to start spending cash to keep playing.

Love playing this game. Very challenging missions and awesome weapons and graphics. There are a few drawbacks thought, you almost have to spend money, because you need to consistently upgrade your weapon or buy a new one and upgrade that one in order to play missions and advance to new ones.

Overall OK but I HATE the fact that my time to play is reduced because of my energy level. I'm a fu@%in' sniper sitting on a roof how can my energy be drained? That is ridiculous. The other negative thing is the constant prompts that come up to upgrade your weapon, which if you want the better ones it makes you purchase them, or offers you to purchase them (which I never do). I like to play it but because of the two negatives above I will probably stop soon.

I love the game but it has had its serious issues with cheaters, Many people have experienced not being able to connect for server errors, The only way to get around that for a time was to buy a new weapon upgrade everything but one category such as ammo, And then it would bypass the server error but of course you would be handicapped, I believe they were trying to weed out the cheaters. However you still have SUPER SNIPERS In the PVP arena killing beginners with one shot over and over.

It does take a while to get the coins you need to upgrade your weapon but if it didn't you'd get through it too fast. The special missions like Halloween and Christmas suck because you can't use the weapons in other missions, what's the point? The pvp respawning needs to change. Sometimes I'm dead within seconds because I respawn in front of someone. Also how the hell can others find me so fast. Again, sometimes dead within seconds of respawning.

It is a really great game single player wise, but the multiplayer is so unbalanced and broken as to where you can shoot a guy 25 times in the head and they'd be at half health but they can kill you with 3 body shots. They shouldn't put those people who are so far ahead with the people who have no chance against them.

Great game. Horrible glitches. I started out playing for free, enjoyed it and decided to buy a package, and that's when things went south. More often than not, I can't double my rewards or receive the free diamonds as advertised. I click the button, and nothing happens. No ads. I don't know if this is an on going issue or a recent one, but it definitely makes the game less enjoyable, which is why I'm giving it three stars.

Complete pay to play. Don't expect to get anywhere without spending real money. If you are okay with that, it's a fun game. I'm having some issues with the ads giving me diamonds though. It's just unresponsive and causing headaches and when it does work, it is always for another of their games 'war machines'. I've already missed out on about 200+ diamonds because of it. And that caused me to miss out on a really good tier 6 sniper rifle that I'll need for the next levels.

Great game. But way too many ads. And if you want the really cool weapons it's definitely a pay to play game. Also you get diamonds that can be used to purchase weapons but after a certain point all your diamonds go into a stupid piggy bank that you have to pay $2.99 to open and collect otherwise you lose them after a set amount of time. Come on really? Aren't you making enough with all the damn commercials? discountedweapons at times but they always cost more than you have. Pay 2 play.

Enjoy playing but get a lot of server maintenance and can't get bonus a lot of the time. And sometimes men be shooting at me from behind walls or out of the concrete floors. But are making some improvements but hard to advance when time is ticking on you and you're getting shot by people you can't see let alone shoot.

love playing this game! my single and complaint and large frustration is that between each level, you have to upgrade arsenal so much that you can't afford to do so without buying something. Game would be perfect if you could sell back older weapons that you have no use for.

This is a fun game, although some levels are super tough to beat. Evenutally I will manage to beat the level. I've pretty much beaten all the available missions, however at the moment there is no next mission just a "Coming Soon" image. Would like to be able to continue on with the next mission but nothing is coming to fruition. Interesting how they keep creating side missions like tournaments but no regular missions.

Game is okay. Graphics leave a bit to be desired and there is definitely a pay to play aspect when it comes to pvp but I like that I can just play solo missions. Mainly the bump down in stars for inconsistent scoring. On range for example I will get all head shots and not miss a round and score 480 other times I'll miss rounds or miss head shots and get 620. Seems to be pretty random. Always behind on buying guns and thats how they get you to spend money. Overall not a bad game.

Too many annoying ads between missions that don't allow you to exit the ad even when clicking on the X. And the X starts on the left side of the screen then appears on the right side of the screen. Most are loud and obnoxious even with the sound turned down on my phone.

Not to bad of a game, but there is quite a few bad things like it takes a ton of money for upgrades. This means to progress, you will have to do countless side missions. A 15 second mission requires a 30 second video and it burns thru data like mad. It is the same mission over and over...

This would be an amazing game but too many ads. If you try and close the video ads they still laumch your browser. The same for game apps - especially candy crush - and the Play Store. For both the game (screen) hangs for a good 30 seconds each time. Cut down the ads guys and make the reload faster and you have a winner! I'm going to uninstall the game now. Enjoyed and would have kept it except for these issues.

PvP has major problems with lost connections. I like the game, but this issue is very annoying. Internet is perfect on my end. I see many others have the same problem. Will not be making any more in-app purchases until I can at least go through five rounds without losing connection.

I'll start by saying that I love this game. It's tons of fun and i play it every day. Now comes the negative review portion. After beating levels you are sometimes given the option to watch an add and by doing so double your reward or gain extra diamonds both of which are used for upgrading your weapons and you DEFINITELY need all you can get or else you'll be spending a lot of money on the game. The game will give you the option but 8 out of 10 times the add will never play and nothing happens.

Game is kind of challenging. Don't like being forced to by things. Loose the piggy bank, have to order upgrades? THAT IS STUPID! Once you buy something for your weapon you loose it on next target. Once you buy something why do I have to buy it again? THAT'S STUPID! Make it more free to play ! I don't mind watching the adds my choice if I want to download them . Let me choose what weapons I think will do the job on the running and multiple moving target's

Game is great but support is terrible. I went ahead with their Premium Plus and get constant error messages. I deleted app and reinstalled, disconnected Google account and reconnected. Restored 20 times. Works for 30 minutes and is gone. I email support and they reply with asking to use some imaginary help button in the app. Would love to but it doesn't exist.

The game is fun. It has various challenging missions and interactive platforms. But the app has issues.. it lags, a lot. Bonus videos continuously won't play which means I'm missing out on extra coins and extra diamonds; that is seriously annoying! Watch out for hidden costs too!!

Freeware bloated with ton of guns, missions and frustrating in-game popups about special deals and paid subscription specials. On my second visit to this game from a year ago, back then similar missions no distractions just fun and action. The action has been crushed by repeated popups now. way too many, it literally forced me to uninstall. Treating users differently ( seen at guns selection) makes you feel low if you are different type of user. An action game should not be distracting.

It's a good game but PVP is horrible, and in the primary missions (in the third city is where I had this problem) bullets sometimes would fly straight through the targets dealing no damage (This happened on #24 and #25) which messes the mission up for you and costs you one energy, there are also TONS of notifications, I actually got two for the same thing within 5 minutes of the first.

At first this game was awesome and challenging, but then it started going down quickly, and then BOOM BA DA BING. Suddenly, I couldn't procede without spending $10- $20 to get upgrades. These upgrades are apparently so crucial, that $10- $20 must be spent. After $10- $20, another $20- $40, oh and not to mention that it just started to suck. So me being me, I didn't spend a cent. Now if you have an unlimited amount of money, this is the perfect game for you. Oh , and merry Christmas there Bobby

I love the game, the only reason for the 3 stars is because their PVP options often times glitches or disconnects while in combat. I can be shooting people and nothing happens even at point blank and they can turn and shoot me no problems. This seems to be some sort of lag spike and I only experience it with this game.

Everything cost so much money and if you have dimands in the piggy bank you cant aceses them unless you pay 3 dollars it is VERY annoying like I mean you should be able to access your dimands without having to pay them! Also the things you shoot for is TOTALLY UNREAL I had to shoot someone for snatching a back pack I mean the game developers NEED some more real life situations to shoot for! Other than that the game is pretty fun and you can play most of it offline.

Good but full of ad delays. Play for about 20seconds. Then if you have failed the mission, have to watch a 1 minute video or vame advertisement. Price to go premium?? Which I hope would mean no ads, is $60!!! That's insane for something I'm just goofing around with while waiting for the dentist. If I could pay a few bucks for a paid ad free version it would have been a good game

Cool game, beat all 21 levels, waiting for new levels. Latest update has one annoying issue. When you run out of energy and the countdown timer hits zero, it shows that you have full energy, rather than just one bar. Kind of misleading and wish this would be fixed.

Great, fun game. However, it consistently leads you on a path towards spending real money to keep playing the game at your pace. I refused to spend a cent, consequently, I had to wait 15 minutes for this, 30 minutes for that. The rounds, if you're at least decent at any shooting game, will last 20 seconds. There's no upside. Uninstalled.

Very enjoyable, but, WAY to many ads, and few give you anything. They are just forced. Then the upgrades... you will have to pay real money if you want to upgrade many of the important features. You also have limited energy. Good game so 3 stars, but to many negatives for continuous play and upgrades for 5 stars... unless you have money of course.

Apparently your complaints only matter if you pay! This game would be 5 star if it didn't keep going into mode where I can't kill, but can be killed! I've lost many points, placements, tokens and diamonds because of this and for no friken reason away all! I've lost 100's of points and tokens and placement when my friken pvp round won't even load and I don't even play the round! Ive put a lot of time in this game because I used to enjoy it and recommend it, now lose valuable items!

It's q great game very addicting. But it drains your coins. At every turn you have to be spending. The game does not allow beginner to advance without having to spend alot of money. There are just some level you can't pass without having to spend on a new gun then upgrading it and then there's still alot of money spending in the online mode. One has to upgrade and buy new gear and this does not allow beginners a good chance against the pros.

Overall good game- good graphics, challenging missions. The only thing that really turned me away from this game was ads constantly appearing, especially before getting the chance to watch a video to claim a free reward.

The adds are now consuming much more of the game. You cannot play two minutes without being hit by a video add. I agree that these adds help you run this game, but when they get much of the game, they (adds) become the game and the game becomes boring to play. Kindly reduce frequent adds and instead of 30 seconds bring back 6,9,15 seconds adds.
You don't need to pay cash to upgrade and continue missions, but they make it increasingly difficult to complete without paying extra for "upgrades". Fun game overall.

In City 2, the 3rd Spec ops, I'm unable to complete it even though my gun meets all the criterias. Every time i try to shoot one particular guy, he doesn't die and my bullet doesn't go through. I thought there was a problem with the range so, even though my gun met all the criterias I fully upgraded the range and damage. But I'm still facing the same problem.

Every time you complete an easy 1 kill match,(takes approximately 30 seconds), you'll have to watch an unskippable boring ad of another 30 seconds.... soon you'll run out of supplies and you'll have to wait for another day for a bonus for a chance to get some supplies. Even watching ads to get supplies is not an option, the only way is to spend real money to pay for them. If you're ok with that, then go for it.

Was a very wonderful game . Used to play since years . Installed recently again and started since the beginning and I lost all my progress . Moreover even when I didn't purchase any diamond or anything it said payment successful and amount was also deducted from my account. I request the developers to please return the amount as it is very important and please do rectify this bug . It always rotates on each level even when offline as if it is loading some data . Please rectify this ASAP.

Played game before went premium after months of play. They lost all my efforts. Massive effort! They couldn't fix. As a non pay to play. Seriously challenging. All gear extremely hard to aquire . Sniper fodder. Once I started being potent. And thought I would pay .they lost everything.

It loads fast and is pretty fun. I think this game is ran by a bunch of shady peeps. Lots of decieving behavior when it comes to purchases. For example, big items pop up sales w huge discount that's always just a little bit more than u have Never available when u have game currency on band Also, purchased an elite weapon that was on sale, only to be told the sale happened to end at the exact same time I hit purchases .... Right . I bet. Too bad u got greedy, ur game had potential. Liars

The graphics is good, game enjoyable but interms of demand to upgrade all the time you want to do a mission becomes sort of a stressing game because l cannot enjoy my earnings at all since l have to keep purchasing staff. Allow the player to enjoy their earnings! Offline mode is very limited because now and then l need to go online to download content.

Watching videos to earn rewards stopped working. It will show a button to click to watch videos, but when you click on it, it doesn't work. It says you can double rewards or earn back energy, etc. but nothing happens when you click on it

Awesome thanks for the game 3 stars is the best I can grade with a good game normally 4 stars but too many times the advertising is a bit much, perfect as some are playing past 30 min a reduction? Cuz every single time u do snipe 95%of the time ads pop up and the people who are not excused from ads are keeping the game going üíØ if nothing more than to be involved for the "patrons' to snipe. White on white small font is not easy for phone playing but again it is a very fun game. Ty

Again, my main gripe with this and others of its ilk is having to aim, then take your eyes off your target, slide the mouse pointer to what feels like 12 yards to the left so you can click on the fire button....wait, what??? It's not how you shoot a rifle/pistol for real, why is it this way in these games? Is it too much to ask to make it aim, then click *Bam!* right where you're aiming? As it is, it's far from realistic and a boring chore just to pull a trigger. Fix it. Please.

I enjoy the game for the most part, however, the "special" gun offers ALWAYS are above your current diamond and gold levels, so really it's just a shadey way to get you to spend money as they won't make the same offer if you already have enough to purchase it. That in itself, really made me not want to spend money and they're lucky I gave them this rating. I could've gave them way worse... Also, the special shards to get special weapons are crazy high. You'd have to play 24/7 just to get enough.

I enjoy playing this game but there are some drawbacks that put limits on progress, success and fun in the game. First, everything, especially upgrades and gear, is EXPENSIVE AS HELL!!! Hundreds of thousands and millions of coins to upgrade a part of a weapon...not the whole weapon! Second, in P2P mode with multiple players going against each other there are wide gaps in player and weapon strength. This makes it extremely difficult for those who don't spend the money it takes to really play!

Very interesting game , would like to know more about it to review, after playing up to higher level, a message pop up asking for update and after updating it, it would not load up the game. Keeps reloading and reloading from Start to middle and starts reloading again.

userName: Member of the Unus Annus Cult
content: This is exactly like Sniper of Kill and is more or less better than it. The upgrading system is the same, the home page is similar, the missions page is almost identical, even the leveling is very identical. It's almost as if this game copied Sniper of Kill or vice versa. Whatever it may be, they're literally the same game.

It is (ok) game ... but what really bothering me and making me stop playing it is the amount the unskippable ads between each 1 minute mission.. i mean if u calculate it ... you have to waste almost 40% of the gaming time on the unskippable ads

Would be a decent simple first person shooter game if it didn't ask for money every 5 Seconds. This is an expensive game with weekly subscriptions running the minimum of $6. I realize everybody is trying to be paid for their time and I appreciate that, but I'm not trying to bankroll a yacht. Happy trails.

Great game, but annoying, I've purchased a gun with lots of my saving Coins and upgrade all needed, used for sometimes but next It remains un purchased, it already happened thrice, Can't move to the next level, Hope the developer will looked to this matter

Its a good game, the advertisements are extremely irritating and the time consuming. The weapons are very expensive and at some point when guns are offered they always put coins or diamonds you cannot afford.
They try lots of ways to get you to make in app purchases and ads to watch. Almost all these games do, so no surprise. Easy game play and short missions are great for playing on short time or long.

Fun gameplay, great time killer, but my number one problem is the piggy bank. No option to not use it, "earn" diamonds until it's full then have to pay to get the diamonds out? I'm going to continue playing as far as I can before I need to spend money on this "free" game. If I have to sit threw all these ads, I'm not buying anything in game.

The last 3 days when I'm playing the pvp it has trouble loading after game 2.Is something wrong on your end? For the last week when I go to the pvp it won't down load after the 1st.2 games. The rest of the game is fine just that.Can you fix this please? I just got on an awesome team and I want to perticipate as much as possible.

It is a nice game- I wonder if I'll be able to play it offline. The introduction gun the other guy borrowed me was mainly the reason I wanted to play the game- then he takes it away and leaves me only with an unstable rifle that will not easily give me a clean shot. - by the time I'm able to buy myself the gun that I want I would have completetly lost interest in the game.

I quite enjoy playing the game üëå. With that being said I find that the in game purchases are unreasonably priced. Quite expensive actually if I'm being completely honest. Too few worth while specials is a direct result of the expensive "normal" price. Still enjoy the game though, great game! üíØ
The graphics and everything is good but the timing on the recall and reload or something. As well as too many advertisements for buying more ammunition.

Am tired of the videos in between the game mode its absolutely 30 sec video it's literally irritated so please remove 30 sec video or deductions the duration atleast gave the skip option thank you otherwise it's really good game. If you remove the promotion video or you reduce the promotion video I'll gave a full star to the game

No doubt, s3d is an excellent game I'm addicted to this game and playing since 5 years, everything is good, but there is a very painful thing I found in the game is, hackers/cheaters who played with mod apk. They should be banned immediately and their squad also. So, pls make some restrictions and high security in the game so that they can't enter into the game with any apk mod. Pls save the game from cheaters and hackers. Thanks.
Awesome game, easy to control and realistic game play. Need more detail in graphics. But overall it served its purpose

got a message to update when I opened to play. Clicked the link but no update option. Uninstalled and reinstalled from the Google play and still getting update request. I guess that means I will be missing out on the Easter event. Hope you guys can fix it soon
Basic game is fair, bonus gift videos do not work. Although game listed as free, to get bonuses you must pay. Should be listed as pay to play as the only way to get past level 5.

Overall a decent game... The amount of money you need to spend isn't totally overboard. But, what is up with arena 'rankings'? I'm playing low rank yet I'm playing against people with a full ox or predator set, along with the best weapons in the game... M A X E D O U T. It is just like: wat. Balance it so you don't play against veterans when you are new, please.

Fun and challenging game but glitches quite a bit when not online such as when In airplane mode. I travel for a living and I've lost hundreds of thousands of coins making purchases offline it will deduct your coins but not give you the new weapon.

It is a fun game with some aggravating flaws. It is iften tedious.. once you get to a certain level it is very long and difficult to earn items and upgrade them. They have offers through tapjoy to earn diamonds that NEVER get paid although they say they have been awarded.

Although people are giving this game bad reviews, I think its not too bad. The levels are easy but best of all there are no ads. It CAN get addictive. If you don't like blood do not play this. Once you shoot the person they will bleed out like crazy. The characters are somewhat realistic but the blood definitely isn't.
It's a great game but if you could make the person able to move around and upgrade the graphics and make it not to do a slow motion when shooting one person
great game, but not enough of. rewards. upgrades & guns are too high & only way to get them is to buy them with actual money. game graphics are A 1 though.
I had to reload the game. Problems with serious lagging. Double rewards videos not playing, diamond rewards videos not playing. Could not get into World Ops. Giving it one more try.
Adds after every mission which take from 45 seconds to 5 minutes....so alot of ads and the weapons are stupid expensive...youll be stuck with the hunter rifle unless you pay to win.

I like the way the bullet travels plus its accuracy at times... enjoying it at the moment. I was too quick on giving the review.. too many ads which is quite disturbing and too many times they ask for money each time you level up or want to buy a new weapon. Very irritating.

Cant really play offline because you need to be online to generate more energy and cost way to much to buy weapons and upgrade them as well. Good game though. Nearly didnt keep on going past animal trafficking level with the two guys. I was luck to have double shot killing two guys with one bullet. Never expected that.

I love the game actually but the math is wrong when you're paying on the missions I made it all the way to the end and started over and halfway through I bought a gun and it took my money and never gave me the gun so I don't know if I'm going to play anymore or not anyway I did like the game

Hi Team, I installed the game and subscribed as well, it gave me vip access to War machine which I believe the game got never linked and I didnt get vip access. On top of tht to recharge my energy it said I meed to play 2 war machine games for +10 energy which I did but doesnt seems to be working

Very fun to play good graphics and weapons are real!!! Great job guys!!! The only downside is it's very expensive And when you don't have money to spend or you can't link a credit card it sucks cause you're extremely limited

You Can do better. An ad after every mission. I get it but after every mission. Good game but it is 3 star for all the ads. Just sad that gaming software dev companies are like this, is funding that tight considering you have over 500 million users? Not happy

If you've played cell phone sniper games in the past this is nothing new the only thing I like about it is the graphics are a little bit better than they were in the older versions of this but expect they had to pay while at some point and

I just started two days ago and it's been ok. Unfortantly it doesn't upload the option to double my rewards and I don't like that you need to play other games to win huge rewards of diamonds or pay money.

I love this game so much! I was happy because there's a game like this, i was looking for a lower MB of shooting game and i found this! This game graphics very good i enjoy this game it is so good game but one problemüò°üò° in this game is his all special and better gun price too much high enough too buy latest gun and difficult to collect (coin and diamond and other special coin) that reason i give only (3 star) to this game but sniper 3d is best game ever
The game is good, interesting and addictive. However, videos won't play to grab those bonus diamonds. Why? Until this happens, you'll have my 5 stars.

I am very dissatisfied with the fact that once you become a premium member, then opt out of that status, you lose the ability to get watch anymore videos. This means that you no longer have the ability to earn extra diamonds, double your cash, and any other of the small percs you get. It's not cool to say that if I stop paying for the app I can't receive any extras that you can if you don't pay initially. I recommend that you only become a premium member once you get closer to the tier 21.

I've just started playing this game,why the 3stars. It's a little on the easy side and the graphics could use some improvement, the weapons also. The big irritant is in order to get ahead you need to pull out your wallet to get ahead it's damn hard to get Jewel's.and.if you have any the pig swallows them up and holds them for ransom. If you can get over these and other little pickpockets without totally losing it, it's a good little game to pass the time.
Best sniper game ever the only drawback is too that there are too many adds in the and requires lots of coins to upgrade the weapons
Fun enough game but the ads are terrible. Every few seconds there's another ad. Some you can't even close and all you can do is force the game to shut off and restart it.
Should be more details about the levels and points. Whatever you get extra life from world ops will disappear once it reaches to 5. PVP ARENA connection issues. Apart from that decent time killer.
Yes it is good to play but there is no unlimited chance to accomplish a mission , you get just 10 chances . And graphics are little dull but it's ok.
Game us good, but seems that every time you finish 20 second mission, you have to watch a 30 second in app advert. Way too many adverts.

I had already buyed a tier 17 sniper rifle using 1.28m gold coins..and also upgraded it till level 3 ...next day when I opened the game it shows buy it option on same weapon...and had to buy it again..wasted coinsüòµ.. other than that no prblm...please fix this issue probably some bug...

Worst matching in PVP, Im a low rank sniper but my opponents are high ranking snipers that can easily kill me. It take a lot of shots for me to kill my opponent, but the others can 1Hit me. Please improve your match making.

Video to dark most of the time and don't like it when I have the arsenal to take someone out and still have to spend more money just to continue even thought I am already spending money and when I buy something why should I have to wait for it to be delivered
Very simple game, lots of adds, geared towards people willing to spend money, but otherwise fun and entertaining.
I am unable to play PVP Arena since few days. Every time I try to play it shows unable to connect. Please check your connection. I've changed my server too but the error remains same.

I just love this game.But the inly thing I don't like in the game is it use to draw my coin too fast.But the game is really good I am not discouraging people that want to download the game but for me it use to draw my coins that is for me
Good except for the fact that i didnt like the challenge part of 100th round shooting then if you hit the red skull you loose every thing you suffered for thats bad.....

The games are fun but the amount of advertising is overwhelming. A mission may last 10 to 15 seconds but at the end of every mission there is a minimum of 30 seconds of advertising. Fix the over advertising and the game will rate a 5 star.

After 3 years, CoVID and all the BS that engulfed the world I managed to find time and finish all cities and all missions . Everything is nice except the policy of your giving ads in between! Forcing 30 secs ads after every game is too much even when such ads don't give any benefit to the player! Decent game. The PVP matching needs to be fixed. Sometimes first place will have 20+ kills, while second place may have 5 kills. It's extremely difficult to win any prizes in the shooting range challenge, without spending diamonds. Pretty much seems to be your average pay to win game.

Basic game. Not bad. But as with all alot of these types of games you can see that there will be money required soon and you can expect that you will not go far without spending some real coin. I'll play occasionally till I see there is no moving on then delete the app. Ok way to pass a few minutes every now and then.

This is a decent game but its most attractive in-game - the player vs player battle is ruined by the matching logic. 8 players battle it out in a fight of skill and also based on their defence and attack points. One would think that players having these points in some approximation would be pitted against each other to make it fair. But they are made to play in some random order it seems. A player with defence point of 10k is sent into a match with 7 other players having an attack of 16k. It takes 1 shot and then you are sent into a 8 second wait to respawn and be shot again. At the same time these higher rated players have a defence of 60k while your attack is 6k so you need 10 shots to down 1 player, which i must add is impossible because each shot exposes your location. In my 3 years of playing and suffering, there was only a couple hours of pleasant playing when this matching algorithm worked as it should and players were stacked fairly. Please fix this!

Great graphics. Minimal lag. Easy controls. Fun (albeit slightly macabre) way to pass time. A few more ads than I would like, but they are not overwhelming. Only problem: a bit hard to progress past the first or second city. Special Ops requirements too strict, which makes it almost impossible to complete missions without spending money (both real and fake/in-game). Not fond of developers forcing payment. Other than that, awesome game. Lots of fun! 8.5/10, highly recommend!

This game is a great form of entertainment! It compares to watching TV, Playing sports, going to the movies, etc... Because it totally keeps your focus, it's exciting, thrilling and challenging everytime you play it, from start to finish. It keeps you busy enough that the time seems to zoom by so, you have to keep track of the time in order not to put too much of your daily routine schedule into it and try not to get hooked on it. The graphics are wonderful and it will keep your interest!!!

This game is awesome, but it gets 4 stars because I have one problem with it. You spend lots of coins and battle tokens to get your guns upgraded enough to pass levels. Once that level is passed, the gun you spent all that time upgrading is now obsolete, and you can't do anything with it. If the game would allow some type of sale for these useless guns, even for a fraction of the price, I would give it 5 stars.

I love the game. It's really fun to play. One thing I hate though is the energy. You shouldn't need energy to do missions. One suggestion I have is if you want to keep the energy, then make it so that playing wanted missions doesn't take energy. We play those for money for upgrades, and it's annoying when you use all your energy for money and can't play the primary mission you were originally getting money for.

Good game. Takes a long time to get any real good weapons or much else.... But you can. Just depends upon how much you're willing to spend, compared to time played. Paying will get you more, and quicker of course. However, you can get along fairly well without buying. I even had to make few Small purchases because the weapon and other items needed was inadequate for the levels as if my weapon was never gonna be upgraded quick enough to get past an area. Upgrades to arsenal are constantly needed

Great game throughout. Only complaint is the last part of the game begins to have continuing problems. You will not be able to hit other players in the sniper Arena but they can shoot you. Also the game will glitch and keep asking you if you would like to quit the match. Making it impossible to find other players. They will on the other hand find you and finish you off. 1 in 10 matches end because the game looses connection. Makes you üò† when it happens at the end of a match and you loose all your battle points. This doesn't happen through most of the game. Hopefully the will fix these bugs soon and add a new city. Still is a very good game. 8 out of 10.

I stopped playing for a bit, they disabled my account so I had to start a new one. Lost all my progress. Now I can't save my progress because it wants to save to my disabled account and merge the two. Other than that issue, I love this game and dig the accelerometer option which gives it a more realistic feel. I recommend it if you like the strictly sniper aspect of shooting games. The PvP is great too!

Has been mostly good. Lately, with their last update, I was cut off from playing on all of my devices. Updated, and restored progress, and now, some of the controls are lagging and direct hit shots are not being recognized. Not sure what happened with the previous update, though guessing that they rewrote the operating code and are now trying to get it back in shape.

Love this game. You got to grind a bit to get more powerful weapons but it's worth it. The Online sniper game & zombie games are nice change of pace from the campaign. I have one problem though..I can no longer receive reward ads for some reason. There are loads of them in this game & I cannot aquire them. I press the button and nothing happens. I've restarted my phone, turned it off, I've cleared the cache & still nothing. I would like to get rewarded for my missions cause I'm losing out!! 5/5

This game is Awsome. However, it's sometimes difficult to find the target and before you can, they end up getting away. Also, the upgrades can be a little too expensive. Oh, and sometimes you end up shooting accidentally because the "shoot icon" is right underneath the the zoom slider. If you can place the "shoot icon" slightly towards the bottom center of the screen, that could help from accidentally shooting before wanting to. Thanks.

Very challenging and real to life situations. Graphics could be more detailed. Enjoy playing it a lot. Also can create better incentives and more opportunities to earn diamonds instead of having to buy them all of the time, as well as being able to finish at the top for World Ops because it seemsI'm always in the 450,000 place and it's not from lack of trying

Would rate the game 5 stars but a subscription based "premium" system is kinda dumb. Really wish a lot of the reward features weren't locked behind pay walls. I'd glady pay 2$ to 5$ for the game initially if I'd be able to unlock more as of result of playing versus paying. Upgrading is pretty time consuming otherwise. Time and "resting" periods of the game fair and add to the challenge. Its a pretty fun game overall. Would like to see more realistic guns and gun features. Great time killer.

Pretty fun and entertaining game overall, the only things that I think should be fixed is about every 2 challenges, you get some pretty long ads, and you run out of energy fairly quickly. I think I would enjoy it much more if there weren't as many ads and if you had a little more energy. Gameplay is great, controls are very easy to learn, and the graphics are pretty realistic! I definitely recommend if you like sniper games or would like a game to cure your boredom.

No matter how many diamonds you have, it isn't enough for the specials. Sometimes the graphics is off. Sometimes a zombie is near a wall and the bullet splatters as if it hit the wall instead. Sometimes you get a kill when it was a near miss. Sometimes a kill shows as a miss. Overall, it is a fun game. I do not like being nickeled and dimed. This game does that.

It's a fun game that is exactly what I expected. Perform hits, gain currency, upgrade your weapons, repeat. The shooting interface is a new challenge for me, but easy enough to figure out. It's a little heavy on the push for microtransactions for my taste. I know the developers are in this to make some money, and the game is worth a few bucks. But the ongoing pestering is a bit trying.

Since I have a Chromebook I'm always looking for games that are laptop friendly. It's not great to start with but once you grow the stability on your weapon it's not too bad. I've never really liked games where you have to buy a VIP membership or a bunch of add on's but even though this game is full of add on's you can still progress without them.

Nice shooter with great graphics and sound. Challenge is just right and the multiplayer is nicely done. I only have 1 issue. The placement of the fire button. I OFTEN hit the fire button with the fleshy part of my thumb while I am zooming in or out. Could you please add an option to change the layout? I gave 4 stars because of poor placement.

Just started..I like it so far, I have made it thru all cities without spending real money, waiting on more to come. The arena part has to many hackers that cause you to lose a lot of trophies. Wish something could be done about that ! There is another game called(Sniper Master)that seems to have copied this game. To many similarities with missions and everything. But its downfalyou can max out a gun and still can't finish a city and it freezes up in the arena part with 1 second till respawning.

You know it takes longer to watch the commercials than to just restart the game? If you're playing outside of airplane mode just restart and save yourselves some seconds. Always start outside of airplane mode. Then when your energy is loaded and you've completed the challenge, switch to airplane mode and skip the commercials. I know, "the commercials are what keep the game free for the most part". Come on, let's be honest, it's not really good enough to pay for in the first place.

Overall it's a pretty decent game. You can easily advance through the game without spending any real money. I made it really far in and only stopped because after awhile the energy system in any game gets annoying. The pvp is fun but it randomly places you on the map and some spots are right next to another enemy or out in the open and you get killed the second you spawn. Other than that I really enjoyed this game and I'll probably redownload it in the future to play again

This app is really good so far. Its really addicting and fun! However i do wish there was maybe a moving option. For an example, Say you have to take out two assets without being seen. And you were able to move to hide behind the corner of a building. Lets face it, A sniper cant do their job if their sitting ducks on a ledge. But other then that little suggestion, Its a great game!

This game is very fun and challenging enough to keep you playing. I do have a suggestion for the developers, it would be really awesome to be able to sell back the guns and upgrades that were purchased and used in the earlier missions. Once you move forward into the game you never need the earlier weapons used and could use the coins to help upgrade the next guns. This would be a great feature and would make the game worth 5 stars.

Lots of fun, but buggy, especially during PvP. The "sonar" will show a target as being close when it's actually behind a building or obstacle. Often you can see your shots hitting an opponent, but they will not register - very frustrating. During world ops when shooting the city scene, enemies will sometimes be shooting at you from behind and through a building. While you can't hit them, they will eventually kill you. The controls can be a little sensitive. We are waiting for the next city.

Awesome game and it's very addictive. It's a little slow to get going at first but after a few cities in it starts picking up and opens up several additional features. Love this game but I'd say the only issue alive come across is that recently I've been having issues with arena challenge. Occasionally when I win a round app forces closed and Says I lost and wants me to buy back in which I feel is mandatory as I've usually acquired a huge surplus of accumulated prizes that I dont wish to forfeit

Great game but... it seems nearly impossible to report a bug in the game. The only option is to select a pre-provided problem and check the box without a category for "other". Obviously they don't care enough to fix a level where an enemy is shot it is considered an "innocent", making it impossible to pass to the next level. I give the game 5 stars, but I give the game 1 star for their player support. You have a great game... so stop sucking already!

The sights sway alot ! I'm using a mouse only, because I don't like using a keyboard and a mouse, I'm not ambidextrous ! So you have to line up your sights and hurry and click on fire before your aim drifts to far off the target, which isn't always easy ! If I had a controller, and I knew how to link it to the game, it would probably help with the time it takes from moving from aiming to firing ! Other than that, I like it ! I recommend it, but I've only be playing approximately for 10 minutes

Decent graphics, solid physics and campaign gameplay is progressively challenging. EDITing my whole review a 3rd time bc these guys really stepped up! There was a lot of issues before and I took a break from the game. 6 months later, tried again and every issue is resolved!! Recoverd my progress perfectly, pvp is better and connection and loading issues are gone. Back to loving this game! Good job guys! Minus 1 star bc 'premium' is extremly costly. I will never pay that much for a phone game.

It's a fun game. It ties in some fun factors into the games and has other cool stuff to do other than just the main story. Though, the game is pretty much pay to win. From premium getting you new guns that are way beyond the starting level (which I'd understand for a free to play) to having to spend 500 diamonds (basically the only way to earn them is to either rank up which stops after a while, whatcha million adds that don't always load, or buy them.) It leaves beating the levels unsatisfying

The English in the description is overly cheesy sounding, like they tried too hard to sell the amazingness of their game. As for the game itself, the player models could use some refining, as could the animations for both your character and the hostiles/hostages and such. Also, I believe this is related to my phone (LG Stylo 4), but the loading times are astronomical compared to Contract Killer: Sniper. Very enjoyable game nonetheless üëå Keep working on the game though üôÇ

Fun, simple game with some pretty damn awesome graphics. Lots and lots of in app purchases and many requests and suggestions to make purchases. I could see where people could very easily accidentally tap on one of those options. Kind of pushy about it. But the game play is cool.

This Sniper App was a real challenge to operate after the first two stationary targets, when a moving target came into play, It took me three tries to finally get the method of operating the Rifle to score a hit on the moving target, which not only moved backwards, forwards, and side to side. It took some skill to score a hit with the third target. I got stuck on the mandatory choosing of a more advanced and accurate firearm and when I did choose one, I still could not get back to the Game itself, as if I was stuck on picking the Rifle step and so my ability to rate the entire Game to Level 10 was not allowed. It seems to be an interesting challenge to someone who enjoys the use of Firearms which I certainly am a Fan of doing. I did appreciate the ratings that were given as to the Rifles offered as choices and it was a factor in the choice I made although I never got back into the Game itself after choosing the updated Rifle I ultimately chose.

great game fun and addicting. you don't have to buy anything to finish levels. you can just put in the work/ time and upgrade your weapon until it's good enough to finish the level. I would spend money to buy upgrades if they were cheaper. one game i played i ended up spending over 20 bucks because they just charged 1 dollar a time for upgrades but this game wants way to much at once so I never spend any money. 1 dollar from 100 people is better than 50 dollars from 1 person

Great game overall. The reason for 4 stars is that there are problems with pvp matchups. I am not a gamer. There was an interactive ad in my podcast app for this game. I tried it and got hooked. The missions gradually become more intriguing and complex. I am steadily progressing without making any purchases. Using the default sniper rifle and consistently upgrading it as I accumulate points. I play this several times everyday and I'm not bored yet.

Great graphics, and I enjoy the many different missions offered. Only issue , sometimes its hard to find the target in the allowed time, this should not be a timed game. When assassin's kill they take there time with no hurry so that the shot is perfect. This game gives you what 10 sec to find and kill target, don't like this aspect of the game at all!!

Dope sniping game. Easy to play, nice difficulty and all around enjoyable experience. Not too many ads either. The graphics are ok, they could be better but it's still passable. It doesnt take forever to upgrade your weapons either. Overall a fun game that's good for a quick pick up during your lunch break or something.

Very fun and challenging game, great for binge playing or just to pass the time. There were minor issues in the beginning but they seem to have figured most of it out although it does still have some minor glitches during gameplay that should be addressed, but almost all games are going to have that. Other than that great job on all other aspects, also I would highly recommend getting through most of the storyline or making a purchase before trying pvp, it's crazy hard without a powerful rifle.

This game is so awesome! Very fun and detailed missions & graphics. The controls are pretty easy to maneuver, to focus on, and kill the targets. If you don't have money to upgrade your weapons and energy, there are other ways of doing so, like watching videos or completing missions on other games, that you have to download. But in any case, Sniper 3D is a very fun and entertaining game to play! üëåüíØ

super addictive. get in with a squad as soon as its available. itll help a lot in progressing through the game. also start the free trial of the optional upgrade at the beginning of the game. you get a gun you can use for the first few cities and it helps a lot. just remember to cancel if you dont want it.

Bro, this is the best game I've ever played!! The graphics the controls even the missions they give you are awesome!!! But one thing though, whenever you hold the sniper it moves a little bit, kind of in a circular motion and it gives me a disadvantage to make a clean shot. But other than that, this is a really challenging and fun game!!!

There are many reasons why I absolutely love this game. it features a variety of weapons, including snipers, assault rifles, and more. Every weapon is fully upgradable, allowing you to improve scopes, magazines, stock, barrels, and more. Another reason why I love this game is because it features a variety over a hundred different missions that provide different challenges, such as stopping suicide bombers, eliminating targets, stopping illegal trades, neutralizing threats, and more.

Super fun & amazing graphics for using just a phone, never could have imagined this a decade ago that I'd be able to play a video game on my phone with better graphics than my old video game console!! I just wish 1 thing, that I would be able to get upgrades on rifles & packages without having to spend money! It takes a lot of time & missions in order to get enough coins/diamonds to get the really good weapons or even to make upgrades to your own weapon.... Please help me out with something!!

I've reached level 9 so far, and I have to say it has been a fun play so far. Have to go through the "Wanted" segment quite a lot to build up enough cash to upgrade my hunting rifle so I can progress, but better than spending real money. I like that you can play the majority of the game alone, not against other people early on. Need to improve some before trying that. So it's been a blast so far, and love the slow-mo on the kill shot. I'm looking forward to seeing how far I can go. Nice job!

Great game! Yes, it has ads, but they are placed apart enough so the flow of the game isn't too shaken up. Developers can't maintain a game for free, and they are not aggressive about selling you the ad-free version anyway. The animations are visually spectacular and gameplay is highly intuitive and forgiving. I love it.

Very fun game. Can advance in game (so far) without spending money. mission completion gives you coins to keep adding parts to your weapon. may have to make an in-app purchase later, but might be willing. Still in the early stages, but so far so good. Love the little plot lines for each mission.

It is a little slow at loading but overall a GREAT game!!! There are NO ADS!!! I love this game so much, it's got just the right amount of effects and the music gets you pumped up AND focused at the same time!! The ingame prices of weapons arent really cool because you dont get that much money on a mission unless you buy premium, but reaching the achievements are fun and the game is great.

Fun so far, but will have to see how weapon upgrades go without having to use real money. Just started and have been able to purchase a fair (tier 1) weapon and add a level 2 silencer. Graphics are good at highest level setting, and aim & zoom controls respond well allowing for pretty quick target acquisition, even with a rifle with only a 10% steadiness rating. It looks like better rifles have higher steadiness ratings.

I LOVE this game. Play it every night. I travel supporting our Service Members worldwide year long and this gives me down time between the craziness. I just would like to progress smoothly without spending so much. Seems unnecessarily greedy at times, especially when it feels like you're paying for your outlet. No Fair. Still enjoy it, but would love to see more perks for regular users.

Love this game! Great sniper sim! Like any game there are a few bugs from time to time (especially for android users) but the technical support staff do a good job of keeping the game running smoothly for the most part. Not a game for children, it's really violent and bloody but, for an adult it's all kinds of fun. Best of all it's free to play! There are in game purchases and people who invest real world money certainly have an advantage over FTP players but, not so much as to send the game out of balance like other mobile games do. There are ads but you have the option of skipping most and some offer rewards like gems or energy for watching. I highly recommend Sniper 3d.

for those that like sniper games, this one is lots of fun. Sure, the game keeps pushing for opportunities to sell upgrades, but I have been using it for a day and I have avoided spending. At most, I agreed for the Premium trial which I can cancel within 7 days.

This game used to be my favorite. It was well balanced and one could progress pretty well without paying to play. The past 3 updates though have chipped away at the free to play model and significantly reduced the notion that one can play an enjoyable game. The pvp is screwed up, and the side quest levels that one could play can't even be beaten on normal mode by high their players. If they straighten it back up, I could see myself enjoying it again. replyContent: Dear Archer, We are sorry to hear that you've been having a negative experience. I've passed on this feedback and we'll do our best to ensure you have a more enjoyable gaming experience. Thank you for your feedback.

content: I've spent a bunch of money on this game, but I've had the same Glory Skill Bug for over a year now. This is ridiculous. I've tried the restart game at wave 0, uninstall and reinstall, and clearing ram, and everything else. It has been another year. Updated the app, but I am still not getting my 1 free glory skill at the start of every run.
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: To get extra rewards they want you to purchase an Adv Battle Pass at $17 every 2 weeks, so $32 a month. As well as other purchases to give "a more enjoyable play experience". After 2 months you could buy Metroid Dread or Horizon Forbiden West which are far better games and they doesn't ask you to pay more and more and more. The new updates have pushed toward pay to win. content: Amazing game that is now unplayable. The core game play loop is awesome, it's kind of the Dark Souls of mobile. But the character effects and animations have been raised to sit above enemy animations and effects. This makes it impossible to track enemy movement at melee range or incoming projectiles. So you end up taking a lot of damage because the attacks are not appropriately telegraphed. If they can fix that alone, then the game would be 4 star. While I like to give the benefit of the doubt wherever possible, the cynical interpretation of this change in arranging character animations vs enemy animations is an attempt to drive ad revenue and microtransactions. I have no problem with the devs and publisher paying the bills, this is a really frustrating and annoying way to get that done. I prefer to give my time to companies who choose to pay their bills by pleasing their customers, rather than at the customer's expense. Getting that fifth star would be a matter of refining the character progression. They have introduced a lot of abilities that are not useful at all. That makes a very few of the abilities basically mandatory, and if those don't come up on the RNG, then you are basically guaranteed to lose the round. Additionally, there are abilities that are not explained well or even at all on the in-game interface. You have to to external sources to get an explanation.
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.
