content: The new update has made it clear the direction this game is moving towards pay to win. 2 of the new characters are only available through purchase and 1 through gems. It costs >$30 to unlock all of the characters, way too much for a mobile game. Additional ad options during the game ruin the experience. The player is basically obligated to watch an ad to gain a sought after powerup. I played this game daily for a couple months and it has gotten to the point where progression seems unachievable.

This was almost a fun game, with a bunch of small annoyances that got in the way, until world 3. This world perfectly brought out every single shortcoming of this game. It is almost a masterpiece how quickly I went from enjoying a slightly original and challenging game, to complete loathing. The lack of choice and control that were once quirky obstacles become sheer, impassable walls to gameplay, and every time you fail this world (as quickly as a minute) you must wait an HOUR to try again.

Game is becoming more grindy with each patch. Loot is entirely random and it is impossible to target specific items, even when spending money. Item pool is more diluted with each patch and you can use only one item in each slot. New heroes are added often and while they do give some passive bonuses, they are mostly useless. Feels like the game is moving in 'idle hero game' direction and not in a good way. New stages feel same as old ones with only increased difficulty and maybe new enemy type.

Scales to hard way too fast. It's fun at first when you can actually make progress, but it turns into a pay to play game very quickly, otherwise it requires hours of grinding to get enough money and experience to progress. But you can't even do that because you only have enough energy for 4 runs before you have to wait an ungodly amount of time for your energy to refill. This game is a one pump chump. You get one little burst of fun and then it's over.

Would be a great game if the aiming system was not down right awful. Either you start shooting at an enemy behind a wall that you CAN'T hit instead of the enemy right next to you that you CAN hit or your character completely refuses to finish off an enemy unit before moving on to a new one. Like I said, it would be a great game but because one of the key components is utterly HORRIBLE it only makes you frustrated.

Good game but the only thing I hate is when you die you have to start all over from the beginning. The game is great but all it needs is little less enemies because it makes it impossible when your 240 hp and you have 8 enemies on you that does 140 damage.

content: It was a fun concept at first, but then the way you move I found is absolute garbage, to where it is stuck at a speed so you can't slowly guide yourself around the spikes. Second, and my biggest problem with the game, is the difficulty. It gets really, really difficult really, really fast. The first monsters you encounter somehow track where you are going before you get there, and since the movement is terrible you can't get out of the way, along with flying monsters. This game needs a balance.

The idea is great. Move, shoot, and don't get shot. But, it is so difficult to progress that it quickly loses its entertainment value and becomes frustrating. Game developers have to make money, and I am willing to spend if its worthwhile. You would have to spend hundreds of real dollars to notice any improvement. The level of difficulty increases nearly as fast as your armor and weapons. And I don't mean new levels - the first levels you already finished get harder. No thanks.

Starts off strong, then the spike comes. After you progress a ways into the game, the difficulty spike hits like a ton of bricks. Its not that the tactics or the enemies change all that much, but the damage values sure do. It really was fun to learn the unique enemies and how to avoid them, but after a while it turns into you running from a group of enemies and stopping to fire every few feet for quite a long time before finally moving on or getting hit and losing. Worth a look, but it gets old.

content: it's kinda fun to play. it starts out pretty fun to play, but each stage becomes exponentially more difficult. it's not even just a matter of leveling up more to make the stages more survivable. there's new iterations of the enemies that become so much more difficult to defeat that the game really becomes too difficult to enjoy playing very very quickly.

Such a great game, and incredibly addictive! HUGE PROBLEMS THOUGH!! They make the game so insanely difficult after the first few levels it's just stupid! You literally have to play the same level over and over again about 1000 times before your character gets stronger to even have a chance to pass the level. Need to have a much higher drop rate of items, and not have every new level be basically impossible unless you spend 10 million dollars on upgrades.

content: Looks great, had so much potential. The leveling system is robust but feels like it has little impact in game, especially with the infrequent loot drops. The two biggest complaints are the lack of i-frames after getting hit. You'll get stuck in a corner and get melted. Worse yet is the lack of damage indication. If focusing on enemies you won't know you're taking damage other than you health bar that gets lost in everything going on on screen.

content: It's super easy but occasionally just downright unfair. The abilities' descriptions aren't revealed until after you've chosen one. Enemy descriptions are also up to trial and error, and when you're playing a game where you get one life before starting back at level 1, it can be pretty annoying to find out the hard way that orange skeleton heads split into two white ones upon defeat.

Great game. At one point I had uninstalled the game. When I reinstalled it I had lost all my progress. Not a big deal, but as soon as I find a piece of equipment or beat the first map, then I get a network error and can no longer play without uninstalling and reinstalling and starting over. I have sent support tickets several times with no response back.

content: This game was fun at first but quickly became boring and repetitive after Chapter 3. You die pretty fast and have to rely on certain skills to get past a certain stage. It's not as addicting as I thought it would be. Cool game but short-lived. Increasing equipment drops, decreasing ad time, and decreasing enemy damage output would all be helpful in keeping the player enticed.
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: I would give it more stars, probably 4 because the game in all honesty is really fun! The grind can be annoying and the energy system is not balanced at all (to long of a wait). All that aside, the 2 stars comes from lack of playability. It becomes far too hard to even bother. Also the one thing I hate is that it still takes energy to play previous levels. Instead of hindering us from playing your game let us play previous levels with no energy cost or at least just 2 energy or something!

While the game play is good to begin with, as you progress forward there is to much going on in the levels. It gets to the point where the game starts to lag, the cursor will either not register movement at all or stop working at random intervals. As I said in the beginning it's worth playing. Just don't waste any money on it. Wish I could post pictures to show what you end up against in later levels

This game is fun and addicting, however, a problem just occurred while I was playing. I completed a run of one of the events and got some loot, but when I went to the equipment page to fuse items, the game gave me an error saying "Be sure not to use third party apps, or you may be banned" or something like that. I don't have anything like that on my phone, yet once that error popped up, everything from that last event run was deleted from my account, including the items, scrolls, and tokens.
replyContent: We have completed the repair, please restart into the game to see if it has been restored, if it still prompts an exception, please try to uninstall and reinstall

content: Like any other pay to win games. First few levels were really enjoyable and fun, but then the grind is just too much. Also the RNG is really bad on this game too. There is no personalized build, everytime you level up you get a choice of 3 randomized skills in the game and hope that you get the one you need or want. There are times where you can get amazing perks and can clear a room in no time at all, and then there are time where the perks you get are so trash that you die in first room.
replyContent: Hello, the game can be strengthened by accumulating equipment and upgrading talents. If you feel that the level behind it is too difficult, you can play the previous level and make yourself stronger! Then challenge the level behind!~!

content: The joystick shifts whenever your finger lands in a different spot, and while this isn't bad in concept, I often found that it would simply lose accurate tracking when shifting around so much because you're required to stop and start repeatedly to attack. An option to have a fixed stick would be appreciated. Plus, there is no music past the main menu, and more often than not I found that sound effects will simply refuse to play, most notably the sound of you taking damage.

A fun Rogue-like shooter with creative enemies, upgrades and upgradable items. But the randomness of the upgrades when leveling up, both in the overworld and during the levels, and the ever expanding amount of upgrades in level can be very frustrating if you don't get any you like. Also, not being able to level up your character unless you reach a certain rank is annoying because your forced to play the same levels over and over until it gets higher.
replyContent: Hi, Sorry for the bad gaming experience,I will feedback our team,Please look forward to our new version.

content: If i had reviewed this game earlier it would be 4 stars. The reason its all the way down at 2 stars is because i reached stage 3 without spending money. The game is challenging, a little grindy when you get bad abilities several times in a row, but still a fun experience that makes you think quickly. The issue is, as soon as you reach stage 3, the game shifts. The combat in each chapter becomes much longer and it turns into a bullet-hell, and the way forward becomes money, not skill.

Cool graphics and the play is good but it was fun while it lasted. The difficulty level is insane to the point that you can only advance is by paying to play. You take 75% by and give 15% damage to enemies. Also, very minimal when upgrading your character, and weapons. Nothing to see here. Just another set of greedy developers creating a game trying to get rich! Uninstalling!

It is alright. the energy used to play and the amount you actually have in total it's really low. you only get about 4 games at a time before you are completely out of energy. It does not seem like they provide upgrades to those types of things either in order to increase how much total energy we have. Upgrades are randomized which is strange and incredibly slow to manage. Combine those two things and it is a slow grind fest to actually get anywhere in the game. The game is definitly pay to enjo

Update: eh, uninstalled it. The constant grinding doesn't seem to pay off well... If you don't mind it, this is still a good game. ===== Great game. I like the graphic. It's the most polished I've played so far for similar games with the same style. One thing that I don't like is the wheel of Fortune thing after you kill a boss. If we could disable the animation, that'd be great. Just wasting a few seconds every time you run that wheel.

content: Its an interesting game, the only issue I have, is that the textures and boundaries do not match up, so you get some places you can't get to, or enemies you can't get to because they are behind a way and there is an invisble wall blocking you from getting to them. So, in my opinion, it could be much better in that case, if that is fixed, 5 stars all around, but until then.

This is what makes it a grind. I have to play the same level over and over after beating it in order to be strong enough to take on the next one. content: Fun for a bit. As you progress further it seems to take longer and longer to progress through new zones. The enemies in new zones are about as challenging as they were in the previous, but the "challenging" part becomes the increased health and attack of enemies. This really makes for a lackluster experience. As an aside, the new season pass is definitely overpriced for most players, unless you play this beyond a casual amount.

It's a fun game, and fairly challenging after the first world (in a good way), but if you came to this game based on any of the advertisements, I'm sorry to say but Archero doesn't do any of it. You won't be building, clearing hundreds of enemies in waves shooting dozens of arrows at once, none of those advertised modes. It's really disappointing, since it sure looks like they have the capacity TO add those things. So it's good, but not great, and not what was supposedly promised.

This game is really fun, but after the first 2 worlds, the game becomes such a bullet hell with insane amounts of damage that you either have to get lucky with certain upgrades, or just continue to grind/pay for better gear. It just feels like the difficulty curve as you progress isn't so much a curve, as it is a brick wall.

Archero is a decent game. It runs smoothly and has pretty good graphics. But it's just another mobile game that either requires a sizable wallet, endless grinding, or strong ad watching endurance to progress. Additionally, they use an energy system that allows you to play about 4-5 times before having to wait until it recharges. (Or you can pay, of course). This is supposed to be "developed further", but I certainly doubt it. TL;DR Need to watch ads or pay to progress efficiently.
replyContent: Appreciate your attention to Archero, and the energy system would be continually optimized in the future: ) Thanks, have a nice day!

content: The gameplay itself is quite fun, but the game really suffers from how money grubbing it is to actually play it. Everything is horribly expensive, $20 for certain characters and even for a single outfit! If you try to play for free, the grind is super slow to get new equipment and heroes, which really pushes you to watch ads to keep moving around. And boy are there a lot of ads! You can easily end up watching an ad per minute, and more at times.
replyContent: Watching ads has chance to get coins, items, gems, skills or revives in the game. You don't have to see the ads if you don't want to. Thanks for your support.

content: Fun for a bit but you don't get many drops for weapons at all. I've put in quite a few hours and the difficulty changes. Sometimes I can make it to level 39, then only level 7 then 12 then 4 its like the more buffed up you are, the harder the enemies hit so it doesn't get easier and starts to get boring after putting in so many hours and you can't upgrade. I'd also recommend lowering the damage on the bullet seed guys that can shoot over walls. They hit for 400+ and I'm at 1800+ health.

content: The dev's have made the game unattractive with the recent updates. You're now needing certain abilities to be successful in later stages. content: Game is redundant and boring after a while. The first couple stages are interesting, but it gets to a point where it will take way too much time to level-up without paying. Equipment and upgrades are all up to the roll of the dice, so whether you can beat the level has a high chance being determined by what you roll at the beginning.

While fun, it becomes basically impossible. You begin to just not deal enough damage while the game throws tons of enemies with many projectiles at you. It becomes a bullet heck game and those are played twin-stick, but to shoot in this game, you need to hold still. Then, once you die you can choose to restart, or spend a rare in game currency, (which coincidentally you can pay for). Overall, I think the game would be better if the shooting mechanics were improved, and it wasnt impossible to see

It's an okay game. I've been playing since it was called archer.io and it's gotten better. It's a good time killer but the games get too frustrating. You randomly get crappy abilities that don't make it fun. You hit like a child while the enemies scale way too high and fast. Getting the gold tier items is almost impossible if you don't want $49 to be able to get 10 obsidian chests. All in all its a pay to win game but not the worst one.

content: the game is very fun, however theres quite a few things that just dont make sense. Why is there an energy system? That's so played out at this point, and in a game like this it doesnt make sense. There definitely should not be an energy system. second, sometimes the levels right off the bat are pretty challenging, which again plays into the energy system. when you make a game, where alls you do is grind, why the hell would you put in an energy system?! Please remove the energy system...

Fine concept, pretty terrible execution. Success is 80% luck- based, and the energy system is a bad joke. Level layouts, enemies, and skills are random-ish, so often you'll find yourself in impossible situations. im fine with a luck element, but this game goes too far. Starting at lv5, the enemies' damage becomes absolutely insane, in no way pacing the progression of the player's health pool. Overall a strong concept but just needs some number tweaking and the energy system has to go.

content: Only issue is the energy system. takes too long to get back in the game. maybe increase the Energy cap ( not sure if that's a thing already but im still at 20 energy ) or decrease / remove the wait time for the energy. this game has alot of potential and needs grinding to get better gear, but it comes to a halt when there is no energy. (edit) another issue is the lack of heart drops, i find myself always low on health due to so many enemy projectile flying randomly with no warning.

It's a really pleasant game. No annoying ads and no banners that keep saying rate me. It's gameplay is easy to understand and difficult enough to keep me playing. Graphics are good. All around, it's just an enjoyable game. It does need an update on the energy system. It adds nothing to the game and it's incredibly annoying. I'll do runs on lower levels because they last longer than the level I'm currently on. Update: Became a cash grab. Don't bother.

Its a fun game and the grind is real, but there is a huge issue with the ads and draws. Sometimes you can watch an ad and not get anything at all for your bonus or draws. Another issue is, sometimes the draw button get stuck as a free draw and you have to watch an ad and it costs gems and then doesn't give you the item you drew. So you end up watching an ad and using gems with nothing in return. 2/5 stars for that.

Perfect mechanics for a great game. Too bad its completely ruined by ramping up the difficulty quickly in order to force you to spend lots of money to keep completing levels. I've spend $15 and that turns out to be nothing close to getting me where I'll need to be to complete the game. No way to grind yourself to completion. Dont waste your time or money.

content: Challenging game, horrible bug! After finally beating the 7th level of all bosses (which took me 857 attempts) my game data is erased and it put me back at the start of the game... I invested tons of time and even some money into this game only to have it randomly reset itself. Tried reinstalling, it didn't fix the problem. I am thoroughly disappointed and looked forward to the levels after 7.

The game is fun, albeit repetitive. I like running levels hoping for the best upgrades to help me beat the final boss in each stage. However, my low rating goes directly to the support team and devs. Not only have players been staring at an outdated CHRISTMAS event (makes you all seem lazy) but a crash issue that's caused me to lose energy and rewards has gone unanswered twice over. Seems like the Gorilla Games has been riding the coattails of "innovative game of the year" and slacked off. Shame

Not only does this game have an extreme difficulty curve, but the game tends to make my phone lag intensely ironically when im doing good. The chance of getting to higher levels is based solely on getting lucky with your upgrades. The game itself is interesting and fun but you're only given four times to play at a time and there's honestly no point in trying to revive yourself cause the enemies start to hit much harder as the game goes on. This game is a play-to-win in disguise unfortunately. üò°

Not a bad game, but it needs more weapons/pets/equipment and maybe some sort of competitive game mode with other players. It is a little too grind heavy and some of the enemy attacks feel cheap as you can barely even see them to dodge. Edit: The new characters are a joke...the only decent ones require at least $10 real cash to purchase and their stats still aren't even as good as the original free character...greedy and disappointing.

The game likes to do this thing when you're fuzing item where it freezes and all you see is the furnace. Then the app closes or you have to restart it because you can't do anything. When you do this you lose all the items you tried to fuse. This doesn't seem like a big inconvenience until you're fuzing something into a perfect epic and it takes away all your epic items and doesn't give you a perfect epic. It's happened twice. Once when I was making a blue and then once while making a epic

This game has a great concept but it has become increasingly less fun to play as it is extremely pay-to-win, and even when you pay your chances of succeeding due to the roulette wheel of abilities are still nearly impossible. I've made it to stage 6 and had to play it over 250 times in a row to make it to the last boss, only to be killed immediately. Very disappointed in the need for gems to revive without losing progress. Very disappointed in the 4-try limit per full energy bar.

It's a relatively fun game, it gets really hard really quickly. The ads for this game are very misleading. So about the "5 new characters", you can get 1 new character through progressing, one you have to spend 50k coins (in game currency) which is just ludicrous, another one you can spend gems on which you can get for free but I think it would take forever to buy it, and the last 1 you have to spend real dollars on. And the only girl is $17... Seriously?!

Honestly, I got this just to see why it was recommended to me, and after playing it, I can see that they must have paid a fair bit to shove it into the feeds. It's easy to progress at the start, but being a roguelite, you can't always be confident in your runs. Servers are unreliable, the ui glitched a few times for me, the randomness of the stat upgrades is annoying, the gear stats are shallow, and there's no clear way to gain new characters or outfits. Passes time, kills the battery.

Iv played this game for a long time. With all the new stages added in it's become increasingly difficult to grind for better gear. The best place so far is I think the third stage were the enemies spawn in waves. Tldr; only one suitable loot farm and it's still bad. The battle pass is terrible. The character and gear system needs rebalancing (some characters & weapons take way to long to get or make others extremely weak in comparison).

content: I can see why this would get praise, its a great concept in a fun package. However, it is marred by the foul touch of greed right before the game can get to the point where i would call it good. The enemies, abilities, and weapon variety are all great but just the terrible way that progression is dealt with keeps this from being anything other than a grind fest with an energy bar. Maybe without the energy limit and the only guaranteed way to get weapons and items was through the loot boxes

I really wanted to rate this game higher, since I've had fun with it in the past. What has really ruined the game for me is the ridiculous scaling in difficulty of the daily challenges, and the inexplicable varying degrees of difficulty between chapters. There really should be more variety in the daily challenges as well, it's boring. Chapter progression in 13 and 14 have made the game frustrating. The only way to progress is to get the correct abilities, which happens far too infrequently.

Fun game and mechanics. Later stages can become a bit difficult with rng and artificial difficulty begining to weigh in a bit too much on whether or not you can pass a course. Ad's become a bit more aggressive as well due to the additional difficulty and need for extra life and/or power up at the cost of watching an ad. This is the nature of mobile games now-a-days though unfortunately.

Cool idea. Awful execution. The character auto-shoots, which is smart for a mobile game, doesn't do so while moving, which is fair, but there isn't any aiming. The character doesn't lead shots even when necessary to hit, and even when using bounce shot, doesn't bounce shots around corners. Additionally the energy system makes this game virtually unplayable without paying vast sums of money. A cool concept turned into a soulless cash grab, would love to see someone else remake the game entirely

content: Honestly I loved the game at first. But I soon realized how flawed it really is. To get past the first stage you must beat all 50 levels in one go. You can revive yourself but only once. It can get incredibly difficult and after a week of playing the game I can say it is no longer fun. I have made it to level 41 but got stuck. They surrounded me and unless you managed to choose all the right skills, you lose. It seemed so fun but its simply horrible. Don't download it. It is a waste of time.

The gameplay itself is entertaining and provides a good level of challenge. The biggest issue I have had with the game is that there are a ton of ads and nudges for microtransactions in the levels and while you are spec-ing your character. I have also had problems with not recieving items that I was supposed to have earned, like the daily login rewards, or the patrol rewards, just not showing up. Its not a bad game, it just isn't very focused on providing the best experience for the player.

It's a fun game but some things are programmed to be intentionally obnoxious. In lost castle, there are enemies that throw red boomerang scythes are you, they are basically impossible to see due to how many particle effects are on screen. In response to the dev, it's not about "not being good enough". It's, "you've programed a projectile to be almost impossible to see due to how it's colored". I have mostly high level purple and blue equipment, I 2 shot anything. Your programming is bollucks.

content: This is such a fun game to play on your spare time, but when i play it there are invisible walls and I can walk right through water and walls. There is also a glitch causing me to not be able to use the whole area, instead i am only able to go out of the playing field behind my charater. This causes some levels to be physically impossible to get passed, which is extremely disapointing when you get to level 46 and you have no choice but to die.

I love the game, but it's a bummer you can't go back to past levels. Once you've beaten stages 1 and 2, you get to stage 3 which is a dungeon. It spawns up to 4-5 new enemies every 15ish sec and keeps going for five rounds with or both out killing previous enemies. It caps you at levels for gaining new starting options and that really affects the gameplay when you cant go back to previous levels for more xp. I love the concept but it needs a lot of work to make it worth playing and paying.

the two stars are for the fact that the first two levels are actually enjoyable. however, past that it comes a slow and unbearable pace of using a ridiculous amount of energy just for one go then waiting nearly an hour to give it another go. thats ludicrous. if you decide to download it youll enjoy the first couple days but then you will realize how agonizing it is to slog through the rest of the game when you have to repeat the same level over the course of days.
replyContent: Appreciate your attention to Archero, and the energy system would be continually optimized in the future: ) Thanks, have a nice day!

content: i didnt have a problem with the game until i started hitting the later chapters. leveling up and upgrading weapons is way too tedious and has very little effect. the most frustrating feature is if the enimies are moving my guy just shoots behind them without hitting them. overall this game is addictive but would be amazing with a couple of fundamental changes.

The game is fun but you do end up hitting a wall. The monsters get very difficult with ridiculous health and damage past island 4. This type of difficulty feels very artificial, it has unique monsters in each stage, they need to rebalance the game difficulty. As it stands you need very specific perks to win, ricochet, bounce, etc. My final problem with the game is the progression system is all dependent RNG this is fine for the perks as it's like a rogue game, but not okay for loot and skills.

Update: After tacking in some more purchase options, the developers have continued to fail to listen to any feedback. The game is fun in theory, but there's so many bad design choices. Enemy health pools growing raise the time to kill to unmanageable levels, rather than focusing on good enemy and level layouts to challenge the player. Item drops are too rare, and the murky visuals get you killed more often than any player error, especially with your own shots in the mix.

It's fun, but I feel the randomness of the abilities, especially at the beginning of a round is bad. Skills you randomly get can make or break a run. Should be a talent system instead of random.
