content: Re-rating this app from a previous review, the game itself is very fun but very repetitive, and it's really hard to progress when you only have 20 energy. *It takes 5 energy to enter the game* And each single energy takes 12 minutes to come back. So it takes an hour to get one try??? That's a very long time to wait. And gear doesn't drop often enough. Those are the two big problems I have with this game. Other than those, it's pretty fun. Please reduce the energy timer.

The game is loads of fun and surprisingly challenging. The only issue is the energy system. It needs to be removed/revamped. Having to wait an hour just to attempt to grind more coins/items in order to play at the current level is annoying and pointless. Given how much fun this game is I would gladly pay a $5 fee to remove the energy system. Also increasing item drop rate (not scrolls) would be smart to keep interest in the game otherwise it takes to long to advance.

Like the game. Very entertaining. I've read some other comments that the game is difficult or that you have to hit the monsters so many times to kill them. It's a game and is supposed to be hard as you progress. I love challenges and this one is a good one. Although, 2 things... you only get one chance for reviving, which it sucks big time. You get 20energy but can only play 4 times !?!?
replyContent: Appreciate your attention to Archero, and the energy system would be continually optimized in the future: )

content: Really fun and addicting game but i am really bothered by the fact that even after buying the $7 intro pack, (which I only bought after playing 20 hours in the game) I still have to watch a full 30 second ad every 5 levels. Which equates to a 30 second ad every 2-3 minutes of play. It really pulls me out of the game. I understand that there is a reward for it in most cases, but you cant just skip the reward and go on... it's watch the video for a reward, or watch a video for no reward. sucky biz

The game is awesome, i put it down for a couple of months, and when i came back to it, it was even more fun than i remembered. My review is 3 stars because of a major bug in the multiplayer portion that renders it useless. Whenever i try to create, or join a match, it loads, but stays at title screen. Then when i click tap on a single player game mode, it displays a white screen with "waiting for other player" and therefore stopping me from joining the single player game.

Fun enough game for the first level. Every level after is just too difficult. The villians are able to move and shoot much too quickly; their powers grow rapidly and exponentially with each level. While the player is stuck with the same choosing power as the very first level. You can have good runs, but its nearly impossible to have a good run and get the powerups needed to pass the level. Overall, the first level made the game worth downloading, but the following levels makes me want to delete.

Like a lot of others have said. It's fun for awhile but at a certain point takes way to long to beat a level. Especially when you can't pick your own weapons. At level 7 you rarely get an option to pick one of the better abilities. An option to watch a video for a re-spin would be nice. Also, It sounds counterintuitive, but being able to REJECT a prize you win on the wheel. Coins need to be collected right away, there's way too much going on sometimes

Very enjoyable experience. Challenging, and cool concept. Update: after being stuck on the same levels for 1.5 months, my review changed. It used to be challenging, while still able to progress. But now it feels like I'm grinding just for the sake of grinding. There needs to be some give somewhere. It takes way too long to level up items and character, even when that is done, the difference it makes is so minimal that it doesn't really matter, much more to say, but I'm out of characters...

The game is really fun. But I kinda feel like I've hit a point where if I don't pay money into this game that I cannot progress. I'm stuck on the 4th area and just can't get passed it. Been stuck on it for almost a week. Plus there are a lot of crashes that seem to waste my energy and kill runs. Making it more difficult to complete. Plus it seems like all drops are at a common level which makes them useless and the infrequency of the drops makes it impossible to forge them into better items.

I played it since it was not developed so much up until now (96% percentile). I have all my gears to epic, and was really excited to see what effect the perfect epic will bring, since they are three times as hard to get. Turns out nothing. They have no new effect. Some skills are not scaled well, so they are useless if you're in high level. One of the melee monsters that teleport was set to land right where you are so dodging is not fun. Ads are 1 min long, very annoying. So I uninstalled.

I'm many hours into this game and I really enjoy playing it. I've never been interested in a game like this before but I've been playing for weeks. It's well polished and easy to control. I do have a few suggestions that would improve my experience. I'd like it if the energy limit or regen time could be improved. Waiting an hour to play another round after only 4 attempts is a bit much. I'd like there to be more to do with equipment and upgrades, and picking buffs rather thsn relying on luck.

First of all, I downloaded this game after seeing an ad for it only to discover the gameplay in the ad was nowhere to be found. Despite that, it's a pretty fun game to pick up and pay for a couple minutes at a time. Unfortunately, it's mired by a strange ad system that either doesn't work or freezes and makes you lose progress. Would have been a 5 star game without the false advertising and buggy ad system.

Game is fun to play. It's challenging yet great fun. The issue I have with it is whenever it tries syncing it renders all control useless. It's an annoying issue that I have experienced multiple times. Another issue is, if you're stuck syncing and you get out of the program and restart it, all your previous progress you just accomplished is lost and that is super annoying. All in all great game but annoying sync issue. I hope it gets fixed.

I liked the game overall. However: The sound effects range from "tolerable" to "obnoxious," but turning them off is disadvantageous. The joystick is buggy; sometimes, when trying to move in a direction, the character just stops or goes in the opposite direction. (I know it's not my phone because ones from other games work fine.) The skills and items acquired are basically entirely RNG based. The gameplay is very repetitive.
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: The game is super fun at first, when you can actually complete levels. Eventually, it gets to a point that no matter what gear you have, no matter what random skill you get, it's nearly impossible to progress. Also, it's hard to keep trying when it takes so long to recharge energy. I loved this game at first, so I hope there will be updates that improve your gear to actually matter.
replyContent: Hello, can you introduce more information? Please send your game ID and screenshots to archero@habby.fun. Thank you for your feedback. After receiving the email, the team will respond to the reply in time and wish you a happy game.

content: great concept and fun game however. 1. The plant guys that shoot the red beads need a nerf, they can lob things over the entire map but you can still run into them while they are flying making it almost impossible to dodge if there are alot of them. 2. there are way to many things on the screen at once. Its extremely difficult to determine what is your projectiles or the enemy's. so you get hit without even seeing the projectile. 3. the energy system is stupid, it's like you dont want me to play

It's a really fun game. But crashes are pretty consistent and you'll lose progress or items. Another drawback is the way the sales are set up. You want to spend money to get better but you can't spend it on items or upgrades and the amount they offer for what they charge doesn't add value to your game. It would probably make a lot more money if there were other types of items to purchase, different value put on the current items, and/or ways to earn using an offer wall.

Played for a couple months, game is pretty fun. More about learning the enemy moves than anything. First few stages were pretty easy, then took a couple days to beat the next, as well as the 3 hardmode, couple weeks to beat the next, and now I've been on chapter 7 for almost a month. Whether you know the enemies or not, the randomness in skills and enemies sucks. Doesnt matter how much you upgrade equipment, it's like enemies scale on percentage, so you never get ahead. Starting to feel P2W.

The game is decent, but the game mechanisms & rewards are frustrating. The nozzle causes a delay in movement. The amount of coins made per gameplay slowly adds to upgrade a skill & it's random. Getting 640 points only gives you 64 coins. The enemies are a bit too stronger than the archer. The little upgrade choices doesn't give a description of how it could help until you pick it. It's kind of easy to level up. I don't like that the character can only shoot when not moving. Archery is on point.

I had to post a comment instead of going through the feedback option because it wouldn't allow me to submit it. When there are a certain amount of enemies on the screen, the spirits stop working properly. They stop targeting the enemies and just spin in a circle. They continue to spin until there is only one enemy on the screen and sometimes they don't stop spinning until all enemies are gone. This makes them completely useless when they are most needed.
replyContent: HiÔºÅSorry for the bad gaming experience, I can't imagine the trouble you have encountered....Can you tell our more details or send an Email to Archero@habby.fun.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: The concept is fun, but it lacks spice and the controls are badly made, or rather "control" cuz there is only a joystick. This game would do good with character customization, battle music, actual enemy variety (seriously most just shoot projectiles), and some way to make it less repetive, like mayne challenges that give more rewards. At the moment, this game is very bare bones, but it can improve, and I believe it can improve if the dev(s) care enough about it.

As someone who really enjoys rouge-like mechanics, I found this really fun at first. However, once I got past level 20, it really felt like more of a chore to keep making progress and it only gets slower. I felt like there was very little reward for my efforts once I hit level 20, especially because xp is not based on how far you make it through a dungeon. It's more like a set value. Super slow gear grinding makes it hard to keep going too. Might check back in when it's gotten some updates.

I'm impressed. I'm always looking for good, one handed, portrait view games. And this game is definitely one of the better. The gameplay is nice, with good difficulty ramping, and I love the upgrade system. However, I'm tired of games that require "energy" to play a round. It makes them terrible time killers, and this is one of them. You have 4 games worth of energy and it takes an hour to recharge 1 game worth.. Would be 5 stars otherwise

Updated (again): It drops frames like crazy and you'll die without even seeing what happened. The game just adds more enemies shooting more projectiles until you can't dodge anything so you have to grind or pay to tank damage. Once you hit a point where it's too difficult to beat without grinding or paying money, just uninstall. The game doesn't get more fun. Even with updates, it's just the same thing over and over.
replyContent: Each of our updates is based on user feedback. The modification of the energy system is related to the game balance. We will try to introduce more reward mechanisms for energy. Thanks to every user who loves this game, so stay tuned!

content: This is a great game, but I feel the energy refills too slow for the amount required to enter any dungeon. Also, the fuse system either doesn't make sense (since there's no explanation) or it completely broken, apparently requiring three of the same item and filling all three slots (both of the input as well as putting the very first item in the output slot).

Mostly about survivability of the game; can we increase the currency just a little. It takes a bit long to earn enough to upgrade around upgrades 18. I think it ties into not having enough energy. maybe more energy would help so that we could play for longer and earn currency more often. Amazing game, one last thing though. A survival mode is needed, it would be pretty neat.

I don't normally click on ads that show up in other games, but I clicked on this one and I'm not disappointed. It's a fun game that's easy to play but gets far tougher the more you progress. Also, it's frequently updated with new content. I'm only giving it 3 stars because it frequently crashes, However, I've never lost progress due to a game crash. Even when crashing during load screens. Fix that issue and I'll definitely give it 5 stars

First of all, I have to emphasize how I am enjoying this game. The game is something I definitely am going to play. I would mention reducing the energy restore time, but I am afraid I have to emphasize about the auto attack system. it is nerve wracking when the character wont aim for someone with low health. Please add a setting in the setting menu allowing the player to choose whether the character should aim for the enemies closest to him or with the lowest health. Thank you.

Its a fresh experience towards a quick ti play shooter to pass the time. the only thing is that the levels are a little too cramped and it makes it that much more difficult depending on the type of enemies tour trying to kill. Oh and if you can do a run and gun type of game like this with different guns and perks similar to whats in the game that would be a great game to add this type of style to.

Tried this game once and didn't like it at all. Wanted a game where I could shoot a bow not just run around and let the computer shoot for me. When I tried it again however I thoroughly enjoyed it, although progressin gets difficult quickly when it does get difficult it's still fun. My only issue right now is currency availability and the fact that I've watched multiple ads in order to gain currency or a revive that have ended up failing and not giving me what I "paid" for.

Really fun game but with a few very annoying flaws. firstly, the energy. Refreshes 1 every 20 minutes, you need 5 to play through once, you have 20 max energy. It takes quite a while before I can play it again, nearly 2 hours. Second, the difficulty spike at level 5. It was pretty hard up to then, but very manageable with some time, but my God THE LASER BATS. Can move through walls, do a good amount of damage, AND they immediately shoot a straight beam through walls after tracking you.

Fun at first, but gets hard extremely fast. Game isn't not fun because it's hard, but it is literally impossible to progress. Enemies take nearly your entire health bar and they can take 10 hits. If you want to advance to the next stage, you have 3 times you can be hit to kill hundreds of mobs... Ridiculous. There should be health at the end of every stage. To make it worse, there is an energy currency to play. 4 attempts is not enough for a game of this difficulty. Balance or players will quit.

Archero is a wonderful game, very entertaining time-killer. Only issue, and a fair issue at that, is that weapon drops and any other equipment necessary for progression are almost non-existent. Aside from receiving mostly 1 or 2 upgrade scrolls (which you need plenty more later in the game), weapons hardly ever drop and when they do they're almost always low quality. This makes progression painfully slow. And will most likely be the reason I stop playing this game.

I really like this game but they have very predatory ads. As an example, the entire ad space is clickable. This causes a lot of frustration when I end up in Google play because of an accidental click. It also will pop up an ad for you to get an item and then refuse to play the ad. This is extremely frustrating and seriously impacts the feel of playing.

I've had this game for quite a while now. It's controls are awesome, graphics are great. The experience is fun! Ads are a bit much, but doable. The thing that gets me at this point, is that I'm pretty much at a dead end. I've got my gear at the highest quality but I can't get past the levels. The pvp is boring, multiplayer has a weird dynamic. I'm in it for the single player campaign but I'm stuck grinding for idk how long it'll take to move forward. Might have to delete and move on.
replyContent: We have submitted your feedback to our dev team for reference. Our dev team may consider your advice. Thanks for your support.

content: The game is very fun and a good time-waster if you're waiting for something. HOWEVER, the developers did a very poor job with boss balancing. One boss bursts out of the ground multiple times throughout the fight instantly without telegraphing its position before causing you to get hit out of nowhere with absolutely nothing you can do to prevent it. Another boss unleashes an instant-kill attack that hits you immediately and does NOT telegraph when it is activating. Very frustrating and needs work.

archero is simple, easy to pick up, hard to put down (except the energy system cutting you off), and best of all: extremely challenging. however, progression is EXTREMELY slow in my opinion. im spending 20-40 minutes spending my energy to get enough money to get a talent upgrade so i can attack 1% faster or deal 5 more damage to specific monsters. there's no real satisfaction of progression to me, it starts to feel like im throwing myself at a brick wall just trying to get good skill rolls.

Great game, super simplistic and visually satisfying. My only gripe is that you are required to connect to wifi or internet in order to upgrade your hero permanently, but once you do so you can never play the game offline ever again due to a "failure to connect to network" error. Please fix this so I can connect to upgrade and disconnect to play offline. If you can I'd gladly grant you a 5 star.

While it was fun and challenging to begin with it's quickly lost its appeal. With the limited energy and the level cap during a stage both take a fair amount of enjoyment out of the game. The biggest complaint is that chapters feel unbalanced. Multiple times I've used all my energy and only thing I've gotten was some coins that don't really help or improve my hero. I don't know when the last time I got a new weapon or armor drop. If the point is for me to spend money then I'd rather uninstall it
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: Fun at first, but gets dull after a few days. A lot is up to chance and after the first couple levels, it gets too difficult very quickly. You end up spending days trying to level up or collect enough cards to upgrade gear you don't even use. It would be great to have daily goals (kill 100 bats earn 30 diamonds, etc.) and to use diamonds to re-spin the ability wheel after leveling up. Also, an encyclopedia of enemies you've discovered (who's melee/range/flying, weaknesses, attacks, etc.)
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: Game is fun to play, controls are easy to get used to, graphics are pleasant. The return factor to replay stages are high because each run is different. I spent money on packs though which helped the progression s bit but it's not necessary. The game does crash though, almost everytime I use a revive scroll, the game crashes or freezes after a few minutes. Seems like a waste of money after purchasing revive scrolls.

This game is really fun, but once you get to the stage where it becomes a wave after wave battle, it stops getting as fun as it was before. I stead of moving through new rooms and seeing new bosses, you just fight a bunch of enemies in the same room over and over again. The progression is slow as well, there's lots of grinding and luck required in leveling up your character and getting new stuff. Fun game, but it kinda falls off for me. Low 7/10.
replyContent: Thanks for playing our game. Can you please let us know more details of your problem?

content: I've been playing this game casually for about a year and it has been fun! I didn't mind needing to watch ads etc. But recent changes made it really hard to enjoy the game, let alone crashing so frequently it's just not worth it. I used this to spend a few minutes here and there, not few minutes dealing with crashes, ads not registering, etc. Uninstalled but 3 stars for good memories.

The concept of the game is amazing! But the delivery is leaning a little too much on the pay2win side. After clearing the first world, the game purposely frustrates you with a steep curve that entices players to buy upgrades to clear it. I played it completely free, and it took weeks to be able to beat the 2nd world.

It's gotten a bit better since its release. One thing I really dont like is the battle pass. It's not worth it for its price. $5 every two weeks and still dealing with ads. If I'm paying anything I should have to watch ANY ads for anything. There's far too many ads to watch for someone giving you money. Also, you need better to earn make coins. Once you hit a certain point everything cost so much and it takes forever to be able to upgrade things.
replyContent: Our team is trying best to add more boosts and features to help with the gameplay. You can upgrade your heroes, equipment, talent, runes and etc. Then you will feel easier to pass the current stage. Thanks for your support.

content: Game is really fun at first, has lots of potential. Only major drawback is that it becomes far too hard, far too quickly. Even If you don't mind spending a few dollars. Many Mobs hit too hard and the "heart" drops are very scarce. Skills need some balancing, hard to win w/o crucial skills like multi, double arrow, Ricochet, peirce etc.I've also noticed the difficulty curb changes drastically room to room. Such as, not getting hit for 3+ rooms in a row, then the very next room nearly impossible.

Good and Bad. The game play relatively well, and fun to play. I would recommend to others, but i have couple problems that needs some adjustments. 1. There is a bug with the armor that freezes the enemy when im hit, when the monster that jump and hit me, it would get stuck mid air and i would take constant damage and the enemy will be unkillanle due to floating. 2. Why cant we have shops to buy material in the select screen that doesnt use gem or money? And its relatively hard to get items too.

So I've been playing this game for a year and a half; my main is a level 73 and I have the best gear. Some I've earned, some I've paid for. I've been stuck at a lvl for 11 MONTHS. Your difficulty scaling needs HUGE work. I've grinded for almost a full year to no avail. I understand progress gating, but this is insane. Please help me some how, from a huge fan of your game. Its the only mobile game I've ever stuck with. I'd like to see a new level, but unfortunately I'm not superman, or rich...
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: The game is fun to play and level up but the level design is trash. some of the levels you play are built in a way where you get trapped almost idmediatley and can do nothing about it. it gets very annoying after grinding through a bunch of levels just to get trapped the second i make it through the next door. this needs to be fixed so that you can't get trapped so easily and right away.
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: It is a good game. Not many ads. But the energy bar is a mechanic that I don't like. Why not let you play the game. Also the levels are nice but, some of them are just a handful of melee enemies thrown into a close quarters battle. And it is the most ANNOYING way to die when your health gets deleted by them when you get trapped in a corner with death staring right at you. Also some of the ads for the game are not what it is. That is why I lowered to a 3 star.

this game is fun.... really fun. but 2 things ruin the experience. the energy system, as well as the dungeons on the third chapter. this is a great game, but there are massive difficulty spikes out of nowhere, as well as a lot of randomness that completely makes the game unplayable at points, which again is only made worse by needing to use energy to actually keep playing the game, after dying to RNG. great game, but some core mechanics need to be reworked. but as i said, great game!

I like the idea of game, but for some reason, the animation seems to studder when walking/running on any stage. When I'm stopped, it's smooth again. Both graphics settings medium and high have the same effect. I've uninstalled and reinstalled Multiple times along with restarting my phone afterwards. I've a Samsung Note 10 Plus. I've also experienced this on my Pixel 2 XL. I want to like the whole experience, but it seems a bit jarring going from smooth to studder so consistently.
replyContent: Thanks, I'll check it out.

content: You have a good game but it keeps network issues. Was trying to collect the free, weekly obsidian chest but it the game kept saying there were network issues. Then it reset the time and i didn't get the reward. The network issues also sometimes prevent me from getting the Time reward. I've also noticed a little bit of lag during periods when these problems occur.

very fun playing, but you shouldn't have to play the same stage for ever, stage 8 is where I'm stuck, and I'm sure with a few more improvements the game would be amazing, first off you should have limited time deals coming every other day or so, different game plays would be great, especially something like endless mode or something so you can gain loot and coins faster(that's also ver strenuous) and fix the wheel of fortune after a boss on stage 8. it gives health when I dont need it too much

This game has excellent core gameplay, but falls into the traps of modern mobile games. The gameplay is very fun, the progression in each life is addicting and makes each playthrough unique, and you always feel really cool when you use your powerups effectively. That said, the limitations of the energy system are counter to the "just one more time" style of gameplay. I wish there were a version i could purchase (maybe even on steam) without these limitations.

it starts out pretty fun, but it gets pretty repetitive. After the first level, progression grinds to a screeching halt. And you better hope you get the right character upgrades to start. They are randomly chosen, cost significantly more over time, and you have caps on how many you can get. fun game for the first couple of hours though.

I absolutely love the game, but there is one thing i wish you would add. Currently the only way to reset your game progress is to completely delete your Google play account, and as someone who enjoys testing a game before actually playing it this has been... frustrating. Perhaps you should add an ability to reset your game after you reach a certain point, as i can see people exploiting it for item drops. Lets say level 15, or after you reach the second chapter. I'd greatly appreciate it!!!

So the gameplay is pretty great no doubt, smooth and fun. The only thing that really sucks it's not like the add where you can build walls then fight, so the add completely lies, and it has a energy system that makes it so you can only play so much before spending $ or watching adds just to be able to play 1 more round. Game would be so much better without the energy ststem.

Having played for half a year now I have given the game a higher rating. I would say for the success that it has received the updates and the additional content is being released months at a time. The November event ended started early November and ended well into December with Christmas approaching. I wish there were more mechanics added to the game - an overhaul of pets would be nice, where they could give the hero unique stats/abilities. The game still is largely ptw, still very lootboxy.

It's a fun game to pick up from time to time but a lot of bugs ruin the experience. For a game mostly based on dodging it's a shame when a boss with no health stays around for a whole extra minute and kills you. Also I bought the battle pass and the next time I opened the game it was gone. Please try to work on these bugs. Thank you. (Update) I enjoy the extra ways to get experience. Makes me want to play more. But a lot of the old bugs are still present.

I enjoy the game and it is genuinely fun anf original, but there is no sense of reward for completing a level/chapter. Every once and a while you get gems/coins/a chest as a result of your progress, but the only truly satisfying reward is progress. When you add that to the fact that the game gets incredibly hard fairly fast, you dont really have anything to work towards.

Fun to play at first, but your character evolves too slow compared to the increase in difficulty between levels. At some point you have to pay to get a bump in strength otherwise you're stuck for an insane amount of time on the same level which is incredibly boring. So yeah you can play without paying, but it comes a time when you're bored out of your mind, failing again and again in the same world bc it takes forever for your character to get necessary strength to put up a decent fight.

Can be fun but gets repetitive. You use energy to do most of the game, which is severely limiting since it takes 12 minutes to recharge 1 and half of the level options require 10. You can recharge it faster with ads but only 4 times a day and they only give 5 energy. Most of the level options are also limited in a similar way. Forcing players wait for a hour just to play one of the main levels is super annoying and enough to take away a star. I have more complaints but I'm out out of room.
replyContent: We have submitted your feedback to our dev team for reference. Our dev team may consider your advice. Thanks for your support.

content: Amazing game, only problems I have is needing to be connected at all times to play, the amount of coins you need to gain any advantage to progress, and the tiny amount of energy you get to play. It takes almost an hour to play one time if you have used your energy up. Just give unlimited energy so we can play for however long we want. Guaranteed you get better reviews.

Great game, very addicting, but constant network issues are seriously affecting the immersion. Network errors are messing with my ability to buy items with gems from either the regular shop or the black market dude, I can't fuse, upgrading takes forever, pretty much the only thing that runs flawlessly is the actual gameplay. 3 stars for now, but im hoping to give it a better rating when and if the network issues are resolved.

This game is a very good time killer but is stupid with leveling and upgrading. They basically expect you to spend money to make any real progress. It claims I am better then 76% of players but I wonder how far I can go without having to making another purchase to upgrade. I've spent a dollar so far for gems to revive. I feel they should offer more to players who choose not to spend money and change their fusing system basic it's horrible. Overall the gameplay is amazing and challenging.

It is a fun game but it still lacks polish. The virtual control pad should stay where we last clicked instead of resetting to the bottom and maybe be smaller, because it gets in the way when you go to upper parts of the levels. Also, upgrade scrolls and equipments should drop more often, as the way it is right now doesn't feel much rewarding. That summed to the steep difficulty curve will probably make players lose interest very quickly

I was one room away from the final boss and fainted, when presented the option to watch an add for a free revive. Upon the completion of the ad no X appeared and the ad would not leave my screen. I had no choice but to restart the app and upon reopening the app, lo and behold I was at the starting menu. Had I known this whould happen i would have used one of my own revives. Thanks for that!
replyContent: Thanks, I'll check it out.

content: This game is really well made and a lot of fun, but once you get past the fourth or fifth stage, there's way too many level up abilities locked for you to build a decent guy. When you start out, you constantly get to choose fun stuff like more arrows, better damage, etc. As the game goes on, it becomes highly conditional and the levels are hard enough that if you don't get a decent starting couple of levels, your whole run is shot. It would be nice to see build options at least.

I've been loving this game, though I'm unsure how long I've been playing. I'm the type of player that clicks the ads for bonus money, scrolls, revives, etc. However, recently none of the ads are seeming to work for me, it just keeps telling me the ad isn't ready yet and I'll keep clicking but it won't work. Great game, runs well, and some welcome changes have been implimented to improve the gameplay experience but I like getting my bonus money and things!

Good game, reminds me of The Binding of Isaac. Some issues though: -Difficulty curve is way too high. Enemy stats shouldnt increase so much after each boss, like world 4 onwards. -The control pad blocks the screen. Maybe part of the screen should be for controls? -Auto-Aim is bad in some cases, there should be a way to manually aim. -Enemy heavy rooms are really unfair if you dont have certain abilities/equips. I think if these issues were fixed, the game would be much more enjoyable.

Good game, would be great if it wasn't so grind and ad orientated. Devs need to keep it fun and worth playing as you level. They've done a terrible job at that. For example there's a hint to a purpose in the game from the characters but there's literally no story. So no reveals as you work through the levels; just more levels. Also any equipment can drop from any of the levels. So you are always grinding for everything and never just one thing. So much rng luck dependency throughout the game.

It's a fun top down shooter game, but there is so much grinding. You aren't really rewarded for your success. e.g. if you die on level 1, you get 100 xp points, if you die on level 30, you get 130 xp. The best way to progress in the game is to just die a lot until you have good stats. Also, about the stats: most enemies' damage scales with your max health, so your health hardly matters (not all scale). also, getting hit by 1 small attack or 5 small attacks all at once hurts you the same amount.

This game is a lot of fun! It keeps me coming back multiple times a day! HOWEVER the biggest complaints are the energy system. You have 20 max and it costs 5 to play a game. Thats only 4 games. It does refil slowly and you can watch 5 ads to get 5 extra games. But sometimes those games are short! Another problem is you can eventually get an abundance of coins and feel like you don't have anything to spend them on. Maybe be able to permanently buy abilities such as ricochet and multishot.

Was fun until you get to the level 8 map (top 90%) as the game says. All the new upgrades you unlock are worse than the old ones so they just clutter the pool to make it harder to get what you need. Like who wants pet crit chance they do about 20 times less damage than you. Some upgrades are so good they are almost required like ricochet. Have been grinding the same map for weeks with no progress because you don't get enough coins to progress anymore. Free players not welcome beyond this point.

Ok, that was terrible. Focusing 1 out of 2 bosses, health bar of fight goes down to 2 percent, nothing dies. Terrible enemy aiming system, enemy projectiles vary in speed depending on distance, invisible enemy projectiles and AOE damage zones. Definitely don't recommend with current issues. Could be a lot better without taking the challenge out of the game, but need a lot of work.

This would be a fun game. However after you get to the 4th stage it's almost impossible to progress. Throwing hoards of enemies that can move and attack through walls while most of the floor is spiked or saw covered. It becomes tedious and frustrating. Leveling up seems damn near useless other than letting you get 1 free skill point while beginning a level, although that maxes out at that single 1 so it becomes essentially worthless. Great concept, greedy execution. It's geared to make you p2w

This game has become very, very convoluted with a bunch of unecessary garbage that just eats away at your phone's memory. It's made the game extremely laggy, almost to the point where it's unplayable. I give it 3 stars, however, because the actual gameplay is fun, you just don't get to play very long before it freezes up. RESPONSE to the dev: you want me to send you screenshots... of lag? How would one go about doing that?
replyContent: Can you please provide us with more information? Please let us know your player ID and send the screenshots of the problem to archero@habby.fun. We will contact you after the tech team checks your problem and reply to us.

content: Really like this game. I would love to be able to recommend it, but the wall you hit is so hard that the game just stops being fun. I could understand the lightning dragon, it was a challenge, but the plant poss in chapter 6 is just... dumb. He constantly ducks and shoots fast bullets so you get one attack off per go. It takes so long to get past him to try to advance that I'm just done. It's become not fun. I don't mind a challenge but it's like sitting through unskippable dialogue.

The play and style of this game is colorful, fun, and a challenging bullet hell. The upgrades in dungeons are about half good and half useless. The simple play of 1 finger is great and the autotarget is usually good. However due to the autotarget, many abilities you can get are worthless. Ads are ok, too long but often optional. The UI changes randomly to make you spend gems, no confirm when spending best currency.

Enemies and projectiles are hard to see, item drops are super rare even for common gear, some enemies are just way too unbalanced (fire breathing dragons to name one), and occasionally there will be a room with just far too many enemies and projectiles going everywhere to the point where it's impossible to dodge and you will either take a lot of damage or die. Usually the latter. Otherwise it's pretty alright for a sort of binding of isaac clone. Wish the transition between floors wasn't white.

One of the greatest mobile I've ever played, but the stingy energy system ruins it. Devs, I have a simple solution and you don't have to change the energy system. Offer a one time optional price for the game that lets players have it with no energy restrictions. I only say this because I looked for it, ready to pay for the game, and it's not there.

I think this is a good game. However, the longer you play, the more it lags, and will eventually crash or be completely unplayable unless you relaunch the game. If you're unlucky and doesn't crash, the textures of the levels won't load up and appear black and won't show any walls or water. Also the game encourages to watch multiple ads; if you had a key, you had to watch an ad to even use it. Though I enjoy the majority of the game, I hope little problems will eventually be fixed.
replyContent: We have submitted your feedback to our dev team for reference. Our dev team may consider your advice. Thanks for your support.

content: When multiple arrows fire simultaneously, the sound is triggered out of phase, which is causing comb filtering. This makes it sound thin and unrealistic. This is probably due to the linear nature of code- try delaying the first arrow by however many samples it takes, and the second arrow will trigger in phase. Definitely made for the casual gamer that cant fire two joysticks at once.

The gameplay is fun but it has two things that stop it from being great. 1. Energy; like a lot of mobile games there is a limit to how much the game will let you play before you either have to wait hours or spend money. If there were a one time purchase for unlimited energy I wouldn't care the devs have to make money somehow but endless microtransactions suck. 2. The gear treadmill is a bit steep since each step up requires 3 times as much as the previous tier. However get rid of energy 5‚≠ê

first 2 stages are incredibly fun and challenging, but they are beatable. you have a lot less dependence on RNG for the "right" upgrades and stages are oriented so that the player has to engage the map to win each level. however, the 3rd stage (dungeon) is comprised of multiple simultaneous waves of projectile throwing madness with nowhere to stand and certainly little hope of survival unless you got a magical combination of upgrades to start off. the gear upgrade system is a joke

Fun and polished but doesn't scale well. The farther you get the more you lose because your pool of abilities grows and it is less likely you'll get the superior abilities. Winning becomes less about skill and more about sheer time to kill, because it becomes impossible to dodge everything, especially during boss fights. The game needs more player agency over random mechanics.

Same as every other review. The game is actually quite good, but the energy system needs a complete overhaul. You cannot play this game consistently. It is, for me, merely a game to play when my other game(s) are waiting for cooldowns. Fantastic for a short bit of playtime, then you cannot do anything for a long while. Scrap the energy system, or at least make it more user friendly and I'd consider a higher rating. All the same, thank you dev for the (otherwise) well made game!

It is okay. Randomization of abilities gets old fast. Level ups should offer the ability to choose which upgrade you want from the full list. You are actually penalized, the higher in stages you go, because they add more things to the list of randomized items. The Lucky Wheel options can stay randomized. The game is stacked against the player pretty heavily to push the purchase options. It becomes more blatant the higher stage you go.

Everything about this game is great, except at a certain point, it becomes painfully obvious this game is a pay to win. You hit a hard wall around level 5 and you flat won't advance much further without spending money. I have no problem with games being free with ads and in app purchases, but not as the only means of realistically advancing. I wish there was a paid version of the game that made gems drop from mobs, one continue after death per run. Great game otherwise.

The game is pretty fun, surprisingly. i despise any game with an energy system in order to play the game though this one is actually not too bad (anyhow, still despise it). I've been playing for several days now and I've never had to spend money or watch some dumb ad to get more energy. Some reviews are correct though about the luck system. you have to be lucky to get a good skill when doing levels. it's like a mix of rpg and gambling, pick one! Devs should add a skill tree type system instead.

Good game, terrible energy system. It's really hard to find a mobile game that I actually enjoy. I finally found one but I can only play it once every hour due to the energy system that's in place. It's as bad as candy crush's lives system. The kicker is that there's no premium version, or even a one time purchase to have unlimited energy. Instead, you have to pay every time you run out of energy (four games total), or wait for an hour. The lack of ads is nice though.

This is a great game and very challenging, but you need a strong internet connection to play because there are serious syncing problems. I finished a level, got some good loot, then the game has to sync with the cloud. But, was just passing an area where the connection was weak. Game becomes stuck syncing. I restarted the game and lost all the loot. Also, "Ad not ready yet" prevents you from getting a revive when you're just about to beat a level

like the game overall, very addictive. Cons: It lags often..when trying to move it freezes for a second or 2 then when u try to move again the mobs are on top of u and/or your dead. trying to control your character is a bit hard as the slightest movement has the character going way farther..the difficulty is high..even in the first 40 "rooms". when u have 6 mobs that follow and attack u while trying to avoid getting hit from projectiles from 4 other mobs at same time before u even reach room 30??
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: Archero has tons of potential. I really enjoyed playing through the levels and the random skills gives the game a lot of repeatability. However, there is only one mode of adventure. Creating a cycle of repetitive game play. If the game progressed at a higher rate it would be more enjoyable.

I used to really love this game 5/5. The levels scale ridiculously hard, but it's fun as a result. Problem is all these "new exciting updates" are usually to add a new subsystem of leveling up your character and, most importantly, added a new pair of resources to grind They keep adding different reasons to add more microtransactions for more resources that weren't previously needed, and it's gotten really boring. They didn't even try to hide the purpose of the most recent one: coupons. ???

The gameplay is excellent, one of the most challenging and fun games I've tried. That said, it feels VERY grindy, the first stage is easy but after that the enemies scale much faster than your equipment does. Combined with the luck aspect of rolling for your skills every playthrough and the limited number of runs you can play consecutively cause some frustration. I would call it pay to win but buying chests/coins won't get you very far without spending ludicrous amounts of money.
replyContent: Appreciate your attention to Archero, and the energy system would be continually optimized in the future: ) Thanks, have a nice day!

content: It's a fun game. I enjoy the RPG and leveling process, but it has too slow of a progression for f2p people; and not enough reasonable priced stuff if I did want to spend some money on the game. I'd love an option to purchase a version without ads where you could still get the daily benefits. There are too many ads which has killed the experience since without them your progression grinds to a near hault.

Game is fun, but the pay wall is too much... Any phone game that would cost $20+ to be able to play is ridiculous. Item drops are too rare which requires you to buy chests if you want to upgrade weapons and armor, and be successful through the levels it is dependent on getting quality levels upgrades which is inhibited by the energy system.  Free to play is great, but can I not have an option to buy a complete game with decent drop rates and an actually path to progression? It is this kind of system that me refuse to buy any in game content.
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: Man I used to really love this game. I originally gave it 5 Stars. But after you reach a certain point its completely unbalanced. I'm at the 5th stage now with 3k health, but enemies are doing 700 damage. With EPIC equipment. I think there were fewer stages, but they never went and rebalanced everything. Now its not fun any more. Just irritating. Even with "hero mode". If they rebalance the damage i'll give it 5 stars again. As it is its really about 2 1/2 after you reach a certain point.

Great, Could be better. The game is really fun, im not going to go off about only being able to play 4 games before you have to wait an hour to play once more, but its when you hit the 3rd dungeon, it doesnt matter how good you are there are just too many monsters that spawn. you cant progress and if you barely manage to not laggingly run around and beat a level the next one will kill you. This is something that needs attention.
replyContent: Hi, Sorry for the bad gaming experience,I will feedback our team,Please look forward to our new version.

content: I love this game no ads (unless you watch a vid for gems or revive, so ads upon request) but i been stuck on chapter 5 because my attacks do really well for the first 5 levels then after that it seems my attacks do less then 75% amount of damage!!?? It takes way to long to kill an enemy there for im stuck cant get past level 40 which takes me at least 20 minutes to get to sometimes more!! Please fix this issue or glitch its really frustrating..!!!

Fun. And frustrating. It's a progressive & somewhat randomized dungeon crawler. Gain drops & coins, level up gear & character, and buy things along the way. It's been pretty fun until reaching a stopping point. Stuck on castle 5 for days. It seems like the enemy health scales unfavorably. More so, enemies don't get much easier as the hero levels & as items get upgraded. The game has 12 castles but good luck getting past castle 5 without grinding for...weeks, perhaps.

Honestly this game is fun. The random level up is a fun way of forcing you to play the game in crazy fun ways but it has alot of draw backs. There are to few options to choose from and sometimes two or more of the options will be the same thing, usually one of the more useless abilities. The energy system frustrates me more than anything though. I want to play this game and sometimes bad rng rolls when leveling up make some runs pointless. I would much rather pay 2 dollars and have unlimitedplay

According to the game im the top 2% of players. I've played quite a lot so I think Im safe on my critique. Once you get to the harder levels it becomes artificially difficult in the manner that it's no longer bullet hell where you can dodge but just huge clusters of enemies in the tightest spots making it impossible to do anything about getting hit, it just becomes a manner of how much dmg you can take or how fast you can kill the enemies. Was good for a while until it became only this.
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: This has been one of my favorite mobile apps in a while. On most of the other reviews, they have issues with the Energy System. They've fixed that which is good. My only issue with the game is the balancing between each dungeon. I find myself having to replay the same dungeon 50+ times just to make little. That makes this game very repetitive and not enjoyable to play. New items hardly drop for you, so there isnt much to do but grind, grind, grind to make any progress. Not too fun...

Pretty fun game until you reach chapter 5, at which point it becomes prohibitively hard without spending money. At that point you will die in 3 or 4 hits to even the earliest enemies, and every bad becomes really spongy. The leveling system is neat, but again gets worse in the later chapters. The more abilities you unlock the worse your options get, and I find the later chapters just water down the pool with less desirable skills, such as boosting your pet damage or pet attack speed, etc.

Changed from 5 to 3 stars. It's an excellent game but I've hit a roadblock. I only get coins from the wheels and hearts are few and far between. Advancement is stalled unless I pay. Unfortunate. The randomness of upgrade choice is by far the most frustrating part along with rarely receiving hearts from killing monsters, sometimes going 3 and 4 levels. I've made no progress in 3 days.

Dropped the game till today and couldnt remember why. Now, thankfully, I remember. Progress is a snail's crawl. Certain upgrades are tons better than others and choices are super limited. Enemies scale with your upgrades during the dungeon so damage never really increases which is why multihit and bounce are the best upgrades. Even then the damage becomes a joke as the enemies scale. Not worth the time. Game is just frustrating.
replyContent: Each of our updates could be based on user's request in feedback. The gameplay can be strengthened by upgrading your hero, equipment and talents. If you feel the current level is too difficult, you can play the previous level and make yourself stronger. Have a nice day.

content: Very Slow to do anything easy to burn up energy, and almost no progress the game is simple and enjoyable, but there is room for improvement to make the game more enjoyable, like a monsterpedia, get to know the enemies you defeat, or a weapons armory like unlock diffrent weapons with weapon skill trees, armour collecting is ok but random leveling and power up based on find and survive are cool but could use better progression in game, the total game gets a 3. Plenty of room for improvement.

Somewhat decent game. I have been playing it for a good while. The game itself is very repetitive and not at all like the ads on instagram said. The gear is annoying to grind and upgrade. Loot and character skill upgrades are also way too expensive. After the second area the abandoned dungeon is the most unfun thing in the game. At least no forced ads...

I believe this game is addicting and all. No the ad isn't like the actual gameplay but it is still addicting, the only problem I have, probably not the only on either, but there is a major difficulty increase. For a beginner, I have some pretty good gear and I can't get through the whole dungeon on world 3. It's a good game dont get me wrong, but a major difficulty spike. Really should fix that.

Good game but I need a checkpoint option right before final bosses, restarting the whole stage is getting tiresome and pretty irritating. I'm stuck on stage 3 and getting to the Dragon is hard enough without good skills so having to do it all over again is pretty angering. Maybe two lives? I don't know but something has to change. Otherwise everything else is great. // Decrease projectile speed for underground worms(bosses) they're way too fast and considering there's 2 it's incredibly difficult

It's okay, but I don't enjoy the whole energy system because now I need to wait forever before I can play again (I typically delete these games because of this). Also, I feel like the upgrade system is a bit high. You have to play NUMEROUS times to get one upgrade. Upgrade system should be tiered and picked at player's choice. And damage from enemies should be congruent with level played. Please consider this in your next update. Thank you!

I play this off and on as the mood strikes me. It's just like the rest of these Archer games with nothing extra. Poison: the most useless element. Similar to fire, it does damage over time but the damage doesn't mean anything. Bosses don't feel it, and enemies die in one it two hits anyway, so all poison mods are just to slow progress. Level up choices are regularly two or three of the same mod, again just to slow progress.

this is a fun game, I just feel like theres a lot missing. first I feel like there should be more variety in gear. also the difficulty is a bit too hard, Ive been playing for a few days now and Im barely on the 3rd area. I also noticed with a certan combination of powers they cancel each other out and dont work (cant remember the specific ones). the energy system is okay, though I wouldnt mind a hightler cap. Im also missing a purple key from the progress rewards (clearing lvl 50 reward)

I love this game, but I'd be much more inclined to give it a higher rating if my game would stop losing its progress. I have a track record of playing the game, then exiting out of it before I can finish my run just because I become busy with other things. Sometimes I won't even completely clear the app from my history, but when I open it back up, my progress is gone and I don't have any of the rewards I earned. It's become frustrating recently.

This game would be a perfect 5 stars if the later levels were like the beginning. No matter how much money you spend, after hitting dungeon 6 or 7, you're done. 10 levels of bosses in a row, with no healing between levels and not even gaining a full level per boss fight?? Plus, without Ricochet and Multi Shot, you have little to no chance of clearing dungeon 6. Having random stat boosts and the inability to choose power ups each level except by a slot style method is ludicrous.

I would love to give this game 5 stars. It is a fantastic game that is extremely addicting. However with the recent updates that they have made to the game over the last year I would say anytime I try to run an ad to get a free chest or to revive myself in a dungeon the game will just crash. Update after "repair" game crashed 12 times playing a single hero map. Ads constantly crash the game and just playing will crash the game. No problems with ads in other games 'cept this one
replyContent: We have completed the repairment. Please restart.

content: There needs to be a way to get rid of some of the items on the rolls. The only reason it's so hard to progress is by random chance that the slots give you a decent upgrade. I only manage to get the garbage upgrades that make it impossible to make any progress. Other than this the game is pretty good but too much grinding to make up for the slots not giving you decent upgrades.

Update to the game, so update to the review. It got an extra star! Almost every problem from my previous review was fixed, the game is still extremely repetitive, but the difficulty has been scaled back tremendously, and you can pick what levels you want to play on. The reason it still only got 3 stars is because there's a new bug, health drop. Occasionally, your health will just go down during an encounter, you don't have to be hit by the enemy or anything, just a random drop in health.
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: It's a fun roguelike game but man the difficulty ramping is just bizarre. Sometimes you just get constant awful RNG where the enemies at stage 30+ is nearly impossible given how enemies can shoot over walls, you're trapped in a tight area, etc. In addition, man there's just too many projectiles on the screen sometimes especially with your own minions going crazy. Still fun, but a lot of room for improvement. Also, stop spawning fire crocs at the entrance to stages good god it's dumb lmao
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: Good game, HOWEVER... Do NOT plan on playing this game without internet. Even thought it allows you, when you connect back to the internet, you lose all. Your. Progress. I beat a chapter that I was stuck on for a while, got tons of sapphires, and when I connected back to the internet, it was all gone. Very frustrating.
replyContent: For your data saving safety, plz login your GameCenter/Google Play Account and keep it online.

content: Super fun and addicting. Also very greedy. Uses the "Energy" to play mechanic so you can only play so much unless you buy energy or watch ads. Game also has a battlepass, so you can pay them for better stuff because you enjoy the product, to still not be able to play as much as you want. There are ads for everything. They all come with goodies of course, and half of them aren't mandatory, but they're there. I'd give 5 stars if this wasn't so blatantly money grubbing.
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: OVERALL the game is good... there is a bug with the bosses where if you drain its health all the way down, it is still alive. you can still beat the boss, but it really messes with my playing. also i was falsely accused of having a 3rd party app and that my account would be banned... I just want to play... tornadoes need to be able to benefit from the abilities such as ricochet and piercing and either all weapons need to be buffed, or all attack/attack speed upgrades need to be buffed.

Since getting into chapter 2 (desert) I'm convinced the ads were misleading about what the game is like, as if it had puzzle elements like setting up the terrain for taking on enemies, or trying to free someone from a maze. Instead it's about dodging attacks and choosing upgrades like multishot or poison. Still somewhat fun, but just not interesting enough for me.

part of the problem is the devil, if you actually kept the buff after that one round it might be worth the trade, as things stand i am now down 300 health, PERMANENTLY. it makes it very difficult, i understand that there has to be a sacrifice but i think it would easier (and more enjoyable) if the process cost money or the debuff lasted like 10 rounds (for which you have to pay 5 energy out of 20 energy might i add). but other than that the game is pretty good. three stars.

A solid game overall, but hard to recommend without improvements. Ads in the game are never forced *technically * but they are forced in the sense that the things locked behind ads are pretty much a requirement if you don't want to have a bad time. they do not offer any option to pay to remove ads. The season battle passes only remove ads from a very specific instance within the dungeons, so even with that pass, you still have to watch 95% of the ads in the game. The pass is also poorly done.
replyContent: Hello~ If you are talking about a video that rewards gem, these are optional and you can get rewards by watching them. You can also choose not to watch it~ Thanks for your support and wish you a happy game!We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience.

content: Fun for a little while. Controls are simple but sometimes are unresponsive. Sometimes feel like the game changes the rules or monster behavior to increase difficulty. Powerups often don't work, projectiles that normally travel straight paths will occasionally chase you, dying for no reason, that kind of stuff. I keep playing but growing tired of the game glitches.

I enjoy the game and love the gameplay. It's super fun and challenging, but like every other review on this game the energy system needs to change its wack and it sucks. If that one thing got fixed or changed it would make it one of my new favorite games but because of this, it's not. Will give 5 stars if the energy system ever gets reworked.

I'm no big phone gamer by any means but this game has captivated me to play more and enjoy it all. The play style and gameplay. The one improvement and i believe to be a big one. Free to play looting system. There needs to be more item drops. Feels like the "fusing" aspect seems pointless without spending money. The upgrading seems lacking +3 when base is at 50 seems small for the hard grind for coins. With slight changes to items 5 stars...

Fantastic game. addictive, creative, and simple. i would suggest either shortening energy regen time or lowering the cost of energy to play. waiting a full hour to play one time is a bit much, but if each energy gave one game play, a user could play every ten minutes. or at least provide a total energy advancement. im at level 11 and havent moved from 20, so maybe there is one in place and i just havent reached it yet. overall, great game.

This would be a 5 star game if they fix the energy system and the item drop rate. The game is really fun and challenging. The enemy bosses scale up pretty fast so it makes progression slower and more frequent item drops would help greatly with that. Overall love this game and would recommend it to anyone who likes challenging roguelike gameplay.

stuck with this game until castle 5. it gets harder as you go, not because of monsters, but because the pool of random(!) skills gets bigger. castle 3 you fight multiple waves without getting xp, so if you dont randomly get a core skill in the very beginning like multishot or ricochet or damage boost, you're screwed. the further you progress, the more useless skills in the pool. otherwise good game, one really silly, but heartbreakingly fatal mechanic. needless frustration, why? its silly to do.

Game is good. Challenging enough too, but that being said, it has PLENTY of room for improvement. For instance, the red reapers with ricocheting (bouncing) attack with their "death scythes" starting at normal mode level 11, are EXTREMELY OP, and I say this as a person who GREATLY appreciates a challenge. Their ability is nearly impossible to track and they're ALWAYS paired with enemies that basically guarentee you will take damage in that stage. Unless you "pay to win" and become OP yourself.

I like this game enough that I've spent a bit of money on it. The most frustrating thing is the consistent network errors that prevent me from collecting any loot outside of a dungeon. It doesn't matter if I'm connected to wifi or not, I still get "network error" messages that block me from collecting loot, watching ads for loot, continuing runs, and synchronizing data...it actually makes the game unplayable at times.

Great fun. Level up bonuses are a bit random, but getting the perfect perk combination is really satisfying. However, there have been numerous progress halting bugs as of late. The game freezes, shuts down, and I lose my end of chapter rewards. The free battle pass rewards are also not being given. Just the check mark that says I already got them.

FIX CO-OP!!! Love the game! I would love to see a defense or resistance boost in abilities since these higher levels can get you squashed in 2-4 hits if you're unable to dodge the billion projectiles around. Not enough opportunities to upgrade armor, not enough drops and they should be included in battle pass say every other season. Also if I'm gonna spin for gems, I want gems to be the only option.

The last update said the chapter difficulty was lowered and drop rates improved. In reality the difficulty hasn't changed and the drops are even less frequent now. I liked this game but it has turned into one of the worst grindfest games in the app store. My feeling is they want people to spend real money. I've been stuck on the same level for nearly two weeks waiting for the drops needed to upgrade and they never come. The random perks almost never help make you stronger either.

Very fun game and great idea. The quick change in difficulty made me lose interest quickly though. The only way to progress is to get enough gold to upgrade, and the only way to get gold is to waste a tremendous amount of time playing the exact same level over and over. It got very repetitive and the progression was so slow it got boring quickly. If you are looking for a fun game for 2 hours and then want to delete it forever, this is it. Also, don't expect anything to change.

The first two chapters get five stars. Chapter three gets one star. Basically chapter three gets difficult enough that it becomes a tedious grind that stops holding my interest; worse it feels like the developers ran out of ideas at that point. Game also has some under utilized systems, like inventory fusing/crafting. I've invested hours in play and still don't have more than two of any one item even you need three to fuse. I suspect I'd be disappointed in the outcome even if i could.

Very fun arcade style dungeon crawl. However, the new skill perk when you get so many kills to unlock a skill MIDBATTLE, requiring a roulette wheel that will spin and requires you to click on it has killed me more times than the skill gained was actually useful due to sudden pause in game play, requiring an interactive button to press which is mid screen (not close to the directional controls) is haphazardly done and frankly would be better if it was reworked if not removed all together.

The game has very solid gameplay but it's difficulty and scaling doesn't make any sense. There's no reason to ever go to the event page once you clear a couple of areas because they just don't give you enough resources and are a waste of energy and the levels go from insanely easy to pay-to-win very quickly. I got to the 8th stage before putting the game down but it was fun until then
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: Its a great game. But it has major flaws. First off, it copied the battle pass trend for a game that didnt need it. Second, nobody should ever pay 20$ for a single character, the stats are barely different. Third, they added energy so you can only play like 4 timea every once in a while. Not as fun as it once was, but its alright.

Graphics are nice, as well as the controls and character choices... However the game only gives you 20 energy and each match costs 5. Not a very good in-game energy system. Also the individual areas in each level are different each time you go in, so its really hard to come back and beat the level if each time it swiches on you. I also belive the character upgrades should be adjusted, and more ways to obtain chests.

This game is a lot of fun. But it has 2 annoying issues. The first involves the daily chest. Opening the free daily chest gives you a free item. Quite often a second free chest appears, but if you take this 2nd chest, it takes 60 gems. Even though there is clearly a FREE button. The 2nd issue is in the support. Several times I have tried to use their contact form to report this issue, but the submit button won't activate. Other than these 2 issues, a fun game.

Was fun at first but way too hard now...lost interest. There is no way to choose an easier difficulty, which seems silly to me. Got stuck on chapter 4 and now I can't get past so I lost interest in playing. Would love to see some improvements, though, would definitely get back into it!
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: Fun but still bit buggy. 10% extra gold effect from the epic rings isnt effective at all. My character is wearing two epic rings but shows no extra gold contribution. Game shuts down randomly, but often by the time I finish the level. Two same skills showing up at the level up is just another disappointment. Also wish there's a way to check the character stats like critical % and damages in mid-journey.

Love this game been playing for a long time now. After update, expedition and infinite mode is way too hard to pass any levels for mid range level players, the difficulty is way to hard to pass levels basically impossible, level difficulty should be set for what level you are, every level should be possible to beat no matter what level you are. Rest of the game I love. Until a change to those things I'll be at 3 stars.

Good graphics. It's initially fun but it has problems. There are too many bad skills. It is frustrating playing through a hard chapter and being burdened by having to choose between bad skills. Sometimes the same skill is offered twice so when I level up I only have 2 to pick from instead of 3. The ultimate ability is too easily triggered. Double tapping on the joystick happens unitentionally. There needs to be a seperate button for it. There are more problems but I'm out of room ...

Fixed issue with my acc.. Great game, I've spent way to much time and money on it but hey It is what it is. I wish that battlepass removed all ads tho, from the wheels aswell, because I find myself skipping them and its just not worth the $4.99 every 2 weeks tbh there has to be more of an incentive. It also randomly glitches and resets everything sometimes and I find myself having to re-equipt everything and switch characters. You still retain everything but its annoying and inconvenient.
replyContent: We have submitted your feedback to our dev team for reference. Our dev team may consider your advice. Thanks for your support.

content: The game is fun overall.. but the energy to play is ridiculous.. the weapon/item drop ratio is very slim which makes it difficult to build your character.. especially combined with the use energy to play.. IMO, it feels as if the auto targeting can be improved. I would automatically target an enemy furthest away from myself when clearly the direction my character is facing should begin to attack another enemy thats closer in proximity. Also, the game intermittently closes at the end of matches.

Archero shoots itself in the foot with its draconian energy system. You get 20 energy, which after advancing to the next chapter will last less than 10 minutes for four attempts. Some of those attempts will be doomed from the start from bad initial ability level-up rolls as well. Then add in very... very low drop rates, and the fact it will take 10 attempts to gain one simple level... A great game, held back by awful game entropy mechanics.

Silly upgrade system kills game progression. I understand free-to-play. I don't pay and am prepared to wait and grind to get the free drops. It's the upgrade system that's fundamentally broken because most people are stuck with tons of resources and fully upgraded "Great" items, waiting to obtain the "Epic" items. Good gameplay mechanics and graphics. Spoiled limited item/upgrade system.

While it's a great game initially, there is little long term potential unless you want to shell out gobs of money to gear up. Gear drops are very rare and difficulty ramps up very fast to the point that if you don't get EXACTLY the right random power-up spins during a level there's no way you can finish it. It can take many dozens of repeats of the exact same level over and over again to progress. It gets extremely frustrating.

While it is a simple and fun little game to play I can't help but list a few issues: Enemy projectiles existing even after you cleared the room, projectile hit boxes (looking at you giant bat boss) are a little bs at points, attack boosts seeming useless as the enemy health scaling drastically increases, and the overall RNG mess that are the skills, you can be screwed over majorly if you don't get the skills you need for the area. That's my 2 cents, higher rating if the issues are fixed.

Pretty fun game, but network errors will cost you. I've watched many an ad to get the in-game benefit, did not receive the benefit. "Chest Keys" will stay in your inventory for a short time after you use them, giving you the option to use them again immediately, but you will actually be charged the premium currency. I've done expensive upgrades that drain the required resources but do not actually upgrade the item. No response from support. tl;dr Have a GOOD connection; errors will penalize.

Expected more out of an app i saw everywhere. The game is difficult at least to me. Gameplay can be satisfying but ninety percent of it can be frustrating with the enemy mechanics. Worth trying at least with very active and kind staff. My biggest problem is that it isnt like some of the ads but that can be overlooked as it is still a unique experience and is fun at times. (Review is much more fair after the revision)

content: Good game overall, smooth gameplay. Certain stupid technicalities really drag it down though. For example, if you exit the room you've just cleared and enter the next before the items have a chance to float to your character, you forego gaining those items. It's the most asinine idea for an item collection system I've seen. If you killed the enemy, you should get the items/coins. Period.

I personally love this game and am extremely addicted to it but sadly Everytime I try to login to play the game glitches. I might be able to scroll to the store then my whole screen freezes and sits bugging up and down really fast. It started doing it after every round but now it does it when I press any button. This game would be 5/5, but the glitching just makes it enraging. Great game though it's super fun and addicting to play.
