content: The game has great controls and mechanics, but some of the enemies are ridiculously unbalanced. Some examples include the final bosses of W7, where the bosses are so completely random that not only do they suddenly leave VERY little room for error, but some situations are completely impossible to not get hit in. Many teleporting have a habit of teleporting directly onto the player with no warning, sometimes dealing over 1/4th of the player's Max HP. It's a un game, but it's unbalanced sometimes.

Decent fun for a short time, but the terrible progression and battle pass ruin it after a while. This game probably has the worst battle pass I've ever seen. Can only get battle pass XP by spending money for the subscription or doing daily quests, many of which require you to spend more money! (Like buying an epic chest from the store). The seasons are also ridiculously short, so you'll be constantly spending money on them. Please don't waste your money on that
replyContent: We have submitted your feedback to our dev team for reference. Our dev team may consider your advice. Thanks for your support.

content: DO NOT BUY THE BATTLEPASS UNTIL YOU FINISH ALL 16 LEVELS! This is a fun game but upgrading becomes a real grind not long into it even when you pay for the various upgrades. As for the BattlePass it can sometimes disappear and then reappear. Recently I was at lvl 15 and lost out on the last 3 obsidian keys because it disappeared for the last 2 days of the season and didn't show up again until the next season had started. Just wait until you have completed all 16 levels before you get the pass.

I like the game but needs more chests or item drops. They are to few and far in between. I've had the same weapon, cloak, and ring for the last three chapters. also maybe go to level 15 not 11. increase max glory every,I don't know, 20 actual character levels. I would like to have more abilities! hell that's what makes the game great, are the different combinations of abilities that can be played with. overall a good game but until these changes or something is done, just a backburner game.

The game's fun and all but I recently recieved a problem where a window popped up after doing the new year event. No my phone isn't the best and it started lagging and it asked if I wanted to revive with an ad. I thought "why not?" Watched the ad and I finished that level and went to the next and noticed my character was glowing blue and thought it was a bug. Next time I died I recieved a window on the screen claiming I'm using illegal 3rd party apps??

amazing bullet hell type game but the energy system feels like it bogs the game down alot wish it didn't have one. or at least a quicker fill rate. Update: the controls get glitchy and the level cap at 10 is pretty weak takes all the thrill of winning a stage away because you're not going to be able to build your character skills and perks after that. from 4 to 3 stars. this game has such potential.

It's ok. Has some things I wish they'd change. 1) It makes you watch an add to open the free chest. If you have a key to open it and you have the "free open" available, then it makes you watch the add before you can use the key. 2) Your run in a dungeon can go from great to terrible, it's all luck dependant. They should make it so you can customize which ones you might get, so you can either focus on melee or range. 3) You're supposed to choose from 3 each lvl, but a chance you get a duplicate.

Decent game, bad scaling and monsters The first few floors (dungeons?) are fun to play with good monsters that have a small flaw to exploit so you can win. After that, the arenas give the monsters ridiculous health buffs so it takes you 2-3x longer to kill them even if you got crazy upgrades. bringing me to my next point, many of the higher levels and certain areas cannot be beat with any skills.you have to have very specific ones to beat it. Some monsters are really dumb and need to be reworke

ABSOLUTE GRINDFEST!!! Game is super fun and easy to play, that being said...It truly feels like the last few updates have made drastic changes in damage to enemies, or the enemy health just got jacked way up. Either way, it's made it even more of a chore to really enjoy this game any longer. It feels like since they implemented the daily challenges they've steadily increased the difficulty of them to a ridiculous level. All purple gear, definitely not a Git Gud set of complaints. Balance is off

Fun game and alot of cool weapons and abilities but feels incomplete. A list of weapons available, types of enemies, easier access to weapons (such as a store in the main menu or less gems for more weapons), a survival mode that continues until you die √ó2 times (also the use of gold rather than just gems would be great!) And finally weekly character unlocks of locked characters to try them out? All the best!

I would have rated this game higher, but the fact is there's no where to go after you've upgraded your character so many times. Hero shards are very hard to come by, you have to pay to win after so many levels and the random pics on the hero selection side where the ruins are done it's so expensive now that there's no way to upgrade it more than once a week. Some of the levels are so difficult and the items are so random that is very hard to get anywhere in this game after the first 5-10 levels.

would be more fun if the energy bar wasn't a thing trying to force me to spend money. Also, the fact that the further you get in the game, the more impossible it becomes. Not in a challenge way btw. It just makes it where your gear is too low level and you basically do no damage without grinding. I've spent over two months every single day to try and level more and more everyday and unlock gear to upgrade my character to beat the level I've been stuck on.

Fun game and the concept is great but the energy system is pretty brutal. After you run out, you can only play once an hour. I'd be a lot happier if it regenerated faster, or if there was an option to increase the energy pool. I'm addicted but I can't play and the result is that I'm frustrated. I'll give five stars as soon as that's fixed.

Do not pay for upgrades. It is the biggest waste of money. The game is fun and passes time. The problem being is in order to get to a next chapter your hero has to be extremely upgraded. Not just the hero but on all phases. This means you will have to spend weeks, if not a month playing to get the equipment needed or pay for the equipment which does not work well because as you upgrade your play they will upgrade the damage made on the character.
replyContent: Hello, We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience.the game can be strengthened by accumulating equipment and upgrading talents. If you feel that the level behind it is too difficult, you can play the previous level and make yourself stronger! Then challenge the level behind!~!

content: The game was really fun in the beginning, but as you fall in to the later dungeons, the damage your hero puts out does not scale well in the later dungeons. Also the amount of abilities just seem way to much especially for the newer ones that have been added in, they add almost zero survivability or damage mitigation. There only seems like a few abilities that are worth anything in dps increase or damage mitigation. Anymore it feels more like a chore to run the dungeons or the special instances.

Well since the newest update the game is glitchy. I went to play the infinite adventure which cost 15 power and it froze. I lost my 15 power and opportunity to play it without paying 100 gems. Not the first time. I just wish they could do a better job of preventing us from having to pay to play. Basically, give us more opportunities or make it cheaper.

Honestly this is a pretty awesome game the controls are easy the gameplay is smooth but like all other games the energy system is flawed big time. Having to wait 12 minutes just for one energy is way to long when it takes 5 energy just to start a round. It would be so much better if it would just refill your entire energy bar in let say 30 minutes that way you dont have to wait a few hours just to be able to play 4 more matches. Will give 5 starts if the energy system is more optimized.

I'm basically comparing this to Risk of Rain 2 as i feel that is the clostest thing to this "game". Lets point out the big issue....you guys put a damn energy limit in your game. I dont want to be forced to stop playing a game. Next up is the fact that its a horrible bullet hell. You get attacked by tons of enemies that either throws things at you or rushes you. You can't even shoot while moving so you basically have to take damage if you want even a shot. ROR2 is better.

Not horrible as a temporary time waster. The rewards system has improved tremendously over the past several months. Unfortunately the newest update ruined alot of the game for me. It's one thing to roll out a new hero (which can only be bought for $18.99). Had nearly beaten chapter 13 and they made it twice as difficult for no other reason than to slow progression. Very disappointing, but my review score is still higher than previously if for no other reason than the additional benefits.

It's a good game,only problem is that you have to stop moving to shoot and a lot of the rooms dont feel centered around that and makes me think they didnt test some of these rooms. I get they were going for a binding of Isaac style but, in that game you have to move a lot and you can move while shooting here it doesnt work at all.

The difficulty spikes in this game are very random. You need RNGesus on your side to progress at times. If it wasn't for this highly random design I would rate higher. Other than that it's a game to play when nothing else sounds good and you just want to kill some time without getting attached.

It starts out super fun, but as soon as you clear the relatively reasonable-difficulty Chapter 4 map, all of a sudden it becomes a grind fest to clear the same level over and over again until your character is built up enough to do anything else. Events and Chapter 5 are basically a place to throw away your activity points until you've bored yourself to tears clearing Ch. 4 a hundred times. Good for a change of pace, but not a game to command much loyalty.

Put Google Play Achievements on it! Update: The game is a great time killer, but the way the enemies attack damage and your health fluctuates very often and random. One moment you take 600 damage and lose 600 health, the next you take 600 damage again, but lose 80 health. They need to work on the health/damage control, it feels too random. No point in buying gems when you get random results that don't have any implication.

The game is extremely fun and addicting... until the grind starts. Now some might argue that there is no grind, but i would argue that because of the horrible targeting system that constantly revokes control from the player even when they specifically choose one enemy, it stops being about skill and starts being about how many gems you can rack up by either grinding, watching ads, or paying real money. Honestly so dissapointing.

This is a pretty cool game to play off and on just wake up do your daily stuff lvl up your stuff and then try to beat stuff I would give it five stars but the game is too much of a pay to win game and when you try to play to win it's gonna take you a while to progress

content: Game would be better if it were more like Crack Shooter, where when you change equipment, all the upgrades you put on the previous item, transfers to the new item you equipped. So you don't have to destroy your equipment or grind to level another weapon. Also when you get a meteor lvl up, maybe outline it another color than red, because it looks like an enemy is casting a spell, when it's yours. The amount of money they want you to spend is also ridiculous. Two different Battle passes? It's bull

Well, I was a bit skeptical while downloading archero, since I've seen some complain about some games having too many and such. But surprisingly, this is a fun game. There's just only one problem I have with the game, but not too much. The game can feel unplayable if you're playing offline or on airplane mode just to play the game ad-free, and you can't make any upgrades to your gear for most. But overall, this is definitely a game to play to kill time. Highly recommended!

An overall fun game except for hero duos. Like almost a pointless game mode to play. Anyone who you get paired up with either doesn't even try to play or will disconnect shortly after starting. That game mode needs consequences for backing out of a game or a way for a player to revive the dead teammate so you're not playing alone.

The game has gotten better since my last review and it's nice to see new content fairly often. However, I would like to see the ability to refund levels (for coins, sapphires, chips, and shards) in heroes, because 100% of the time, I'm only playing one character. Regrettably, I've still sunk levels into other heroes. Other than that this game has come a long way. Keep it up.

Nice little vertical scroller with basic strategic challenges and upgrades. Ya well, the unfortunate truth about games like this is that if you think it's free then you are incorrect. With this update and the "Battle Pass" price increasing to $17 then don't plan on achieving any high level. Sad truth is that if one is disabled as I am(tiny fixed income), or just regular poor, it's probably time to move on to another newer "free" game. But if you got a few bucks cash then this game is fun.

A pretty good game in general. Although, to be fair, you know it's a good game if every other "game developer" are trying to rip it off to gain its popularity. I will say though, the Hero Duels is kind of bad. It's really laggy when controlling and doesn't shoot half of the time. A lot of times, I don't even get a match up. I personally think the way to fix this would to have some sort of AI that uses the account-you're-fighting-against's stats, like some other games do. Overall, fun game.

Great game, and I have been playing for years. I would have given it 5 stars, but there are cheaters out there. I tend to stay away from Hero duels, or the monster arena. I have seen everything from players moving sideways, 1 hit and dead, defense set up behind, etc. Stay away from anything that involves you playing other players because the cheaters will always win.....it's the only way they can win. I do recommend this game and if you pay to play, you will get more stuff faster.

A fun game to burn your time on, I cycle back to it from time to time. But many of the features are stuck behind major paywalls. I wish there were more permanent options for payment, many of the things you purchase are temporary. And paying $25 for a character is rediculous. Update Dec21: I've discovered a free, yet tedious method for unlocking characters without paying. The game is a fun little bullet heck with a whole ton of typical lootbox additions.
replyContent: We have submitted your feedback to our dev team for reference. Our dev team may consider your advice. Thanks for your support.

content: adds are actually fairly close to what the game is. (Though still slightly misleading) to be clear, the game is a bullet hell where you improve your character through a run to reach stage end. enemy damage is high and most builds feel satisfying. have yet to encounter something that feels unfair, though im only 2 stages in(50 rooms per stage) there is preasure to watch random adds if you dont pay 17$ for the battle pass, so far they've all been optional at least.

Overall, a very enjoyable game. I love the concept and enjoy the changing enemies as you progress through the chapters. I do have a few things that i think would improve the game, however, for example, some of the upgrades are very unbalanced. In many games, a bloodthirst upgrade is incredible and essential. Here, it's not even worth it because the healing is so low. In addition, a way to remove a couple upgrades from your pool would be great as I often get unuseful options.

This is a great game. Each level is unique and thematically cohesive. The difficulty is challenging. The controls are simple and tight. But (and this is a big but) the energy meter cripples the experience. In a game that leans on the need to upgrade your character to even stand a chance in the higher levels it is absurd that you have to pay the same energy to grind lower levels. The energy system should be remove or at the very least decreased on chapters you have already beaten.

I've been playing this game for a few weeks now and I love it. Pros: You get to level your character and equipment and become more powerful. Every single play through is different because you have to choose from a random pool of power ups during each adventure. Cons: It can be a little complicated getting started. The power ups are a choice but it gives a title (Headshot) and a picture to show a representation of what the power up does but there's no description to help.

Very good. The controls are tight. But please remove the energy system. Or at least reduce the energy used in each game. And for a roguelike where a player's instinct is to press play right after losing, they dont want to be limited to a couple of games. It's just not a good system coupled with genre. So please, remove it. Or create a new system of managing time played. Just don't let the energy system hamper game time. It's a really bad system. But everything else is well done.

Great game. Finally, something different. It's simple to pick up, but challenging as you go up. You move your character with one finger; he automatically shoots. You go from room to room killing all the enemies. When you die and start over, you relevel up again and try different skills. It's very fun. The only draw back is that once you deplete your energy, you have to wait (unless you pay) to keep playing. (You'd the developers would want to keep you playing). Unlimited plays = 5 star.

Good game with some key flaws. The energy system is bad. I'd much rather have the option to pay money to get that mechanic removed. I get that it's used to get money out of folks, but it's a huge bummer that's the way the game tries to do it. It'd also be nice to have the option to continue using ads vs the gems. I also feel like at some point, they just overload enemies vs making them more challenging. Outside of those gripes, it's a really well done game that's kept me entertained.

The game is really fun and addicting, awesome that you don't need internet connection, and the combination of RPG elements with mobile devices is really well done. The main problem I have with the game is the enemies. As you advance you see nice combos of enemies, but the only way to really get stronger is to shoot out a hailstorm of projectiles. This is very annoying because as you fire a lot of projectiles you have to somehow see the enormous amount of enemy projectiles coming from the enemies

Challenging, but also engaging... The lack of time limits on levels is so nice. It is a tad time consuming if you get good, so set aside time to play it rather than whipping it out when you're bored or waiting for something - however if you do need to stop, the pause feature is there for you edit- I got a lucky break and got past a very difficult chapter, and now I'm stuck! I wish you could go back and play previous chapters, even if the drop rates for items was lower, I'd still be able to play

Love the game so far. One if the best mobile games I have ever played really. The variety is awesome. The reason I cant give it 5 stars would be the energy system. It needs reworked or something. Only giving me one run an hour is too low and only being able to bank 4 total runs is not much. Also, give me the ability to modify controls. The visual is too large and sometimes obscures the bottom part of the screen. Fix that and we will be at 5 stars.

Definitely needs some balancing. The double burrowing snake bosses on the 3rd world are MAD over powered compared to everything else. Frustrating enough to stop playing for a while. And the regular sized ones need to stay out a hair longer as well. Otherwise a very fun game. Haven't had to spend money on it as I play casually. The ability to watch ads for a bit more game time and rewards is a nice way of doing it. It would be cool to see more items, weapons and armor added to the game.

Overall, fantastic game. The ads are optional and always give you in-game bonuses, which are nice. I'm taking off 1 star because I cannot get past the Barrens (Lv7? Room 9, where there are two boss enemies); normally, I wouldn't mind admitting that my skills just aren't good enough, but I'm pretty sure the game *sped up* just to make it so I couldn't dodge their attacks. I won't be spending money, so.... I'm out. I still recommend this game, though! Many hours of fun, and well designed overall.

Generally, I enjoy this game but a few suggestions. The hit boxes need to be fixed: I won't be anywhere near an AOE attack and it'll still hit me. Some of the bosses should be balanced: some of them are way too easy, others are way to hard. I'm also at the point where I have way too much coin and nothing to spend it on because main leveling takea so long. There are also still instances of frame rate/lag even when there aren't a ton of things happening on screen.

Pretty good game.  Extra points for the simplicity of their interface in that it really only requires one hand to play.  It's simple and easy to pick up, but fun.  That's the right balance you need for mobile games.  It starts to be a grind after you've completed a few levels because you really need to start leveling up your equipment to pass level 4.  I got by the first 2 levels in a couple days.  The 3rd level in another week and have been grinding it out on level 4 for the last month or so.  There are some ads here and there to get bonus stuff, which is kind of necessary to get gems for better equipment, but it's not overbearing.

For a game I found through Facebook, this is actually one that I enjoy playing. The game play is smooth and with it being a free game, watching ads is optional and doesn't affect your game play. Only reason I give it 4 stars is because everytime I open the game it won't let me click anything for about 20 seconds, like it's frozen but the animations and music are still going. Not sure if it's still loading or what but it's rather frustrating. Other than that, I really do like the game

I am only giving 4 stars because I feel like there are some bugs that need to be addressed. Overall this game is a fun, exciting, addicting game that will remind you of running a demon hunter in Diablo. Graphics are great and the enemies are just challenging enough to keep you interested but not so easy that you can memorize their attack patterns. One of the main bugs I have encountered is directly after defeating a boss it will act like you died and return to main screen. Couple others as well.

Great game in general, but advancement slows to a crawl if you aren't spending money, and would be at a dead stop without watching ads. The ads are optional, but you'll never get premium currency without them, and drop rates are so low for equipment that you simply wouldn't progress. On the up side, the game itself is really fun. The abilities you get are always different, so replayability is fantastic. Would be a 5 Star game if they improved the equipment drop rates.... significantly.

This game is fantastic. There are parts that are crazy hard as you get to higher stages but you can always go back and grind for better gear and levels. Lets be honest with ourselves: this is an RPG. And about the energy system: For every character level gained the energy bar should get a one point increase, and the recharge time should be just a little faster. And once youve drained the energy bar.... go outside, take a shower, have some food. Come on people, its just a game afterall...

This game is fun, don't get me wrong. But I feel the need to point out some deficiencies that really get on my nerves. Like monsters getting stuck in walls that are still able to attack you without any way of killing them. inconsistencies like being able to knock back an enemy with an attack and then the next run though (with the same upgrades) are able to run though your attacks. And taking damage even though I have the invincible star active. I think there's alot more polishing to do.

I wish you could reduce the size or opacity of the joystick, especially since it doesn't matter where you touch, on the screen, the button moves to where to started your swipe. It seems to always be in my way, especially after making it to levels where the monsters don't spawn until you're half way through the room, already.... So now they're all underneath this semi useless picture of a joystick and I have trouble seeing them. Overall, good game, I'm having fun. P2w doesn't interfere much.

Love the game, hate the ads! Recent updates have helped smooth out progression so you're not hitting walls as often.. and the new events keep the grind a little more interesting. But the same updates have made the ads worse and more frequent, and they're the real grindfest to deal with. Yes, they're optional, but the rewards are valuable and it feels like half the progress is lost by skipping them. I haven't paid for anything in this game, but I would gladly pay for an ad-free option to keep the rewards and skip the wait, but there doesn't seem to be a purchase for it.

it's a well made game with good, one-finger UI and interesting, dynamic mechanics. The upgrade path is rather slow, though, and the paid upgrades are very expensive. I usually buy an upgrade or two to support the devs, but the $1 purchase is essentially worthless, and the next one is $7 and kind of maybe ok. Overall could use some more features and a quicker progression path, but very fun nonetheless.

Really great game. Pretty generous and not terribly in your face with in-app purchases. Don't get me wrong, there are still quite a bit of in-app purchases opportunities, but the game rarely makes you feel like you HAVE to purchase anything (at least so far - I'm on stage 7). Great gameplay loop. Can be frustrating with the amount of projectiles on screen causing me to misread one of my projectiles for the enemies. Overall, a very fun game and one of the very few kept on my phone.
replyContent: We will gradually improve the various systems in the game to enhance the player's game experience. We have recorded your Suggestions and fed back to the planner. If you have any other Suggestions and ideas, please feel free to contact us at archero@habby.fun.

content: This is a great game. It does have its flaws, it's slow progress and very difficult, but it has great graphics, constantly building and getting better. But my main issue is once I got a new phone and everything transferred over, all of my progress went with it. It took weeks to get where I was and now i have to redo it. Not happy. But overall i like the game. Just dont switch phones if you want to play it.

Overall, it is an excellent game with a good concept, but there are some connectivity issues (taking a long time to load something, getting stuck trying to get a reward, etc.). When this gets fixed, I will gladly give it a 5‚òÜ rating. Also, it isn't impossible to progress contrary to what some people have said about this, just takes good strategy to do so

A great game for those who like to see how far they can go every round. The controls are a little stange as it's a "joystick" style but you can put your finger anywhere on the screen and the joystick will move to your finger location but still have to move your finger around like a joystick. Other than that it's not too bad of a game. Definently a good time waster.

The start of the game is great. Super fun to pick up and play for a bit. I have made it to chapter 7 but I have been stuck for months now. From other reviews, chapter 7 seems to not have any issues addressed. I have all heroic gear max level and still cant get past 7-6. They at least need more coins to drop mid-level so your character can get more upgrades but it is frustrating to say the least.

This game is remarkable! It is so much fun to play! Yes the energy system could be longer but it helps me put it down. Really the only complaint I have is the difficulty curve but it is all part of the game! I also just need to Get Good haha. I will warn, the controls can be very frustrating and change targets which gets me killed all the time.

It is a fun game and I enjoy it but when I have the chance to spin I ALWAYS end up with currency. I'm tired of currency and I know it sounds ironic but I want power ups. It'd be nice if the chances of receiving currency were dropped. Also, can mobs be less annoying; less hard. The first few stages aren't easy at all being a 'starting sequence'.

the game is really really fun, but there is a need for a few features. possibly character customization, more purchasable items with coins, and a better leveling system when you're not in the dungeons. The gameplay is challenging and addicting but a little unrewarding. I especially agree with the energy system not improving as you reach higher levels. I could spend hours grinding this game. Dungeon 7 is still nearly impossible. added an extra star because the changes have been good keep it up!

wow! one of the best games I've played on a phone since smart phones have been out. Addicting gameplay, cool graphics, fun upgrades. There are a lot of things I'm missing out on though. I really want stats in this game; how many monsters I've killed, how many times I've died, how I've died, how many times I've played, hours etc. I also want to be able to exchange equipment at random at least. I hate leveling up something while I have so many other options in the armory.

Probably the best game I've played, but it has gotten extremely difficult to pass chapters once you get to a certain point. There was an update saying the difficulty would be lowered and more items would drop, but i honestly don't think it worked for me.. **been stuck on a chapter now for weeks and the app crashes every once in a while

I quit playing awhile ago as there was a massive difficulty spike combined with energy system made it unplayable. After downloading the game again and with all the new content is now a much more enjoyable experience so far. While I still dislike the energy system (I understand it is a way to keep people playing) In my two days of playing the game took a very big step foward from what it was. Keep it up guys!

Overall this is a great game. There are plenty of ads shoved in your face, but they all typically offer good rewards for viewing them. The pacing is...questionable. In one level you can feel overpowered, then later in the same level you'll just get dominated for no reason. The combat is extremely concise and the abilities are fun to experiment with. Enemies broadcast their attacks when necessary and deaths usually feel justified, aside from the aforementioned difficulty jumps. Coop needs work.

It's a really fun and addictive game. Keeps me coming back for more arcade action. Gets a little grindy, but pretty much what you'd expect. It is sad you can't go back to previous levels once complete, but there is a heroic mode you can unlock that plays them over again, just harder. Boy does this game eat your battery though. Don't wander too far from an outlet. Also may not be good for away from home gaming to kill time unless you don't mind draining you whole battery down.

actually pretty fun! this is a good time killer and the progression give it decent replay value. the enemies vary and do get more difficult. but once you learn the patterns of their attacks it becomes easier to advance. you dont get gear that often so this is some grinding involved and you cant play too many games before you become frustrated. which is good, it keeps you coming back. the animated graphics are good and the game runs smooth. will definitely be keeping this. well done so far!

Fun Game, the only problem I have is that good upgrades seem to be getting more and more rare to get. I went multiple games without one attack upgrade so by the time I get to level 30 I cant kill anything without dodging fire, bombs, arrows the whole time and end up dying. You should be able to use the tokens you get for enemy kills and be able to purchase upgrades you want. Or have an option to pay to reroll the upgrades so I have a fighting chance.

I enjoy the game greatly. One upgrade to the leveling system I would like to see though is the ability to reroll the upgrades. Could be an ad opportunity or a gem spend. Also, as an upgrade to co-op mode, it would be great if there was a random connect capability for those who don't have many friends who play the game. That way you could just connect to an open session without the hassle of a code. You could keep the code pairing system for people who want to connect to specific individuals.

What I like most is the scaling difficulty does not have have any spikes where you are forced to buy premium items to keep keep advancing. The total resource cost of upgrading is very high which does take away some of the fun because of the need for frequent grinding. A very fun game that is easy to pick up and play. I would rate at 5* but have been unable to match at all for multiplayer/duo.

One of my favorite games, but after a time you hit a wall. You max out at lvl 80 for your gear, and there are no higher combined levels. So at a certain point you just give up, no point in continuing even though there are levels to beat, because it is impossible to do so. I've bought packs and gems, but the reward for use at high levels is miniscule. Granted, until you get to that point this really really is a great game. I highly recommend trying it. I just wish the updates kept up with us.

It is such a fun game. The stopping to shoot and upgrades along the way make it unique from other bullet hells. The only problem I have with it is that I absolutely hate the energy system. I JUST WANT TO PLAY YOUR GAME. Energy systems are a curse to mobile games and whoever came up with it should be hung. Anyways great game terrible energy thank you.

It's a great game for the RPG'er who doesn't mind the slow grind. Getting higher level equipment is a monotonous process. However, the controls are easy and the random skills each time you play make it interesting and challenging. It also allows you to try different combos to see what works for you best. I love the new characters and level up process - good touch.

I really love this! It sort of reminds me of the binding of Isaac in a way, where you can get a choice of three random items when you level up The only thing I don't like is the energy system, you only get to play like 4 times until it has to recharge If I could make a suggestion, maybe add more maximum energy, or maybe a mini-game in the menu so you can do something while you're waiting for your energy? I really like this app tho üëå

It is really fun and addicting. There is a diverse amount of enemies which are all easy by themselves but tend to be challenging when put with 2 or 3 other types of enemies. I was looking for something close to the tank game in wii play which it got fairly close to. The things I dont like is leveling up (overall not in match) takes a long time. There is also so many ads (1-3 a match) taking 20 to 30 seconds each. You get bored easily if you dont spend money.

I love this game, but there's a few issues. One, when you first open the game, it doesn't count towards the logging in daily quest, so you have to close the app and open it a second time. Two, I wish they would remove duplicate skills from the "pool" as you progress in levels. Getting two duplicate skills out of 3 doesn't feel very good. Lastly, they need to upgrade patrol rewards more, the longer you play the game, the more gold starved you are. We need a reliable way of getting more gold.

Honestly, this game is awesome. I like the tons of different varients of monsters, items, etc. Also no invasive ads, only optional ones. Finally its offline compatible, which is really cool for when you don't have much to do. My suggestion is to fix the energy, you could either decrease how much is used, or increase how much you have. Overall a really good game, which is rare nowdays. 9/10 Edit: The game is still good, it's just the stages are way to hard! 7/10

Very enjoyable game, and I rarely find a mobile game that keeps my attention like this one does. only problems I can find are some balancing issues with some of the enemies. Biggest issue I'm finding right now is the Treant boss in the 4th chapter is far too overpowered. Its speed and randomness leave little openings to attack it, and it deals very high damage, making it very hard to progress.

Fun gameplay, but ruined by repetition. The core gameplay is pretty enjoyable, the shooting and dodging provides a decent challenge without feeling unfair. Unfortunately there are very few new mechanics introduced, and the game becomes a repetitive grind fairly quickly. You can progress without spending money, which is a plus, but it's a significant time investment.

An excelent game, to the point of being subgenre-defining. However, it is not without flaws: there are far too many abilities that are just "this other ability that you have had access to all along, but with severe drawbacks (only at low health, for a few seconds at a time, when you kill something, etc). Additionally, while most of the upgrades are relatively clear just from the icon, there are a lot that are not so clear, and you can't find out what they do except by taking them (fix this pls)

The game is really good and the controls are really easy to use. It would be a five out of five but I fell that that difficulty of the game is almost too much. At one point I had to delete the game because I literally couldnt get any further no matter what I tried. So I think it would be useful to get more items and currency, and to get it easier from playing through. I think that the higher you get the rarer the items, but maybe 1-3 equipment should be almost guaranteed on each run.

The game is very fun, but almost too challenging. The enemies can easily hit you with 3-500 damage in one go, meaning you're done for in like 5 hits while it takes 7-8 to kill one enemy. You have to be lucky with upgrades to really get anywhere, but even with my attack and crit damage way up, the same exact enemies it took 2 hits to kill, now take 10. Those upgrades should be making it easier, but it seems as your power level upgrades, so does theirs, which is frustrating.

This app needs a little work. The app, not the game. The game is there, but loading happens in the middle of a stage that you are currently playing, so you get a 1-2 second freeze on inputs, but the enemies continue to kill you which results in a lot of unfair deaths. very frustrating at the higher levels, after you've spent gems.

I was disappointed that the battle pass only lasts a season. Also feels like I'm not making progress when I can't improve my gear. A system where equip can be broken down and turned into something else would be more engaging, if the loot drops increase as well. Otherwise great, like the challenge, told all my friends about it.

Great idea, awkward implementation. I don't mind how slowely items build or how difficult it gets. What I DO mind, however, are all of the nonsense abilities that get added to the pool of abilities. And pets; dear god why pets. I ended up unequipping the pets so that they wouldn't cause so much extra clutter on the screen and it significantly helped me to better see and avoid things. This game is a wonderful idea, and I'd love to see it get fixed. For now, I'm uninstalling.

I really really love the concept of the game and the way it plays. I love the power ups but I hate the energy system and the fact that you pretty much need to spend more or progress very slowly. I'm not against spending money but when they money is gambling it's a no go for me. Hades is a great PC game with a similar concept but only cost $10 and you a nice steady flow!!!!

Potentially one of the best games I've ever played on mobile. It takes the funnest aspects of IO games and let's you collect exp to level up to unlock a new perk that enhances your character. This would be my favorite game on mobile by far if it weren't for the energy system. You're only provided with 20 energy and that number can't increase at a base level. It takes 5 energy to play a game. That means 4 games then it takes an hour to build up again. Still a fun game but it COULD be the BEST

Its a very fun game. Easy to pick up yet hard to put down. I would like to offer some constructive critisism though. Lower enemy damage by about 25-50. It will make this feel a bit more balanced. (At least I think so) Also add the level creation we see in the ads for this. Its already nearly the same as what we are shown but it would help the games popularity and replayability.

Solid game. I've spent more than I care to admit as getting resources the legit way takes way too damn long. With that said, I can't go higher than a 4 for the following reasons: 1. There needs to be a true ad free feature. Tie it in with a subscription, make it a monthly recurring charge, but there needs to be a true zero ad option. 2. Be able to buy scrolls. The drop rate is too random and too inconsistent. The level of grind to get items to level 80 is truly a pain.

A lot better than I thought from the ads. I had no idea this was a progressive level by level game. I would like to see a PVP option added, maybe in Archero 2? Another thing that could be added is an in game directory, I had to Google for any useful information. I really like the controls, very easy to maneuver single handedly which is great for mobile games. I did wish that the leveling system wouldn't be all random and instead only unlocking skills was random; this would add customization.

A great solo, dunegon crawler game. Lots of gear and heroes to upgrade. The only problem is that progressively throughout the chapters you do end up with worse set of abilities to run through rather than make it better. So in turn making it kind of worse to progress through the game in a sense which no longer makes it about skill, but about alot of RNG.

Archero feels like a pay-to-play cell phone game, meaning if you dump like 50 dollars into it, you will have a smooth experience instead of a grindy, frustrating one. That being said, I'll admit I got hooked. I spent 2.99USD for a little booster pack in the beginning and the games kept me interested for weeks since. Not a lot of interruptions with forced ads (you decide if you want to see them or not). That alone is a huge plus in my opinion. Overall, I'm glad I downloaded it and gave it a try.

Very fun, very polished game. The combat feels great, the enemies are varied and the game is just fun. Ads are sparse and optional. The only blight on this otherwise 5/5 game is that for some reason, they felt the need to include an "energy" system requiring you to wait or spend money to play. It's really out of place for an offline, solo game, tacked on for no reason other than encouraging spending. The limit is absurd: one run per hour. Please stop encouraging me to download the cracked APK.

Actually a fun game. There are no mandatory or forced ads, just optional to gain boosts. I only have two issues: 1) Energy system. This is not the kind of game that needs an energy system. Shouldn't you want me to play the game more ü§î? 2) Not easy if you're colorblind. This goes for all bullet-hell type games. Sucks if you literally can't see a specific attack. A toggleable colorblind mode would be helpful. All in all I would recommend this game to anyone.

Very fun game with easy ways to improve. As you advance it definitely gets harder as any good game should. I just go back to the easier levels with a a low weapon that I haven't used and play them with it to learn and it has kept the game intriguing. Ways to improve - allow the co-op mode to be with someone random who also wants to play. Allow multiple equipment items to be dismantled simultaneously as it is a pain to do them one by one.

Love the game. Been playing for almost a year now couldn't be happier with the new upgrades you've made. I run into alot of "network error try again later" messages though. This makes it hard to redeem stuff I've won and honestly in the long run makes it difficult to properly participate in the game as a whole. I dontkn if there are others like me out there but please fix the bugs. Other than that literally the o lying game I play. Congrats on one year hope to see many more

Every since I've updated this game, I don't like it. It's glitchy to the point where I'm stuck, but the monsters are still whooping my ass. I see a monster shoot at me and run, and the projectile's trajectory follows me, and when I'm hitting a weak enemy, it pushes through to get that final death blow, that takes a 3rd of my HP. But the lack of ads makes it a worth while play

Great game I'm really enjoying it. If you're reading this and asking, "Should I download this game?" The answer is yes. It's awesome. However, there are several Ads that crash the game. Which makes it sketchy if you're trying to do an Ad based revive, if the game crashes you lose all progress in the room. This has happened to me a few times in the difficult rooms which has now forced me to always use gems, just in case, which aren't free.

The game is really fun! However, there is a bug on expedition stages (stage 90 most recently) where the player character (At least Atreus and Urasil) are bigger than they should be. Other than that (and still hoping for a female hero that can be obtained through coins), I love the simple controls and how smooth the gameplay can be (despite how frustrated I get going against enemy Scythe Mages! ;P ).

The game is pretty fun. The controls are simple and the gameplay is quite easy ro understand. My biggest problem here is that its a solo game. I know that may have been the goal but adding a little bit of coop, or one v one/online, might add a little spice to the game. Since you need internet for opening things, maybe use it for something else as well. Either way its a great game. I would give it a 5 star if its a bit more than just that.

Fun game with pretty unique mechanics. I return to it every few weeks/months. It is fun, but at this point the game is merely repetitive grinding with no clear goal in mind. Some of the prices for premium content are a little high ($18.99 for a fighter without clearly explained advantages over free-to-play alternatives comes to mind). Something new (at this point in time!) is definitely needed; add something fresh instead of the same weekly refreshing of quest-esque tasks to keep us coming!

Gameplay is overall pretty fun, however from a design standpoint the game is very unbalanced. First off a successful run is determined by getting very particular talent upgrades when you level. If you don't get them you cannot win. The lack of ability to AIM really sucks. I often find my character shooting EXACTLY the wrong enemy which is just poor design. The player needs more ability to influence what is attacked. Also sometimes the game will crash and you'll have to redo a hard room and die.

Good, but I noticed that the hero throws his or her weapon to the location where mobile enemies have already been, instead of leading the target. This makes for a much longer battle level, and an ineffectively thrown main weapon; and it's convenient that it seems many enemies walk in a diagonal path, which is a recipe for many missed shots. Other than that...very nice!

Love the game but a few things I'd like to point out. Number one is the fact that I just beat the third dungeon on hero mode yesterday and now after it says "connecting" it made the third dungeon say 19 out of 20 instead of 20 out of 20. So I'm suggesting you guys fix that "synchronizing data" stuff and make this a completely offline game. Number two when the synchronizing data pops up I noticed it drains your playing energy which is also kind of messed up. So I really suggest fixing that stuff.

Hate to do the cliche thang, but: This game is very simple to learn, but (nearly) impossible to master. What I particularly enjoy is the mix of multiple genres built into a low-resource mobile platform. Dungeon crawling with loot drops? Yep. Loot that affect both the visual & gameplay? Yep. RNG that makes every run unique... got it. Varied enemy types that can create chaos... got it. Gameplay that rewards... got it. Only thing it's missing? Pay to win. Look forward to playing for awhile.

it's a fun game, there are unique power ups when you level and progress in the dungeon. you can equip and level up your gear after you die or finish the level. the only down side is the "energy" mechanic. it takes way too long to re-fill. ultimately they are trying to force you to spend money to get energy back.

Definitely needs some sort of music in battle, and some audio adjustments between sounds. Players want to be able to use audio cues without their ears being bombarded with explosions and jump noises that are much louder than other sounds. Otherwise, it's a great game. Very satisfying, and the gameplay is on point.

Great game, one of the best I've played in a while. However, can ya'll make the auto aim a bit better? If theres an enemy further away from me than an enemy behind a wall that's closer, make it shoot at the enemy further away from me. This happens frequently when I'm trying to shoot an enemy further from me but it's instead shooting fences which have flower pots enemies behind them.

overall a very good game, my only problem is the aiming system. most of my deaths are because the game decides to aim at the person who across the map instead of right in front of me, or I'll move closer to the enemy I want to kill first, but decides to aim at anything else. The game is very fun and addictive and wish it had an option to change the aiming system, but that's about it for me. everything works the way it's supposed to and the only reason I give a 4star is because of the aim.

Combat system is imbalanced. Relies too much on big hits and accuracy. With an accuracy of 94% a fighter can miss multiple times in a row. Accuracy should simply reduce damage not miss entirely. Enemy shouldn't be able to pass a fighter when touching an adjacent hex (or at least slow them down). Quick fights shouldn't result in dead heros when vastly overpowering the enemy. I could come up with a dozen more improvements to make the game less frustrating and keep the difficulty the same.

Its a really fun game with a great concept that takes a very simple control scheme and pushes player skill. However the difficulty and currency spikes between Chapters 3 through 5 are insane. Equipment upgrades become completely meaningless as the damage is only going up by 5 each time while enemies are taking huge chunks of your HP, and sometimes you just cant avoid damage. Some of the skill upgrades are worthless. Which you get is random and cant be taken back, as well as being level capped.

So, I saw this game in ads for other games and thought it looked interesting. So far, yeah, i can say I'm enjoying myself. About the only real complaint i have is just how slow F2P progress can be. Unless you're REALLY good at the game as far as dodging, etc, you have to throw yourself repeatedly at the same dungeon over and over until you finally get a very lucky run or enough upgrades using tokens (or whatever the gold arrow currency is called) to compensate. Overall, 4/5. ^^

New edit. This game has come a long way and has been very enjoyable. So here's a major fix you should consider. Maybe don't auto load the level up screen at the end of a level BEFORE ALL THE ENEMY PROJECTILES HAVE GONE AWAY!!!! I got very far into one of the harder levels and was on my last bit of health. I would have succeeded in dodging a very slow remaining projectile but no the level had to happen then and there leaving me to get struck by it and subsequently lose. Insulting. Fix it please.
replyContent: Hello! Thanks for your comment, I have feedback to the team, please look forward to our new version.Thanks, have a nice day!

content: This game is incredibly fun, but there is a problem with the progression system. I've played at least once every other day for several months, and I can't progress much further because the enemies deal sooo much damage. I currently have 1500 max health, and the average projectile from an enemy does 600. I enjoy most of the game, but I can only handle so many deaths to the tree stump boss.

having to restart the game every time it needs to load or sync is not fun  Edit: the Network seems more stable now! thank you Habby Crew!  the actual game is fun, it would be nice to possibly customize your hero by having more drops of items that you can fuse and build. also seems like a no-brainer to use ranged weapons, so if someone wanted to go the melee route, there should be incentive.
replyContent: Hello, the network has been repaired. Do you have to close the background to restart?

content: Gameplay is great so the grind is, actually, enjoyable. Genuinely able to play free. Great game <3 I have noticed a few bugs: 1. The lightning upgrade only works on the first hit with double-shot (subsequent attacks do not proc). 2. The option to watch an ad for 3,000 tokens, from the wizard that pops up after a room clear in a dungeon, does not actually grant any tokens. I've stopped watching adds for this reward and it may be impacting earnings off ads if others are noticing it.

I have been playing this game for about 2 months and overall I believe it is quite fun and addicting. My only negative feedback is the length of time it takes to level up weapons. I have spent a few bucks, more than I will admit to and I feel stuck at times just replaying the same levels over and over. Perhaps with the new update that issue will be adressed.

The game is fun, just gotta say, dont put the energy as 25 when it takes 5 to play a level. Thats just 5 plays then. I get that you get 1 energy back every so many minutes, but at that point you might as well just expand the amount of time it takes to get energy rather than have it as a maybe multiple of 5. Or allow energy to stock pile with the same recharge rate. The idea is neat, although its another case of the adverts not matching up with the game, still ended up being fun.

I have blue keys, why do I have to watch an ad to use them? Also you should never make enemy projectiles the same color as the background. It makes it difficult to see which makes the game difficult artificially. You can have attacks that are hard to dodge, but you want to make sure that if the player gets hit, it's the players fault, not because it's of something out of the players control. I am quite happy with this game overall. I wish I had more space to type a full review.

Great concept, great time passer too. Very addictive. I would LOVE to see like a "dungeon mode" with multiplayer, where you can go solo, or up to 3 other people where you can fight through rooms and bosses and find treasures with awesome loot. Maybe also add some classes with powers to assist your team. I have great ideas for this game. Overall even if my ideas arent taken up, still a great game, just dont see it being too long lived as is.

Tons of fun with very manageable ads and progression. 11/10. EDIT: After playing for roughly three months, I'll say the game does get practically impossible to progress after the dragon and evil witch. You're basically out of luck unless you get weapon specific upgrades. The element-based powers aren't very resourceful on their own, especially since their damage seems to be fixed / scale little to at all, and I haven't seen any weapon or armor bonuses give element damage.

Overall, Archero is a lot of fun. The upgrades are great but rare except for the scrolls to upgrade them. There are no ads that you're forced to watch but.you get 5 wheel spins per day for watching an Ad. The one flaw is their energy system. It requires 5 energy to play a board, but takes 6 or 7 minutes to replenish 1 energy so you'll be waiting a bit to play unless you spend real money. I would love to see some sort of clan/leaderboard system implemented.

Game is a lot of fun, but only when you have perfect internet connection. This game requires constant perfect connection to the internet whoch makes no sense, theres nothing about each level that needs data. The monsters do so much damage that if you lose connection for a second (even with full bars) you'll die. This needs to be fixed. UPDATE This issue seems to have been fixed. Been playing this game for a long time. Have had a lot of fun.

it's good for play but too hard to farm

Alright so I've been playing the game since it came out in 2019, so please hear what I have to say. Yes, this game is a P2W only in the sense that IF you want to unlock EVERY character, EVERY weapon, EVERY level, and upgrade EVERY weapon and character to its max level, yes, you will need to put money into the game. Is it NECESSARY to unlock every weapon, character and level to enjoy the game? No. The game is a grind, it does take lots of time. But that does not mean it isn't fun.

content: I've been playing the gsme for about a year and i must say, it's one of the best mobile games i've ever played. Great time killer, fun, and easy to learn.
