Good game

Review was one star, but after playing opinions change. Only real gripe is some elements are weird. Pvp is a good example. And coop your hero level/equip doesn't get taken into account, but in pvp it does??? Bc being fair matters more in coop then pvp? At least in coop I'm not basically gambling with special resource. That and some heroes can ONLY be bought. I don't mind making them difficult to get, easy to buy. But putting that barrier in is weird. It's the only part that feels pay to play.
replyContent: Dear Archer, We are sorry to hear that you've been having a negative experience. I've passed on this feedback and we'll do our best to ensure you have a more enjoyable gaming experience. Thank you for your feedback.

content: Updated Review: recent updates have been way better at helping the players out with the rough grind. Recent events have been kinda lack luster though. The most recent big event for the new weapon was horrible. The grind was insane and you'd be lucky to get any materials during the runs even though it said Normal/Hero mode. Been around for a while and know Habby can do better than these latest events.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback of the battle pass and the clan. We will submit it to our tech team for review.

content: M√¥≈æe by≈•
Love the game it fun to play and it's just good overall.
Fun game I like to play but it's hard to get good gear
Idk
Fun.
Yes sir
I love this game it's the best
I üëç

I really like playing this game. But why i can't connect it with my facebook. I want to play it on my new phone. I aldy collected a lot of things and hero i don't wanna start from the one again. How can i do lah...
Fun game, easy to pick up
Its good but kinda repetitive.all you do is kill monsters. But you can do 1v1,s so i give it 4 stars
Cool Game!!..
A high quality base mobile game
Fun but challenging
This game is amazing and so addictive. But please make an offline mode. Like a horde mode, or endless mode that you don't need wifi.
Rwally great game i love it
Lot of ads but fun to play

I've really enjoyed the game. I got rid of it three times for space, only to go and download it again a week later. I have yet to spend money on it after two years. The ads are really low compared to other mobile games and the tech support get on any issues that may arise, to the point of contacting me with-in two hours of my complaint and on that time they resolved my problem. Thank you developer team.

Been playing the game since September 2019, maybe around 95% of all the days from then up until now, ive been pretty much free 2 play, spent maybe $200 lol. I don't have a single mythic, but there better be another upgrade by the time I get one, I'd like to see a different kind of upgrade that's obtainable unlike how we've seen before

Surprisingly fun. I was not forced to watch ads at all. There are free coin or upgrades for watching ads (I skipped it). It actually depends on ur skill, u have to dodge attacks and be a bit strategic. It might get reoititve after a while, but it is fun, no forced ads, and polished. The game is Rouge lite, u move ur character from room to room killing all variety of enemies. It auto shoots when u r not moving, so u r mainly dodging the enemy attacks, fun

This is a solid app to sink some time into if you want to play a combat game which requires skill. The challenge in the combat comes from needing to move to avoid the projectiles but having to stay still to fire. On the monetization, the prices are high but I haven't been tempted to buy anything. You can get a fair amount of materials for free or by watching ads to upgrade your character. I don't feel pressure to purchase anything so that's a plus. It's fun to just shoot away and dodge.

This game is a fantastic attention sink. The game play is a bullet-hell shooter, single-stick auto-fire. You start over at the beginning of each run and gain abilities throughout so you get to play with different builds each time. Where it really shines is outside of the dungeons, there are so many currencies and characters and rewards and items and runes and gems and pets and so on, and they can all be collected and powered up. The reward loop is fantastic and generous. Some ads.

I wish that the monster-treasure event is easier, cause I keep dying on the 1st-3rd wave. I also wish that there were better power balance for hero battles, aka: first to hit the other player 10 times wins, cause I keep on losing due to Higher-level players with insane attack speed. And please path these bugs: 1. Opposing player turns invisible, and, 2. Opposing player teleports (Visual issue, they are actually in the same spot) Otherwise, I love it! :-)

This game is a lot of fun. The levels and monsters ramp up at a fair pace. The controls are responsive, and there's no lag, no matter how many monsters, or attacks are going off. I don't mind the ads, because they always grant money, gems or upgrades, to help you progress, or you can just avoid them. Its not a pay to win, but they do have fairly priced, in game shop items.

Been playing this for like a year on and off. Haven't spent a dime in app. Completely free to play and always room to progress without spending money. It just seems like an option if you want to. I give props to the devs, this is how monetization in a free to play game should be. Games addicting too at times when you get into the hero stages.

Super addictive time killer. Lots of ways to play, and customization. A little slow if you're not willing to watch videos. There is a pay to play element, but manly to speed things up, not a lot of exclusives you have to pay for.

One of the greatest action games, lot of choices of character and attack tools. It is an amazing experience, once you play you will not realize where the time went with all the fun you can have in there. Character choices, attack choices, stages, online gaming if you like that. It's old school style of armor, swords, bow arrows, rings, stones etc. Learn to upgrade tools, rings, armor using blacksmith. One of the other advantages of this game is that it is light on your phone memory

Well made game. Good variety of enemies, rooms, powerups, and bosses. Small bits of lag, but only when the screen is littered with enemies/projectiles (which isn't often). Good balance of luck and skill. Only complaint is that energy takes a long time to refresh, 12 minutes per energy. Maybe 10 minutes would be better, but I would love to see 5 minutes per energy.

Interesting concept! Great game to pass time on a road trip (not driving), or just needing to pass the time. I think it'd be interesting to see the joystick setup have options. Example: Have the options to keep the run/fire option or have 2 options for run & fire. So you could either go "Hard" and be strategic with when to fire (how it is now), or "Easy" and be able to run & gun at the same time. Other than that, I like the concepts of everything else.

So far so good. It's a fantastic rogue-lite (I don't know if it's procedurally generated) shooter very much in the line of The Binding of Isaac. You move around the screen, dodging enemies and returning fire, collect gold and Gems representing XP, and when you level up your choose an ability or stat buff. I don't have a good feeling about this energy system, though. I haven't hit the limit yet, but you start with the meter at 40/20, if I recall correctly. I will update my review accordingly.

I think this is a great concept and really enjoyable to play. While many games like this feel heavily loaaded with ads, this one feels completely different with the majority of its ads being entirely optional. The way the gameplay works, it feels as though every time you play it is a slightly different experience and I enjoy learning what abilities work well together.

So far I like the game play, it's different than anything I've played before and has potential. Downside is that i get server connection errors when trying to collect any of the rewards, or perform any of the upgrades. I'll give it a day or so to sort that out and play without that benefit for now. Edit: that network issues resolved after rebooting my phone and I believe they had something to do with my VPN. This game provides good passive fun.
replyContent: This might be due to the network conditions. Please try it out under a stable network condition and see how it goes.Thank you very much, have a nice day!

content: First off, the game is fun and challenging enough to play for a few hours or multiple weeks. However, I've spent a dozen hours or more playing the game and have some suggestions for improvement. Some enemy attacks are difficult to see in the dark stages. Some enemies shoot in random directions, and getting cornered by even one of these is too RNG to be fun. Additionally, boss fights sould not require luck to win, but many have unpredictable attacks that cannot be dodged intentionally.

This is a very solid top down shooter type of game. You actually have to learn creature patterns and how to counter them, and you can actually see yourself improving as every level builds on how you improved in the last one. It may take many runs to finally beat a level, and maybe a bit of RNG, but every time you figure out how to combat something makes you feel accomplished. If you're looking for a challenging game with a bit of a grind, this is it.

Fantastic game, highly addictive, be careful. Can be challenging at times, but feels really fair so far. Good skill can make up for lack of items, and vice versa. I gave occasionally had problems with ads not playing. The only time it was bad was when I tried to watch an ad for a revive, but it didn't play. I then had to exit the game, and I gained nothing from that run. If it keeps occurring, I will drop my review down, but it hasn't happened since resetting my phone.

Very fun. Theres few games that keep me as intrigued as this one has. Also, when does the new season start? I'm eager to get the battle pass once the new season begins, little confused on when it begins. But like I said, this game doesn't throw tons of rewards and screens at you that take 20 mins everyday just to get through, its just the right amount. Also, as far as pay to win, I havent seen it here. Yes it makes it easier, but if you play it right not a penny has to be spent to progress.

I'm having a really tough time with double bosses, they seem a little less skill/reaction time based and more luck heavy. Slightly frustrating. Some rooms also become incredibly busy and hard to navigate due to the hordes of enemies. However, that may be my fault for not clearing the previous waves better. Besides that it's fantastic, and those complaints are minor. Don't bend to the people crying about the energy system, its perfect the way it is. Makes me excited to come back when its refilled

This game is highly addictive. Simple controls but the game play itself is entertaining enough to let time fly. Some other reviews mention the difficulty sky rocketing unfairly but I don't think this is meant to be beaten overnight. It takes some skill and learning with rng to get through the later levels, but it's not impossible. It can definitely feel pay to win; however it's still very playable without spending any money.

Surprisingly challenging, nice addicting game that does require just enough skill to keep you playing but not too much to push people away. I don't like that choosing skills is a lottery. Besides that, when everything lines up, it's great. The game also gives a decent amount of currency without ads which is great. Almost gave it 4 stars but this definitely plus 90% of the games in the play store to shame. Other developers should look close.

This game is AWSOME!!! I love it so much. you dont feel the need to play it constantly. if you do want to play it constantly. I get that it is annoying that I have to wait a little bit to get more energy, but once you get farther along, and I dont fully understand why, its great. I play after classes during free time and I get to like level 20 to 30. I I have basically no critiques. it combines all the good bits of games seamlessly. Ads aren't a big part and only pop up when asked. I LOVE IT!!üòç

I absolutely love this game. I have been playing every chance I get for 2 weeks now. the game is incredibly challenging, while easy to learn. There are no ads, unless you volunteer to watch them, endless combos of skills per run, new equipment, upgradable equipment, pets, etc etc. The controls are intuitive and easy to learn and its playable with one hand. This game has it all and it has been an absolute blast. Only downside I have found, is the energy. It takes a bit long to regen. Great game!!

Overall a great game. You have to build up your character skills and armor and weapons to get far. Which is great for me because i like to take feel like I have achieved something when I pass a level. Not a whole lot of ads. If you want more energy or gems they give you up to 4 ads a day. If I could change anything it would be the energy cap. Takes 1 hour to get 5 energy and it caps at 20. It would be better if it capped at 25 or even 40. However, 20 is good because it slows down the game. :l

I never review games, but man is this one addicting. I love that they only include ads for "extra" items and don't require them to play the game. There were some recent connectivity issues, and we were given gems (items you can use in-game) for experiencing it, and I thought that was awesome. Just please don't follow the route of so many other games and start adding mandatory ads!

This is one of the best mobile rouge-likes I've ever played. When you get a good run in it just feels good. The advertisements are elective for an extra boost, which is nice. This is an easy game to put a little time here and there as locking the screen will pause the action for you to resume later. Only gripe was that there was a max level in the first stage. This is likely a balance choice by the dev. It does not ruin the game and I understand why, but I wish we could get more buff stacks.

Insanely fun and addicting! The levels are challenging and exciting. The progression feels natural. You get to customize your experience each time with different choices in bonus powers each level. There is zero pressure to pay-to-win (!!!!!) and no mandatory ads. They choose to highly incentivize optional ads instead, which puts this game on an entirely different level from most games. Incredible job on this game! 10/5 stars from me!

Easy to learn, difficult to master. Pay for items but not to win. In today's market it's hard to find a game that offers you legitimate choices and doesn't just feel like an annoyance. I don't feel hampered by not paying, and I don't think it would feel like cheating if I did pay. Controls are simple, move to avoid projectiles and shift targets, stand still to fire. At later stages, there are so many effects on the screen that it's hard to tell what's friendly and what's hostile

PLEASE READ It's a challenging, fun and time passing game, however the energy system is poor. Either the 20 energy limit is too low or the time per energy is too high. This makes the game kind of pay to win by basically forcing the player to buy energy just to play, but it'll be a complete waste because as you advance you get overwhelmed with enemies making it nearly impossible to survive. Other than that, the game is well developed and entertaining. I look forward to future updates and events.

I love the game! It's a bit unique to me. I've never played a game like it. It's really interesting & although it has a bit of story, it's not exactly all about it. I just don't really understand how the levels work. Well, you start off just normal & go in the battle area as level one. You get to move around and get skills that aren't permanent every other level or so, they are only for before death & then you can use tokens to pay for lasting ones. It's fun, play it! No, I'm not a bot!

A very good mobile adaptation of ARPG type gameplay. Can pick up and play for short or long sessions. The energy system can be a bit frustrating but I actually appreciate it, it forces me to not play the game all the time and not brute force the difficulty curve. Controls are tight and satisfying. The interface is also good, and eases you into its features at a good pace.

Super fun and entertaining! One of the best games I've played so far. The game helps you to increase your skills as you play it. There are GoogleAds but only if you choose to watch, the rewards are pretty good and the videos are short. I haven't seen any bugs or problems while running the game. The beginning of the game can be "slow" but after you start reaching arena 3~4, you will be receiving more rewards after each game and you will go further faster (depending on your skill too!). 10/10

Overall this is one of my favorite games on mobile. The only thing that i would personally like to see changed is some of the upgrades. I feel like some of the circles, shield guard, holy touch, strong heart and similar upgrades doesn't perform well enough to be useful. Maybe if the circles turned a bit faster, and the shields were a bit bigger. Again, this is one of the best games available for mobile and I love everything else that game has to offer

When I first saw an ad for this it presented an almost tower defense approach (numerous enemies, narrow pathways, etc.) That's not what this is. I'm hoping we see something like that in that future. My only complaints are: Updates can't be rolled out fast enough (yes, I'm pouting over the new character I can't receive.) -also- The unnecessarily long grind:luck ratio required to progress. - and, lastly- Only the first character changes appearance depending on the equipment used.

Challenging, but fair. A great game to pass the time and test your reflexes. My only change would be to give the ability descriptions more detail when you press the pause button. Sometimes it can be difficult to optimize your build when you dont have any percentages or much other info to go off of than just the basic idea of each ability. Overall 5/5, I've already made multiple friends download it.

Absolutely love it! Best mobile game of 2019 in my opinion. Only a few complaints. 1st it's has an awful forced difficulty where you get random upgrades every level. This is fine on level 1 and 2, but the pool only gets bigger as you make it further in the game. We should be allowed to pick what is in that pool of upgrades and not be forced to use stuff that is useless for how we play. 2nd is the chests. Box 1 common and great. Box 2 rare and epic with a slight price increase take out the great!

A fun game with lots to do, different characters to unlock that have special abilities, weapons to suit your playing style, and a several perks you can get to help you pass the game. For me personally it isn't to challenging to the point where it's frustrating but it also isn't just a game that you can just leave. It's the right balance of challenge and casual that I enjoy.

I love it! I find the art beautiful though it's certainly simple. The player character and all those you encounter along the way are cute... And sometimes intimidating üòÑ. The levels go from very easy to more and more and MORE challenging. I am enjoying seeing my character's talents grow and experiencing all the different boosts and weapons and equipment and such. I'm having fun. Thank you. P.S. Is the developer willing to make it possible to slow down and navigate more carefully?

So far so good aside from a few crashes and ads for revive not playing, but these aren't big set backs since it saves your progress and the revive isn't always ad guaranteed anyway. It's a tough game because of random chance, but it's fun. My husband and I are kind of challenging each other for the lead between us. Also this game doesn't force you to pay ever. It hands out the gems often which alone is a reason to play since you don't have to pay for items in order to advance.

It's a very good game that often has you going back through the levels if you aren't strong enough. Yes you have to grind, but I find that's part of the fun. I see another review says enemies pop up underneath you, they do if you dont move out of the way. However there are ways to increase agility, which makes up for the amount of dodging you may have to do. I love the little pets and other characters you can unlock. Very well made and fun!

Superb game! I've been playing for over a month now and have had no complaints. Only ads when you want to revive or get more loot boxes. I really enjoy the concept of attacking when standing still and the skills are very cool and fun. I play every day and look forward to it. I've searched for more games but this one is the only one that has me hooked. Beautiful game 10/10

Great game! I wish and hope you tone down some of the mobs attacks. The fire breathing dragons are a little overpowered in my opinion. If their able to shoot through walls then their attack range shouldn't be that far. I also don't like that in the 2nd world the tornado throwers their attacks are very hard to see. The attacks kinda blend in with the ground when the screen gets pretty chaotic. But all in all it's a great game. Perfect balance between tough but easy to play.

All other game apps should take note - this is how you monetize a free game! Not inundated with constant ads between each level, they simply make it incentivizing - you can watch a quick 30 second ad to gain valuable stuff to progress faster in the game.. or, if you choose not to, you can just keep playing this fun, highly addictive game! Watch them when you want, pass on other times.. Brilliant! Couldn't recommend it more! Wish more games used this formula..

The controls are really easy and the joystick works no matter what your finger is on the screen. all the monsters and enemies look great and your character although it was not customizable still looks pretty cool. It has elements of more classic games while still remaining modern with controls upgrade ability on items that you can equip on your character and level upgrades. It's a really fun game to try and it's easy to get addicted to.

Great game, I love the concept and the levels. Only have a few issues with crashing after I die and get sent back to the menu, and I feel the hero's you have to purchase are a little pricey. Does have a great Ad system which doesn't spam you after every level which is hard to find, keep up the good work can't wait for the next update

I do truly love the game. been playing it nonstop. but yes, I'm on chapter 3 and have notices that in the first 5 room, 3 to 4 hits kills an enemy. the rest of the floor, unless you get lucky enough with attack boosts, it takes forever to kill anything. and range projectiles take way too much health off. getting git by one can be a game changer. and the tree stump boss makes or breaks a run. all it does is jump. can attack it if its jumping. he needs a little tweeking badly

The one that every game like this tries to copy. Archero presents an almost perfect balance between challenge and reward. Great graphics, smooth gameplay, a wide variety of enemy types, and a straight-forward progression system. I do wish that the in-level rewards weren't quite so stingy, and I would love to see a mode with no level cap, but these are tiny gripes about an otherwise perfect game!

so far it's the best mobile game I've played. gameplay is super fun, there isn't a need to make In app purchases, and the upgrade system is pretty great. I feel that the only thing it's missing is a extra life system. I know you can use diamonds to revive. but you can only revive once per play through. I think there should be at least 2 or 3 revives. but other than that. it's great.

Fun and addictive. My old review complained about the ads cutting the audio from my podcasts. Since then I have noticed the ads no longer do this. Has me feeling like I was listened to. This game is a fun little thing to play for a few mins at a time. Easy to continue if you had to close out the game in the middle of a run. Can be grindy if you don't spend money but I like that challenge as it makes getting high up there even more rewarding.

I like the progression. The play is challenging and frustrating in a good way. I like that you can play a long time, and not run in to a wall that can only be breached by money or boons that only money can buy. The enemies are cute, but it's hard to tell what some of them are. The tornado throwers are confusing, and why do the ghosts throw electric nunchuks.

Yup. It's a winner. Perfect game for the mobile platform. Has great elements of an RPG. Learning curve is there, but it's a game that's actually enjoyable to die and try again. The progression system is well made. You don't feel pushed to buy AIPs. I'd like to see my "stats" on the pause page, the upgrades are listed, but I'd like to know my total attack buff etc. Overall 5 stars and hats off to the dev.

This game is a lot of fun! Graphics look nice. Lots of ways to improve your character. You don't need to spend money to play. Ads are used (To pay for the "free" game), but not overwhelming which is great. I like that upgrades can be bought using ads instead of money. Suggestion is to have an explanation of upgrades when they are offered mid level. Great job!

Very fun I love this game easy to pick up hard to put down very fun overall. but sadly everything good has something wrong with it. The one thing that is odd about this game is the shooting mechanism. When you stop running you can shoot. Well I think it would be nice if there was and option to change the way you could shoot or maybe have an option where you can change the controls. Idk it seems like a good Idea to me. overall a great game very nice well done.

Very fun game. I think the level difficulty, prizes/rewards, and stop-to-shoot aspects are perfect. The third level even changes up pace with the waves which keeps the game fresh. One part I think should be added is the ability to actually see what upgrades are doing in a quantitative way. For example, the critical damage has a "minor" and "master" but I have no idea what that actually did. I think the wait time for "lightning energy" is a little drawn out as well.

Not a bad game. pretty fun gameplay but the difficulty curve is a little intense. I think either scaling it back or increasing equipment drops would make this an excellent game. *Edit* Now the longest I've played a game but I'm having the same issue that most people have, level 7 is too hard. Need more equipment to drop or tone the difficulty down just a touch. I like the new additions though. This game is a lot of fun.

I Really Like this Game! It is a definite stress reliever shooting down the baddies and also leveling up your character is cool as well. You have to 'think' about which powerups are going to be useful for you as you go through the levels. And you get to choose which style of attack suits you best. I definitely prefer the sharpshooting arrows. Good Game!

Honestly one of my favorite games to play, you can pick up different abilities each playthrough to see which ones you like and what's the most effective, the levels are just hard enough for you to be satisfied when you beat a world, and the gems are uncommon but not rare. Even when you run out of energy you can watch 4 ads a day to get extra runs if you don't want to wait for it to replenish. Really well made and loads of fun!!

I see copycat games like this popping up all over the place and it's quite annoying. As far as I remember, this has been the original game of this type for quite some time, at least the first I encountered. I'd like to give it the 5 stars it deserves for it's originality. Also, the nice graphics and diverse enemy roster and equipment collection it has. I'll admit, I've played a few with some better bells and whistles, but for what it is, this game's pretty good üëç

Fun. Rogue-lite elements, but with potential progression between runs makes it feel satisfying to replay and keep playing. Feel a little stronger and smarter every run or so. Doesn't seem aggressive in microtransactions. Energy system isn't too annoying, mostly just keeps you from spending way too much time on the game. Would prefer unlimited runs, but it's a minor nitpick because it seems generous enough to not impede play time much. Good game.

My most favorite game!! I give the controls 5 stars. The game play only 3 stars because the game its self can be a bit glitchy, a long with ads. Sometimes after watching an ad my whole screen will go black and I have to start the game over. I simply try to avoid the ads when I can. And last I give the graphics 5 stars because this game is awesome. Please keep up the good work, maybe add a sandbox mode where you can make your own levels, that would be cool. Thank you.

I LOVE this game. This is one of the few mobile games I can actually enjoy playing day in and day out. The game is challenging without being backbreaking hard. The weapons and abilities are fun to play around with and test out new combinations. My only issues are with the energy system. it should be either brought down to 3 per attempt or you increase your max pool as you beat higher levels. Also I feel like the armor types aren't that useful especially in the higher levels.

Its really simple but at the same time its addicting. The game runs well and doesnt lag at all. The energy cap is somewhat annoying but by the time your done with the run it comes back so you can do another. Some people are saying it's pay to win which i really dont see, the game itself with out paying, gives you all you need to progress.

I love this game to be honest. The concept of needing to be stationary to attack is really interesting to me. The balance of luck and skill in every game is great, where even the best players can get stuck in a bad run and have to improvise while weaker players can sometimes end up with great chance and make it through a hard chapter. There aren't too many ads unless you choose to use them, I think. The little in game notifications for upgrades can be annoying, but that's a personal preference.

I love this game I play it all the time. It's challenging but not without reward. It doesn't hold your hand and getting items and currency is much easier and fulfilling than most games. The progression is amazing and the game play doesn't get nearly as boring and repetitive as every other mobile game. The only nit-pick I'd have is maybe a way or an option to get all the heroes. Keep the pay option so you can still make money, but just make it really hard to get or a limited time event to unlock

This is my favorite phone game. The content is challenging, but I get better personally and progress my gear steadily without spending money. The ads are minimal and unobtrusive. I've seen other reviews complain about the difficulty, but the game just takes some practice. There is also gear and skill strategies that I prefer for specific levels. Great job developers.

fun game a little too dificult to complete some of the levels though. Update, After playing this game for a while now I have to say it's one of my favorites. It's challenging and has a good feel to it. Leveling up is rather slow without paying for jewels so you can open chests to get new equipment but you do get free chests. The chests seem to have a a lot of duplicate items though and no way to get rid of the ones you don't need or want. you should add some sort of exchange feature.

This is a roguelite gauntlet run type game where with each start is completely different than before and as you run through levels killing enemies. As you level up you are presented with a couple random upgrades to either attack, health, damage, etc. So each run is totally different. Very fun. And the variety of enemies makes it fun too. Hope there were more levels, weapons, and powers but it's still really fun just as it is.

This is a great game! For those who like to casually play and/or competitively play this is a all around pretty good game...I like the challenge it gives when you "hit a wall" it just means you have to grind for better equipment or you can take the easy route and pay. I see no problem in a game being challenging. They're not fun when it's easy.

Love the art style. The base shooting mechanic took some getting used to. You have to stop moving and it auto shoots until you move again. But with a little time and practice it feels good. Addictive leveling mechanic as your character improves. I would like to see some customization options for your archer but the gameplay itself is solid and enjoyable. I was pleasantly surprised at how fun this game is.

Love this game! No matter how many times i put it down I end up reinstalling it. Which I can do freely since I save my progress through Google (a prerequisite for any game before money is spent). This game has nice amounts of updates to the game. New upgrades, events, challanges, etc., have kept the game enticing for over a year. If you havent tried Archero, youre missing out. There is even a Battle Pass feature for those of us who like to pay a little to have the upper hand.

Been playing for a while, it was nice to find a mobile game that actually required you to engage in the gameplay. Fun rogue-like elements with a lot of different weapons and armor options to change the feel of the game every time you play. Biggest drawback is items and hero need to be upgraded to get their max benefits, but can cost a lot of the in-game currency (free to earn but purchasable). Ads are all optional and unintrusive, best model I've seen for free games.

Absolutely love the game, I'm super far into it too, almost to the point of waiting for new levels to be released.~~ I'm still this far into the game, still love it, and the error was fixed so I no longer have those crashes! I've played this game nearly since it came out and it's my favorite! Keep improving it please!!! content: At first I thought this was going to be one of those 'ad-spammy' games that you had to 'buy into or would never win' - types. But upon further examination of this game, I have concluded that this is one of the best phone games there is right now. The game is fun without being too easy. The game is hard without it being too frustrating. It's that perfect middle spot that makes me want to come back again. Also I like that there is a lot of customization options in the game!

Downloaded it from a Pewdiepie video, it's really fun and something nice to pass the time. Very challenging at times, but the game helps you level up and be able to defeat the levels. I wish there was some sort of interaction between players. It tell you how far you are against other people, but I would like to see or compete against other players a little more.

Very well done. More mobile games need to be like this. It's fun, the ads aren't constantly in your face and required to continue, and it doesn't seem to cripple your progression if you don't pay money or watch dozens of ads. If you made a few changes and released it on a console or for PC, I'd even buy it as a stand alone game. You wouldn't have to change too much, just being able to play it without energy requirements and with a controller would go far.

Would be nice if I could swap between multiple email accounts and have more playthroughs. It's too hard to get my main account to get noticed and sync data after i get through playing an optional build account. Other than that it's a great game. As long as you're not in a big hurry you don't have to spend a dime to enjoy the challenge and learn to move on with skill rather than brute strength or overpowered equips. It's hard but not impossible and much more entertaining than spending

I would hope to see a better balance in availability of getting new gear, the drop table seems nearly non-existent on Android. I've been playing for a few weeks yet I have nearly nothing but commons and only receive duplicates from chests, it's quite frustrating as the game-play itself is so enjoyable. More levels in combat skills(instead of the max of 10 levels)would be a refreshing addition to such a good game, it's one of my favorites, well done developers ü§ò

Easily the best mobile game I've played. The ad experience is minimal and your choice. I enjoy the balance of the gameplay. The mixture of luck, difficulty, and skill is just right. One of the few games that I feel like I can overcome obstacles in future replays or if I levelup enough. The is the one game I don't see myself deleting after a few months.

Even though it uses energy per run and it takes long to regain it, it doesn't feel like you can't play or you have to pay because the runs you play are long enough for you to be satisfied after to playing 3 or 4 runs. If you wanna play more you can just watch an ad or 10-30 secs and there you go, another try. I usually don't play in smartphones, I think it's annoying and the controllers are dull, but they managed to make the controlls just fine and gameplay fun in a ranged autoattack rogelite

Love this game. Endless replay value. Update: The new ads for Smashing Four are almost a minute long. I understand supporting the game with ads, but this over 30-second ad tips the scale the wrong way for me. If this trend continues i will be forced to uninstall the only game i have left that doesn't play too many ads. Please don't join the others that I've uninstalled.

There is an inovative combat system where you can only fire arrows at enemys when standing still making you think more about positioning and also only using one hand. The upgrades are fun and come quick enough that you won't be bored with garbage upgrades. It has some systems for replayabilty, making new runs more fun. However, the game has an energy system, limiting how many times you can play. I'd be against this but since everthing is random it prevents you from restarting to get better luck.

Very solid game, more addicting than just playing to kill time, you get to a point where you're actually debating watching an ad just to play again, lol. at first it seemed pretty simple but picked up quickly. The item and loot system could use some attention as well as the RNG for abilities per round/level. Often times you'll get the same ability or even 3 in a row... Definitely a great game though!

This is one of those rare gems that is brilliant in its simplicity. The control scheme just works, though it's a bit touchy at first, as you're either still or sprinting. Upgrades aren't too costly, and scale well. Level generation and randomized skills ensures a fresh feel and new challenges every playthrough, while the choice of multiple skills prevents the game from being too luck based or difficult. The ads aren't in your face like many mobile games, and the stamina costs are reasonable.

I absolutely love this game. I only have three ideas for this game. One, i think the energy should take less time to recharge. Two, I believe the scrolls should be used on upgrading equipment only rather than using coins as well. Three, after unlocking a skill you should be able to upgrade it specifically rather than than using random selection.

Fun little 3rd person shooter. Uncomplicated control(s), straightforward gameplay, well balanced levels, weapons, armor, and monsters. And it really is nice to play a game that is NOT pay to win as I have yet to encounter a world / dungeon / level / boss I wasn't able to overcome after a few attempts with smart gameplay.. A couple of suggestions I'd love to see implemented.... Show onscreen what the player's current Crit % and Attack Speed is at. As it is right now they're a mystery.

The designers of this game managed to pull off something that every designer tries to do but most fail: to come up with something simple yet novel. In this game, you don't press a button to shoot. Instead, your character shoots automatically, but stops shooting when you move (to dodge enemies and projectiles). The f2p model is pretty good and not cancer-feeling the way most mobile apps are. I do wish there were a permanent upgrade you could purchase for cash. Other than that, great work devs!

I LOVE IT and its addictive. :) I also met the love of my life while he was playing this game so I have good memories tied to it. Only issue I have is sometimes after I clear a room I end up speeding out of the room into the next one and miss the guy that gives items because they spawned a little late. I also wish I could play this without internet or at least some of it so I could play it in the car. So just slow down to not miss items and if you have data then no issue! It also runs SMOOTHLY.

Polished, fun grinding game where you aren't required to spend money. I have a few requests and suggestions to improve the game: 1. Implement co-op features permanently. 2. Fusing items should require two of the same item, not three. 3. Remove the energy system entirely as it's mostly redundant (progressing gives you tons of it). 4. Smoothen out curve for required XP/level-up. Later levels should give you more XP. With these changes I think this game would be amazing!

Very Fun. If you like rogue lite, dungeon crawler games, you will like is one. The rpg progression aspects makes it more enjoyable, rewarding and allows you to make progress without feeling like you are grinding. If I could improve two things, it would be the option to have a fixed D-pad or increased responsiveness in the controls. Also, I wish the enemy projectiles stood out from your own a bit more. It can be easy to lose track of incoming fire after all the upgrades.

Besides the game lagging at times too often when you get into the Higher/ Harder rounds. 1. With so many enemies popping up on you. 2. Within the level ups all the way to the max level, after picking all your attributes like Multishot, double front arrows, etc. 3. With 1 and 2 being combined and basically happening more then it should, it's like the game doesn't have a bug fixed over that problem of too much going on in the game at once, causing the game to lagg out.

Excelent game. They implemented ads such that you chose when to view them. You are never forced to watch an ad. Awesome gameplay that scales in difficulty well. You also gain items to level up while not playing. This means you can walk away for a week and come back with items which allow you to level up. Very well done game.

This is a great game that you can sink some time into. Below are some things I would love to see! 1. Scale up previous levels once your profile hits a certain level. 2. Specific pieces of equipment have higher drop rates in certain levels! (I.e the bow has a higher drop rate on normal levels 1-5) 2. Loadout system would be awesome! 3. Ability to see character stats along with skills when paused. Keep up the great work on the updates!!

I love this game! At first the energy system was super annoying, but as I got better at playing it became irrelevant. I love figuring out the patterns of the monsters and the challenge of dodging at just the right time! The power-ups you get to choose from every level are awesome and just the right combination can make you feel so OP. 10/10 would reccomend! Im also loving this new update! Oh and probably the biggest plus is that there are no ads unless you ask for them and you can win w/o them :)

Archero is an enchanted hybrid between a top view shooter and dungeon crawler style game. Shoot through waves of enemies and survive as long as you can. This game is nice. I love the main menu music, love the gameplay, love the power-ups and pets who assist you on your quest, and there's hardly any ads. My only critic would be the lack of background music in the gameplay makes it feel a little bland. But overall it's a good game.

This game sets the standard for mobile games. Easy to jump in, fun to play with one hand, no invasive ads! I'm at the point where progression is sluggish but it's still fun to play regardless and the chest rewards usually change the game. I love that the third level changes the formula where mobs come in times waves, it's pretty frantic. I wish the elemental moves were more useful because I often go for additional shots and buffs over them.

Fantastic Rogue-lite with minimally intrusive ads. It's so rare for a free game to not shove ads in your face, but even the few Archero does have are optional. Likewise, the in game purchases are wholly unnecessary to enjoy the game, and also not shoved in your face. Couple that with engaging, challenging and fun gameplay and you've got the first mobile game I've played in a while that I actively recommend to people.

This game does a really good job of meshing simple and complex game play. The concept is simple, shoot enemies, you only shoot when you're not moving. Then it mixes in the ability to level up in combat with powerful upgrades from increased attack speed, chaining attacks to multiple enemies, or even summoning temporary pets on attack. Out of combat it offers a weapon/armor/item system that allows for more moderate permanent boosts. Overall its an addicting game thats a lot of fun.

This is a very fun little game. It's addictive and satisfying. The attack speed and additional arrow skills along with ricochet and other similar effects are the most beneficial skills to take when levelling up in my experience. I like that you continue to level up and that you can continue to play previously beaten levels to help grind your way to a more powerful character instead of starting over from scratch.
